if gem = Gemstone.find_by(slug: "black-moonstone")
  gem.meaning_content = "Table of Contents\n\nToggle\n\n• What is Black Moonstone?\n• Common Properties of Black Moonstone\n• Black Moonstone Meaning\n• History and Where is Black Moonstone found\n• Healing Properties of Black Moonstone\n• Emotional healing properties of Black Moonstone\n• Physical healing properties of Black Moonstone\n• Metaphysical healing properties of Black Moonstone\n\n• Black Moonstone meaning and its connection to chakra\n• How to use Black Moonstone\n• What are the various ways to cleanse Black Moonstone\n• Best combination of Black Moonstone and other crystals\n• Black Moonstone and Lepidolite\n• Black Moonstone and Hematite\n• Black Moonstone and Jet\n\n• Other frequently asked questions:\n\n## What is Black Moonstone?\n\nBlack moonstone is a type of feldspar that is characterised by its inky black colouration. The name “black moonstone” is derived from its inky black colouration, caused by inclusions of hematite. \n\nIt is a relatively rare variety of moonstones and is prized for its unique appearance. This stone has a shimmery, iridescent quality that makes it visually stunning. \n\nIt is said to have a calming, soothing energy and is believed to be helpful in promoting restful sleep. \n\nBlack moonstone is also thought to be a stone of protection, helping to guard against negative energies and psychic attacks.\n\nBlack Moonstone has a unique feminine energy. It is connected to the divine feminine and goddess energy. It is a stone that can help you to connect with your intuition and inner wisdom. \n\nBlack moonstones can also help to bring emotional healing and balance. This stone is said to be helpful in dealing with issues such as PMS, cramps, menopause and fertility.\n\n## Common Properties of Black Moonstone\n\n• Aids in the development of psychic abilities\n\n• Aids in meditation and attuning to the higher self\n\n• Helps to calm and center the emotions\n\n• Aids in the understanding and release of karmic patterns\n\n• Aids in accessing the Akashic Records\n\n• Helps in getting rid of negative and toxic emotions\n\n• Establishes a connection with the feminine energy\n\n• Helps with digestive tract issues\n\n## Black Moonstone Meaning\n\nProtection, Grounding, and Attunement\n\nAs a member of the feldspar family, moonstone is a potassium aluminium silicate. Its name is derived from an old English word meaning “moon glow,” and indeed, moonstone has an unearthly sheen. When polished, this iridescent stone reflects light in a way that makes it appear to shimmer and change colour. \n\nBlack moonstone’s meaning is linked with its ability to protect and ground the wearer. It is said to be a stone of attunement, providing a connection to the energies and wisdom of the moon. Moonstone is also known as a stone of new beginnings.\n\nIt is more like an all-rounder crystal that is known to bring good luck and fortune. It is also a stone that is said to be able to grant wishes.\n\nBlack moonstone is said to be a stone of protection, helping to deflect negative energy and providing a safe haven for the wearer. It is also said to be a stone of grounding, helping to anchor the wearer in times of change or upheaval.\n\nBlack moonstone is an excellent crystal for those who are seeking to attune to the energies and wisdom of the moon. It is also a helpful stone for those who are working to manifest their dreams and goals.\n\n## History and Where is Black Moonstone found\n\nBlack Moonstone was first discovered in India, and it is said to be one of the most ancient stones in existence. It is also found in Australia, Brazil, China, Madagascar, Mexico, Russia, and the United States.\n\nThis stone is believed to be a powerful talisman of protection, and it is said to be especially helpful to women. It is also thought to be helpful in times of great change or upheaval. In the olden times, it was used as a protection against evil spirits.\n\nIn the current times, Black Moonstone is a significant stone for new beginnings. It is also known as a stone of fertility and is thought to be helpful in conception and pregnancy. It is also said to be helpful in easing menstrual cramps and menopausal symptoms.\n\n## Healing Properties of Black Moonstone\n\nThere any many healing properties of Black Moonstone which involves healthy emotional, mental and physical well-being. As Black Moonstone meaning stands for protecting the wearer, these healing properties make sure you stay away from the negative energy and thoughts in every aspect.\n\n## Emotional healing properties of Black Moonstone\n\nBlack Moonstone is a powerful stone for emotional healing. It has multiple benefits which keep the emotions away from negative thoughts and energy.\n\n– Helps to heal deep emotional wounds\n\n– Aids in the release of emotional baggage\n\n– Allows you to forgive yourself and others\n\n– Encourages emotional stability and inner strength\n\n– Helps get rid of past traumas by dealing with them peacefully\n\nIt is an excellent stone for anyone who is struggling with depression, anxiety, or any other emotional issue. Black Moonstone can help to ground and stabilise your emotions, providing a sense of calm and peace.\n\n It is also a helpful stone for anyone who is going through a difficult life transition, as it can provide strength and support during times of change.\n\nBlack Moonstone is unique in the way it helps one deal with past trauma. It enables self-love by making you realise your worth and how to begin to trust yourself. When your self-esteem and self-worth increase, you gain confidence. \n\nThis helps in dealing with anxiety, self-doubt and depression. It is a perfect stone to keep you emotionally healthy.\n\n## Physical healing properties of Black Moonstone\n\nBlack Moonstone is also known for its physical healing properties. It is said to be helpful in treating the following:\n\n– Aids with Digestive issues\n\n– Reduces and relieves headaches and stress\n\n– Helps deal better with Insomnia\n\n– Aids with issues like PMS\n\n– Enhances the overall reproductive health and helps dealing with reproductive issues\n\nBlack Moonstone is also known to be helpful in detoxifying the body and balancing hormones. It is a stone of protection and is said to be helpful in shielding the body from negative energy. \n\nThis crystal has the ability to connect with the feminine energy which in turn enhances the entire reproductive health.\n\nBlack Moonstone is known to be a powerful stone for women’s health. It is said to be helpful in easing menstrual cramps, PMS symptoms, and menopause. \n\nIt is also said to be helpful in regulating the menstrual cycle and increasing fertility. Black Moonstone is also known to be helpful in childbirth, as it is said to help ease labour pains.\n\n## Metaphysical healing properties of Black Moonstone\n\nBlack Moonstone is a powerful stone for metaphysical healing. It has multiple benefits which help to open up the chakras and cleanse the aura.\n\n– Helps to connect with the higher self\n\n– Aids in psychic development\n\n– Increases intuition and psychic awareness\n\n– Enhances spiritual growth\n\n– Facilitates astral travel\n\nBlack Moonstone is an excellent stone for anyone who is looking to develop their psychic abilities. It can help to open up the chakras and increase psychic awareness. \n\nIt is also a helpful stone for anyone who is seeking spiritual growth, as it can facilitate astral travel and enhance spiritual experiences. \n\nThose going through hindrances in life and feel their path is blocked, should use Black Moonstone. This will ensure you are able to explore your true self and true potential.\n\n## Black Moonstone meaning and its connection to chakra\n\nThe Black moonstone is to be connected to the root chakra. The root chakra is responsible for grounding us and providing a sense of security. It is associated with the element of earth and is believed to help us feel more connected to the physical world. \n\nBlack moonstone is said to be helpful for those who feel disconnected from the physical world or who have a hard time grounding themselves. The crown chakra is associated with our connection to the divine, our sense of spirituality, and our ability to connect to the higher realms. \n\nIt is helpful for those who are working on their root chakra. Black moonstone helps in re-establishing the connection with self and balancing the crown chakra.\n\nIf the crown chakra is not balanced, one may feel disconnected from the physical world and have difficulty grounding themselves.\n\nWhen the crown chakra is out of balance, we may feel disconnected from our spiritual side or we may struggle to connect with the higher realms. \n\n## How to use Black Moonstone\n\nBlack Moonstone is a powerful crystal that can be used to cleanse and purify your energy. It can also be used to protect you from negative energy and to help you connect with your higher self. \n\nBlack Moonstone can also be used to release old patterns and behaviours that are no longer serving you.\n\nThere are different ways to use Black Moonstone which are very effective in terms of providing benefits. Below are the best ways to use them:\n\n• As Jewellery\n\nUsing Black Moonstone as jewellery is a great way to keep its energy close to you. It can be made into bracelets, necklaces, rings, or earrings. It is also one of the easiest ways to use it. Wearing Black Moonstone will help in grounding your inner self and promoting a sense of calm.\n\n• In your environment\n\nYou can also place Black Moonstone in your environment, such as in your home or office. This will help to purify the energy in these spaces and to protect you from negative energy.\n\n• In meditation\n\nBlack Moonstone can be used in meditation to help you connect with your higher self. It can also be used to release old patterns and behaviours that are no longer serving you.\n\n• As a crystal elixir\n\nCrystal elixirs are a great way to use the energy of crystals. You can make a Black Moonstone elixir by adding a few drops of Black Moonstone essence to a glass of water. This elixir can be taken daily to help cleanse and purify your energy.\n\nWhen using Black Moonstone, it is important to cleanse it regularly. Read on to know more about cleansing Black Moonstone.\n\n## What are the various ways to cleanse Black Moonstone\n\nThere are many ways to cleanse Black Moonstone. You can use running Water, Smudging, Visualization, Reiki, and Sound Healing.\n\n• Using running water\n\nThe simplest way to cleanse your Black Moonstone is to hold it under running water. You can do this for a few minutes. Be careful while using this method as exposing any moonstone crystal to water for a longer duration can be harmful. \n\nKnow more about Can moonstone go in the water?\n\n• Smudging\n\nYou can also cleanse your Black Moonstone by smudging it with sage smoke.\n\nTo do this, light a sage stick and hold your Black Moonstone in the smoke for a few minutes.\n\n• Visualization\n\nAnother way to cleanse your Black Moonstone is to visualize white light surrounding it.\n\nSee the light surround your stone and fill it with positive energy.\n\n• Reiki\n\nIf you are attuned to Reiki, you can also use this energy healing technique to cleanse your Black Moonstone.\n\nTo do this, simply hold your stone in your hands and channel Reiki energy into it.\n\n• Sound Healing\n\nYou can also cleanse your Black Moonstone with sound healing.\n\nOne way to do this is to ring a bell near your stone.\n\nYou can also use a singing bowl or tuning fork. Simply hold your Black Moonstone near the sound source and allow the vibrations to cleanse it.\n\n## Best combination of Black Moonstone and other crystals\n\n## Black Moonstone and Lepidolite\n\nThese two crystals work together to create a sense of calm and peace. Lepidolite is known as the “peace stone” because it helps to reduce stress and anxiety. Black Moonstone is a powerful stone for grounding and protection. It can help to shield you from negative energy and promote positive vibes.\n\n## Black Moonstone and Hematite\n\nHematite is a stone that is known for its ability to ground and protect. It can help to shield you from negative energy and promote positive vibes. Black Moonstone is a powerful stone for grounding and protection. It can help to deflect negative energy and promote positive vibes. These two crystals make a great team for protecting your energy.\n\n## Black Moonstone and Jet\n\nJet and Black Moonstone together create a very powerful combination for deflecting negative energy. Jet is known as a “psychic shield” and can help to protect you from negative thoughts and energy. Black Moonstone is a powerful stone for grounding and protection. It can help to deflect negative energy and promote positive vibes.\n\n## Other frequently asked questions:\n\n• Black moonstone vs labradorite. Are they same?\n\nNo, black moonstones and labradorite are not the same. Black moonstone is a type of feldspar, while labradorite is a type of plagioclase. The key difference between black moonstone and labradorite is that black moonstone has a lower refractive index than labradorite. As a result, the black moonstone appears darker than the labradorite.\n\n• What is black moonstone zodiac?\n\nBlack moonstone is a zodiac stone for people born under the sign of Scorpio. It is also said to be helpful for people born under the sign of Pisces.\n\n• How to know if a Black Moonstone is real?\n\nThere are a few key things to look for when trying to determine whether or not a black moonstone is real. First, check to see if the stone is translucent; if it is, then it is likely a fake. \n\nSecond, check the surface of the stone for any flaws or imperfections; if the stone is flawless, then it is likely a fake. \n\nFinally, hold the stone up to a light source and look for any inclusions or blemishes; if the stone is flawless, then it is likely a fake.\n\n• Is Larvikite same as Black Moonstone?\n\nLarvikite and Black Moonstone are not the same. Black Moonstone is a type of feldspar, while Larvikite is a type of igneous rock. Though confused often, these two stones are different. The key difference is that Larvikite has a more fibrous or streaked appearance, while Black Moonstone is more smooth and glassy.\n\nInterested in other moonstone crystals? Here is an article about Peach Moonstone’s meaning and it’s benefits."
