if gem = Gemstone.find_by(slug: "black-onyx")
  gem.water_safety_content = "Black Onyx is resistant to water and brief contact with it is safe; however, it should not be submerged for extended periods to avoid damage to its appearance and durability. Salt water can be particularly harmful to Black Onyx, causing discoloration or damage, and as such should be avoided to maintain the integrity of the stone.\n\nCareful cleaning of Black Onyx involves using a damp cloth without soap, gently brushing with a soft brush and mild soap if needed, and avoiding abrasive cleaning methods such as mechanical cleaners. While Black Onyx can be cleansed with tap water, or placed in salt for purifying purposes, excessive contact should be avoided due to potential long-term effects and alterations.\n\nBlack Onyx should be stored away from direct sunlight and harsh chemicals, and cleansed with mild soap and water or alternative methods such as sound vibrations and smudging.\n\nTable of Contents\n\nToggle\n\n• Is Black Onyx Water Safe?\n• Can Black Onyx Go In Salt Water?\n• Can Black Onyx Go In Tap Water?\n• Can Black Onyx Go In the Sun?\n• Can Black Onyx Go In Salt?\n\n• The Water Tolerance of Black Onyx\n• Understanding the Durability of Black Onyx\n• The Dos and Don’ts of Water Exposure\n\n• How to Cleanse Black Onyx With Water?\n• Drying Methods Post-Water Exposure\n\n• Protecting Black Onyx from Negative Energy via Water Cleansing\n• Black Onyx’s Healing Properties and Water\n\n• Identifying Real Black Onyx Before Water Immersion\n• Can Black Onyx Be Worn in the Shower or While Swimming?\n• Storing Black Onyx After Water Contact\n• How to Cleanse Black Onyx Without Water?\n• Sound Vibrations and Black Onyx\n• Smudging Black Onyx for Energetic Cleansing\n\n• How to Charge Black Onyx?\n• Charging Black Onyx with Natural Elements\n\n• Caring for Black Onyx\n• Caring for Your Black Onyx Jewelry\n• Summary\n• Frequently Asked Questions\n• Can Black Onyx go in water?\n• How can I cleanse my Black Onyx with water?\n• Can Black Onyx go in the sun?\n• How can I cleanse my Black Onyx without water?\n• How can I charge my Black Onyx?\n\n## Is Black Onyx Water Safe?\n\nA beautiful illustration of black onyx jewelry\n\nThe general safety of Black Onyx in water is a subject that often piques curiosity, especially for those who wear Black Onyx jewelry. The Black Onyx stone is reputed for its remarkable resistance to water, making brief contact with the liquid generally safe. So, if you’re wearing your favorite Black Onyx ring while washing your hands or caught in a bit of rain, rest easy – your precious stone is perfectly safe.\n\nHowever, like many things in life, balance is key. Although submersion in water is possible, Black Onyx should not stay underwater for extended periods. Over time, extended contact with water can potentially affect the appearance and durability of the stone. So, the next time you’re heading for a swim or about to immerse yourself in a relaxing bath, it might be best to leave your Black Onyx jewelry safely aside.\n\nThis guideline also extends to the cleansing process of Black Onyx stones. While water can be used for cleansing, it is recommended to do so with caution. Here are some tips for cleaning Black Onyx:\n\n• Use warm water and mild soap\n\n• Use a soft brush to gently clean the stone\n\n• Avoid using mechanical or ultrasonic cleaning methods as they might pose a risk to the stone.\n\n## Can Black Onyx Go In Salt Water?\n\nThe situation becomes more complex with salt water. The impact of salt water on Black Onyx is a topic that isn’t as straightforward as one might think. There are two aspects to consider – cleansing and exposure. For cleansing purposes, Black Onyx can be placed in a bowl of salt water overnight, relying on the purifying properties of salt. However, this should be done sparingly to avoid any potential alterations in appearance and energy.\n\nAs for prolonged exposure, like wearing your Black Onyx jewelry while swimming in the ocean, it’s a slightly different story. Given the lack of specific information about the long-term effects of salt water on Black Onyx and its known sensitivity to prolonged water exposure and harsh chemicals, caution is recommended. So, before taking a dip in the ocean, it might be best to remove your Black Onyx pieces to keep them in their optimal condition.\n\n## Can Black Onyx Go In Tap Water?\n\nTap water is a common element in our everyday lives. So, is it safe for Black Onyx to come into contact with tap water? The answer is yes, but with some stipulations. For cleaning purposes, Black Onyx can safely come in contact with tap water, provided it isn’t soaked for too long. Lukewarm tap water is especially efficient for cleansing and recharging Black Onyx, offering a practical and accessible way to care for your Black Onyx pieces.\n\nMoreover, when cleaning Black Onyx, rinsing it under running tap water and visualizing the removal of negative energy is recommended. This method not only cleanses the physical stone but also helps to reset its energy, enhancing the Black Onyx healing properties. However, remember to avoid leaving Black Onyx submerged in tap water for extended periods, as this could potentially affect the stone’s appearance and durability.\n\n## Can Black Onyx Go In the Sun?\n\nSunlight, while essential for life, is not always a friend to our precious stones. For Black Onyx, one should avoid extended exposure to direct sunlight. Over time, constant exposure to sunlight can cause the vibrant jet black color of Black Onyx to fade. More importantly, it could potentially drain the stone’s energy, diminishing its healing properties.\n\nWhile brief exposure to sunlight can charge Black Onyx, close monitoring is crucial to prevent potential damage. So, if you’re planning to sunbathe, it might be a good idea to tuck your Black Onyx jewelry away in a shaded spot.\n\n## Can Black Onyx Go In Salt?\n\nHaving explored the effects of salt water on Black Onyx, let’s consider the impact of direct contact with salt. For cleansing purposes, Black Onyx can be placed in a bowl of salt water overnight, utilizing the purifying properties of salt. However, prolonged direct contact with salt may not be recommended due to potential alterations in appearance and energy.\n\nHistorically, salt has been used in various cultures for purification rituals, indicating its significance in cleansing processes. While crystals with a Mohs hardness score of 7 or above are typically considered safe to cleanse with salt and salt water, it’s always best to err on the side of caution, especially with precious stones like Black Onyx. Rock salt, a common type of salt, has also been utilized in these cleansing practices.\n\n## The Water Tolerance of Black Onyx\n\nBlack Onyx Stone in Water\n\nBlack Onyx, a stoic guardian in the realm of gemstones, stands undaunted when met with water. This variety of chalcedony, with its intricate layers of microcrystalline quartz, is not only visually mesmerizing but also structurally adept at handling the occasional dip. Can Black Onyx tolerate the embrace of water? Indeed, the stone’s composition allows for immersion, making it safe for cleaning purposes without the peril of damage. The practicality of this trait ensures that wearers of Black Onyx jewelry can maintain the stone’s pristine condition with little worry.\n\nYet, while Black Onyx may befriend water for brief encounters, it is not one for prolonged dalliances. Excessive exposure can alter the stone’s appearance or weaken its durability, suggesting that there is wisdom in moderation. The question then arises: how does one balance the necessity of cleansing with the desire to preserve the integrity of their Black Onyx treasures?\n\n## Understanding the Durability of Black Onyx\n\nBlack Onyx boasts durability that matches its visual allure. Rated between 6 to 7 on the Mohs hardness scale, this gemstone is less prone to scratches and damage from casual water contact than its softer mineral counterparts. This hardiness ensures that Black Onyx jewelry, including a stunning black onyx ring, when subjected to the rigors of daily wear, retains its composure and continues to symbolize the wearer’s inner strength and self-control. The Mohs scale serves as a trusted guide, indicating that Black Onyx, with its robust nature, can handle the occasional water exposure with grace.\n\nWhat does black onyx symbolize for those who wish to wear black onyx jewelry as a constant companion? This suggests that while the precious stones, such as black onyx, can withstand some elements, it still requires care to maintain its energetic radiance and resilience against daily wear and tear.\n\n## The Dos and Don’ts of Water Exposure\n\nWhen it comes to Black Onyx, the key to preserving its majesty lies in gentle care. Here are some tips for caring for Black Onyx:\n\n• Use a damp cloth to delicately wipe the surface.\n\n• Avoid using soap, as it may seep into its porous surface and cause discoloration.\n\n• It’s perfectly safe to cleanse Black Onyx with lukewarm water for brief periods.\n\n• Avoid using ultrasonic and mechanical cleaning devices, as they are too harsh for the refined nature of Black Onyx and may cause abrasions or loss of integrity to the stone.\n\nBy following these tips, you can ensure that your Black Onyx remains beautiful and well-maintained.\n\nHence, caring for Black Onyx requires a balanced and precise approach. Exposure to water should not be feared but respected, with the understanding that the right methods will maintain the stone’s composure and self-control—just as it maintains ours when worn on the middle finger or carried close to our person.\n\n## How to Cleanse Black Onyx With Water?\n\nA gentle illustration of cleaning black onyx with water\n\nConsidering Black Onyx’s water resistance, using water-based cleansing methods to maintain its sparkle and energy is perfectly safe. Warm water and mild soap make an excellent and safe cleaning solution for Black Onyx. Using this combination, gently clean your Black Onyx jewelry or stones with a soft brush to remove any debris or buildup.\n\nAfter washing, remember to air dry your Black Onyx pieces to maintain their luster and prevent any potential water damage. For necklaces and pendants, the same procedure applies, with the addition of a mild detergent to the warm water for an extra clean effect. This method is both effective and gentle, ensuring your Black Onyx stays in top-notch condition.\n\n## Drying Methods Post-Water Exposure\n\nAfter being cleaned, Black Onyx should air dry, a method that respects its natural composition and preserves its aesthetic appeal. If one is short on time, a gentle pat-down with a paper towel can help prevent any unsightly water spots or streaks, ensuring the gemstone emerges from the cleansing process as visually appealing as ever. This careful attention to the drying process not only preserves the immediate beauty of the Black Onyx but also safeguards its long-term vitality, ensuring it remains a source of strength and balance.\n\nThe care one extends to their Black Onyx after water exposure speaks volumes of the reverence held for this powerful stone. By choosing the right drying methods, one ensures that the Black Onyx retains its capacity to activate inner power and balance energies, just as it did in ancient times when it served as a symbol of protection and good fortune.\n\n## Protecting Black Onyx from Negative Energy via Water Cleansing\n\nBlack Onyx in Cleansing Ritual\n\nWater has long been regarded as a conduit for purification, a medium through which negative energies can be washed away. This age-old wisdom holds true for Black Onyx too, a stone known for its capacity to absorb and transmute these energies. A water cleansing ritual, when performed correctly, can enhance the metaphysical properties of Black Onyx, fortifying its protective shield and supporting emotional stability without compromising the stone’s structure.\n\nSince Black Onyx attracts negative energy, frequent cleansing is necessary to prevent it from becoming overwhelmed, which could potentially result in its fracture. By activating inner strength and courage, Black Onyx serves as a powerful ally in the quest for balance, and water cleansing is a gentle yet potent means to recharge this stone, ensuring it continues to transform negative energy effectively. Additionally, the presence of a quartz crystal can further enhance the cleansing process.\n\n## Black Onyx’s Healing Properties and Water\n\nAmidst the bustling chaos of daily life, Black Onyx stands as a beacon of stability, deterring negative experiences and fostering a sense of good fortune. The black onyx healing properties are amplified through the use of water in cleansing rituals, which not only preserve its physical form but also enhance its spiritual essence. By aiding in detoxification and supporting the immune and skeletal systems, the onyx stones, particularly the black onyx stone, encourage cell regeneration, and the use of water in such rituals may further promote these detoxifying effects.\n\nThe bond between Black Onyx and water goes beyond simple cleansing; it’s a reciprocal interaction that revitalizes both the stone and the spirit. As water enhances the stone’s healing properties, it aids in the regeneration process, imbuing Black Onyx with an even greater ability to balance energies and provide protection in times of need.\n\n## Identifying Real Black Onyx Before Water Immersion\n\nBefore submerging Black Onyx in water for either cleansing or recharging, it’s crucial to first confirm its authenticity. Genuine Black Onyx possesses the following characteristics:\n\n• A vitreous luster\n\n• A specific range in its refractive index that distinguishes it from imitations\n\n• It may not always present as pure black; natural variations can reveal a brownish or greyish tint, yet its polished surface should exude a glossy, waxy luster.\n\nA scratch test, using a material softer than 6 on the Mohs scale, can reveal the real Black Onyx, as its hardness protects it from easy scratches. Furthermore, the coolness of genuine Black Onyx against the skin is a telltale sign of its authenticity, setting it apart from counterfeit stones that may mimic its appearance. Knowledge of these identifying features is crucial in ensuring that one can identify black onyx and be certain that the Black Onyx they wish to cleanse is indeed the storied gemstone of protection and power.\n\n## Can Black Onyx Be Worn in the Shower or While Swimming?\n\nThe query of whether Black Onyx can be worn in the shower or while swimming elicits a complex answer. Although Black Onyx has a high tolerance to water, making it generally safe for such activities, it is the duration of exposure that needs consideration. The stone’s resilience to occasional water contact must be balanced with the understanding that prolonged exposure can lead to dulling or potential color changes.\n\nTherefore, while it is perfectly safe to wear Black Onyx jewelry for short periods in water, it is prudent to remove it before engaging in extended swimming or showering sessions. This practice prevents potential damage and allows the stone to maintain its properties, ensuring that it continues to activate and balance energies as intended.\n\n## Storing Black Onyx After Water Contact\n\nOnce Black Onyx has been in contact with water, its storage is a critical part of its care. To preserve the energetic properties of the stone, it is beneficial to store it in a manner that allows for charging. Here’s how:\n\n• Place it in a bowl of water under the moonlight for 8 hours. This ensures that Black Onyx is dried properly and energetically reinvigorated.\n\n• After charging, store it in a safe and clean place, away from other stones or objects that may scratch or damage it.\n\n• Keep it in a cool and dry environment to prevent any moisture buildup.\n\nBy following these storage guidelines, you can ensure that your Black Onyx remains a powerful protector against negative energy and a supporter of emotional stability.\n\nPurposeful storage of Black Onyx mirrors the stone’s spiritual significance. By caring for it in a way that aligns with its metaphysical properties, one can enhance the stone’s ability to transform negative energies and maintain its potent protective qualities.\n\n## How to Cleanse Black Onyx Without Water?\n\nAn artistic illustration of sound vibrations and black onyx\n\nWhile water is a safe and effective way to cleanse Black Onyx, there are several alternative methods that do not involve water. These methods protect both the physical structure and the vibrational energy of Black Onyx.\n\nOne such method involves the use of dry brown rice. Placing Black Onyx in a bowl of dry brown rice helps to absorb and neutralize negative energies, rejuvenating the stone’s energy. Sound vibrations, such as chants, tuning forks, music, sound bowls, bells, or chimes can also be used to cleanse Black Onyx.\n\n## Sound Vibrations and Black Onyx\n\nSound vibrations offer a unique and effective method for cleaning Black Onyx. This technique leverages the power of sound to cleanse and recharge the stone’s energy. Instruments such as:\n\n• chanting\n\n• singing bowls\n\n• tuning forks\n\n• bells\n\nCrystal cleansing methods can be employed for this process, their sonic vibrations maintaining the clarity and metaphysical properties of Black Onyx. As black onyx symbolize strength and protection, it is essential to keep its energy pure and potent, and being able to identify black onyx is crucial for those seeking its benefits. One such method involves using a quartz crystal, such as rose quartz, which can help amplify the cleansing process.\n\nThe beauty of using sound vibrations lies in its ability to cleanse Black Onyx at a vibrational level. The sonic waves resonate with the stone, shaking off any negative energies and restoring its natural vibrational state. This method doesn’t just cleanse the physical stone, but also rejuvenates its energy, allowing the Black Onyx to function at its full potential.\n\n## Smudging Black Onyx for Energetic Cleansing\n\nSmudging, a traditional practice that employs smoke from burning sage to clear unwanted vibrations, is another effective way to cleanse Black Onyx without water. Sage smudge sticks are commonly used due to their believed properties to clear negative energies.\n\nTo smudge Black Onyx, simply hold the stone in the smoke of a burning sage stick for several seconds. This process is considered effective in removing negative energies and restoring the stone’s natural vibrational state. So, the next time you feel your Black Onyx could use an energy boost, consider giving smudging a try.\n\n## How to Charge Black Onyx?\n\nA serene illustration of charging black onyx with natural elements\n\nMuch like humans, stones also require energy recharging. But, how can we charge Black Onyx? A common method involves leaving it in sunlight for 6 to 12 hours. However, given the sensitivity of Black Onyx to light, this should be done with caution to avoid any potential fading or draining of energy.\n\nMoonlight and rain also serve as harmless cleansing and charging agents for Black Onyx. These natural elements provide a gentle yet effective way to recharge the stone, ensuring the Black Onyx stays vibrant and energetically charged.\n\n## Charging Black Onyx with Natural Elements\n\nApart from sunlight, other natural elements can also charge Black Onyx. One such method involves burying Black Onyx in soil. This allows the stone to absorb the earth’s energies, providing a natural charge that circumvents the risks associated with direct sunlight exposure.\n\nThis method not only charges the stone but also helps maintain its color and energy levels. Even after charging Black Onyx by burying it in soil, it is important to continue avoiding direct sunlight to maintain the stone’s color and energy levels. So, the next time your Black Onyx needs a recharge, consider giving it a little earth therapy.\n\n## Caring for Black Onyx\n\nA graceful illustration of caring for black onyx\n\nCaring for Black Onyx extends beyond just cleansing and charging. To maintain its condition, Black Onyx should not be exposed to harsh chemicals, extreme temperatures, or direct sunlight. Regular cleaning is also crucial to maintain the appearance of Black Onyx. Using a soft, damp cloth, gently remove any dirt or residue without using harsh or abrasive cleaning products.\n\nStorage is another important aspect of caring for Black Onyx. To prevent any potential scratches, Black Onyx should be stored separately from other gemstones. A little care goes a long way in preserving the beauty and energy of your Black Onyx pieces, ensuring they stay in prime condition for years to come.\n\n## Caring for Your Black Onyx Jewelry\n\nCleaning Black Onyx Jewelry\n\nMaintaining Black Onyx jewelry can be compared to nurturing a significant relationship. It requires attention to detail, respect for its nature, and an understanding of its preferences. Prolonged water exposure, for instance, might lead to unwanted changes in the gemstone’s appearance or a reduction in its durability. Similarly, the chemicals found in showers, which may seem innocuous, can be detrimental to the stone, potentially eroding its stoic beauty. Therefore, it is advisable to remove Black Onyx jewelry before stepping into the shower or diving into a pool.\n\nOnce cleansed, Black Onyx should not bask in direct sunlight, which could cause damage akin to that of UV exposure. Instead, it ought to be stored with care, perhaps in a velvet pouch or a padded ring case, separate from other jewelry that might scratch its surface, to preserve its luster and enigmatic presence.\n\n## Summary\n\nFrom understanding the safety of Black Onyx in various elements to discovering how to cleanse and charge it, we’ve covered quite a journey in the world of this mystical gemstone. Proper care, including avoiding prolonged exposure to water, sunlight, and salt, and using appropriate cleansing and charging methods, is key to maintaining its energy and appearance. Whether you wear Black Onyx for its protective properties or simply for its beauty, taking good care of your Black Onyx pieces will ensure they continue to serve you well.\n\n## Frequently Asked Questions\n\n## Can Black Onyx go in water?\n\nYes, Black Onyx can be submerged in water, but prolonged exposure should be avoided to prevent potential damage to its appearance and durability.\n\n## How can I cleanse my Black Onyx with water?\n\nTo cleanse your Black Onyx with water, use warm water and mild soap with a soft brush to gently remove debris and buildup, then air dry the pieces.\n\n## Can Black Onyx go in the sun?\n\nIt’s best to avoid prolonged direct sunlight for Black Onyx as it can cause fading and drain the stone’s energy. Be mindful of brief exposure to sunlight, which can help charge the stone.\n\n## How can I cleanse my Black Onyx without water?\n\nYou can cleanse Black Onyx without water by using sound vibrations, smudging with sage, or burying it in the earth. These methods help maintain the stone’s energy and properties.\n\n## How can I charge my Black Onyx?\n\nYou can charge your Black Onyx by exposing it to sunlight, moonlight, burying it in soil, or using a selenite or clear quartz charger. Try these methods and see which works best for you."
  gem.who_should_not_wear_content = "Black Onyx is not suitable for everyone due to its powerful energy, which can cause physical irritation or allergic reactions in sensitive individuals, lower blood pressure to dangerous levels, and exacerbate symptoms in those with mental health conditions such as depression.\n\nBlack Onyx’s effects on zodiac signs vary; it may benefit signs like Aries, Taurus, and Capricorn, but Gemini individuals should be cautious, and everyone should consider a trial period to assess personal compatibility.\n\nWhile Black Onyx can offer protection, emotional strength, and stability, it’s important to ensure its bold energy aligns with the individual’s personal vibrations, and it should be cleansed regularly to maintain its effectiveness.\n\nTable of Contents\n\nToggle\n\n• Can Anyone Wear Black Onyx?\n• Who Should Not Wear Black Onyx?\n• Black Onyx and Zodiac Signs\n• Can Aries Wear Black Onyx?\n• Can Taurus Wear Black Onyx?\n• Can Gemini Wear Black Onyx?\n• Can Cancer Wear Black Onyx?\n• Can Leo Wear Black Onyx?\n• Can Virgo Wear Black Onyx?\n• Can Libra Wear Black Onyx?\n• Can Scorpio Wear Black Onyx?\n• Can Sagittarius Wear Black Onyx?\n• Can Capricorn Wear Black Onyx?\n• Can Aquarius Wear Black Onyx?\n• Can Pisces Wear Black Onyx?\n\n• Can Black Onyx Influence Your Emotional Well-Being?\n• Is There Anyone Who Shouldn’t Wear Black Onyx Jewelry for Health Reasons?\n• Could Wearing Black Onyx Affect Your Energy Levels?\n• Are There Specific Times When You Shouldn’t Wear Black Onyx?\n• How Can You Tell If Black Onyx Isn’t Right for You?\n• Who Should Wear Black Onyx?\n• Benefits of Wearing Black Onyx\n• How to Wear Black Onyx?\n\n• How to Safely Experiment With Black Onyx?\n• What Are the Alternatives to Wearing Black Onyx?\n• How Does Black Onyx React With Other Stones?\n• Summary\n• Frequently Asked Questions\n• Who can not wear black onyx?\n• Which zodiac should wear black onyx?\n• Can Black Onyx cause skin irritation?\n• Should people with mental health issues wear Black Onyx?\n• Is Black Onyx suitable for pregnant women?\n\n## Can Anyone Wear Black Onyx?\n\nBlack onyx gemstone\n\nBlack Onyx is a versatile gemstone, revered for its grounding and protective qualities. Its metaphysical properties black onyx make it a favorite among those seeking stability and strength in their lives. The black onyx gemstone is a powerful energy source, so understanding who can wear Black Onyx without experiencing adverse effects is crucial.\n\nIndividuals with sensitive skin may experience irritation or allergic reactions from wearing Black Onyx due to its hardness and density. Similarly, those with high blood pressure should consult their doctor before wearing Black Onyx, as its potential to lower blood pressure levels could pose a risk. Mental health considerations are also crucial; people suffering from conditions like depression or bipolar disorder are advised against wearing Black Onyx, as it might exacerbate their symptoms.\n\nPregnancy and childhood are also periods when wearing Black Onyx might not be recommended. Pregnant women should avoid wearing black onyx due to the increased risk of complications such as miscarriage and premature birth. Likewise, children, with their delicate skin, might find the hardness and density of the stone uncomfortable, leading to potential skin reactions.\n\n## Who Should Not Wear Black Onyx?\n\nNegative energy and black onyx\n\nAlthough Black Onyx provides numerous benefits, it’s not suitable for all. Individuals with sensitive skin might experience irritation or allergic reactions due to the stone’s physical properties. Skin rashes may result from the hardness and density of Black Onyx, causing discomfort for those prone to skin issues.\n\nPeople with high blood pressure need to exercise caution, as Black Onyx can potentially lower blood pressure levels significantly. This property, while beneficial for some, can be dangerous for those already managing blood pressure conditions. Before incorporating such a potent gemstone into your lifestyle, you should always consult a healthcare professional.\n\nMental health is another critical area where Black Onyx’s powerful energy can have adverse effects. Individuals with depression, bipolar disorder, or schizophrenia are advised against wearing the stone, as it can amplify their symptoms and trigger episodes of sadness, paranoia, and anxiety. Pregnant women should also steer clear of Black Onyx due to beliefs that it may increase the risk of miscarriage and premature birth. Additionally, children should not wear Black Onyx jewelry, as it may cause discomfort and skin irritation due to the gemstone’s physical properties.\n\n## Black Onyx and Zodiac Signs\n\nA person holding a black onyx stone\n\nBlack Onyx’s compatibility with different zodiac signs varies, with some signs benefiting more from its energy than others. The bold energy of Black Onyx can foster inner strength and self-confidence, but it may not be favorable for everyone. Depending on individual psychological makeup, Black Onyx can either be overwhelming and intense or provide emotional balance.\n\nWe’ll explore the interaction of Black Onyx with each zodiac sign by examining its effects on:\n\n• Aries\n\n• Taurus\n\n• Gemini\n\n• Cancer\n\n• Leo\n\n• Virgo\n\n• Libra\n\n• Scorpio\n\n• Sagittarius\n\n• Capricorn\n\n• Aquarius\n\n• Pisces\n\nThis exploration will help determine which signs can harness its power effectively and which should approach it with caution.\n\n## Can Aries Wear Black Onyx?\n\nAries, known for their leadership qualities and dynamic energy, can find Black Onyx particularly beneficial. The stone provides protective and calming energy, helping to reduce stress and anxiety.\n\nBlack Onyx is associated with Aries, offering a grounding effect that can enhance their natural traits and provide the stability needed to navigate their ambitious pursuits. In various black onyx forms, this gemstone can be utilized to maximize its benefits.\n\n## Can Taurus Wear Black Onyx?\n\nTaurus, being an earth sign, resonates well with the stabilizing energy of Black Onyx. This gemstone can shield Taurus individuals from negative energy and motivate them towards their goals and dreams. The compatibility between Taurus and Black Onyx is further strengthened by their shared association with the earth element, making it a natural fit for those born under this sign.\n\nBefore committing to Black Onyx, Taurus individuals are advised to assess its effects with a three-day trial period. This approach ensures that the stone’s energy is harmonious with their personal vibrations and provides the desired benefits.\n\n## Can Gemini Wear Black Onyx?\n\nGemini individuals are typically advised to avoid Black Onyx. The stone is believed to bring conflict and bad luck to those born under this zodiac sign. Wearing Black Onyx may attract fear and heighten discontent, disrupting the natural balance that Geminis seek.\n\nHowever, Onyx’s ability to balance feminine and masculine energies may help Geminis, who are often dealing with dual aspects of their personality, feel more grounded and emotionally stable. Despite this potential benefit, the overall consensus is that Black Onyx might be too intense for Geminis, amplifying both positive and negative qualities.\n\n## Can Cancer Wear Black Onyx?\n\nThe onyx stone can be a beneficial choice for those born under the Cancer zodiac sign, offering protection and enhancing willpower and self-discovery. The stone’s grounding qualities can help Cancer individuals feel more secure and emotionally balanced, providing a sense of stability in their lives.\n\nEven though Black Onyx has numerous benefits, Cancer individuals should consider a three-day trial period to confirm compatibility. This trial allows them to experience the stone’s effects firsthand and decide if it aligns with their personal energy.\n\n## Can Leo Wear Black Onyx?\n\nLeos can benefit greatly from Black Onyx, as it aligns well with their personality traits and helps balance out their uncertainties. The stone enhances their confidence, strength, and charisma, making it a valuable ally for those born under this sign.\n\n## Can Virgo Wear Black Onyx?\n\nVirgo, known for their practical nature and goal-oriented mindset, can find Black Onyx helpful for grounding and support. The stone’s stabilizing energy aligns well with Virgo’s analytical and meticulous approach to life, providing a steady foundation to achieve their objectives.\n\n## Can Libra Wear Black Onyx?\n\nLibra individuals can consider wearing Black Onyx, although the stone has a lesser affinity with this zodiac sign compared to others. Libra individuals are encouraged to undergo a three-day trial period to evaluate the initial effects of Black Onyx before deciding to wear it regularly.\n\n## Can Scorpio Wear Black Onyx?\n\nBlack Onyx is suitable for Scorpio as it aligns with their astrological qualities of:\n\n• strength\n\n• resilience\n\n• steadiness\n\n• grounding\n\n• stamina\n\n• self-discipline\n\nThe stone’s layered structure resonates with Scorpio’s characteristic intensity, helping them address their intense emotions and self-repressive tendencies.\n\nFor Scorpios, Black Onyx symbolizes dealing with life’s challenges one step at a time, aiding in emotional grounding and providing the strength needed to navigate their passionate nature.\n\n## Can Sagittarius Wear Black Onyx?\n\nBlack Onyx can be a supportive stone for Sagittarius, offering a grounding influence that enhances their strength to transform and grow. The stone provides Sagittarians with clarity and inner strength, aiding them in understanding their dreams and visions.\n\n## Can Capricorn Wear Black Onyx?\n\nCapricorns can benefit from wearing Black Onyx as it:\n\n• Bolsters self-confidence\n\n• Helps in setting and achieving goals\n\n• Offers protection and grounding\n\n• Absorbs negative energy, preventing it from affecting the Capricorn’s body and soul\n\n• Aids in grounding Capricorns, keeping them rooted in reality during disputes.\n\nFurthermore, the stone enhances mental clarity for Capricorns, allowing them to concentrate better on their objectives. It is recognized for bringing happiness and good fortune into the life of a Capricorn.\n\n## Can Aquarius Wear Black Onyx?\n\nBlack Onyx is beneficial for those born under the Aquarius zodiac sign as it complements their innovative and forward-thinking nature. For Aquarians, Black Onyx acts as a grounding stone, helping to filter out unwanted energies and maintain mental clarity. The stone offers protection by absorbing and dispelling negative energy.\n\n## Can Pisces Wear Black Onyx?\n\nBlack Onyx is suitable for Pisces, offering grounding and protective energy, which provides stability and security for their sensitive and emotionally receptive nature. The stone’s calming influence can be particularly beneficial for Pisces who may experience anxiety or stress, helping them maintain emotional balance.\n\nAdditionally, Black Onyx can enhance the following for Pisces:\n\n• Intuition and creativity, assisting in tapping into their inner wisdom and guidance\n\n• Communication skills, facilitating better self-expression and connection with others\n\n• Trust, comfort, and a sense of belonging, as a root chakra stone.\n\n## Can Black Onyx Influence Your Emotional Well-Being?\n\nA person meditating with black onyx gemstone\n\nBlack Onyx isn’t just a beautiful stone to wear; it also has significant metaphysical properties that can influence your emotional well-being. Known for its grounding properties, spiritual energy, and the ability to enhance stability and security through its connection with the root chakra, the metaphysical properties black onyx can be a powerful tool for emotional balance.\n\nWearing Black Onyx may improve emotional strength, balance feminine and masculine energies, and promote mental focus, concentration, and clarity. This makes it an excellent stone for anyone seeking to improve their emotional well-being and mental clarity.\n\nHowever, it’s also essential to note that individuals with mental health conditions, specifically those with depression, bipolar disorder, or schizophrenia, may experience worsened symptoms and increased negativity when wearing Black Onyx. This is why it’s crucial to consider your personal circumstances and consult with a health professional if you have any concerns.\n\n## Is There Anyone Who Shouldn’t Wear Black Onyx Jewelry for Health Reasons?\n\nWhile black onyx has many potential benefits, it’s also important to acknowledge that it may not be suitable for everyone. For individuals with hypersensitive skin or allergies, wearing Black Onyx can be a cause for concern. The stone’s hardness and density might cause irritation or allergic reactions.\n\nThose with high blood pressure should also be cautious. Black Onyx has calming properties that could potentially lower blood pressure too much. If you have high blood pressure, it’s advisable to seek medical advice before wearing Black Onyx.\n\nPregnant women are often advised to avoid Black Onyx due to beliefs that it may increase risks such as miscarriage or premature birth. Similarly, black onyx jewelry is not recommended for young children because their delicate skin may react poorly to the stone’s hardness.\n\n## Could Wearing Black Onyx Affect Your Energy Levels?\n\nIllustration of negative energy being absorbed by black onyx\n\nOne of the many intriguing aspects of black onyx is its potential impact on energy levels. Known for its grounding and stabilizing properties, black onyx can:\n\n• Absorb negativity\n\n• Promote emotional balance\n\n• Support self-mastery\n\n• Build inner strength\n\n• Enhance intuitive abilities\n\n• Shield the wearer from negative energies\n\nThis can lead to continuous personal growth and a positive influence on your energy levels.\n\nHowever, individuals with high blood pressure should be cautious about wearing black onyx jewelry. Given its calming properties, black onyx has the potential to lower blood pressure levels, which could negatively affect energy levels.\n\n## Are There Specific Times When You Shouldn’t Wear Black Onyx?\n\nWhile the mystical allure of black onyx might make it tempting to wear all the time, there are certain circumstances where caution is advised. Pregnant women, for instance, are often advised to avoid wearing black onyx due to concerns about potential risks such as miscarriage and premature birth.\n\nBeing cognizant of these risks, and exercising caution with black onyx during pregnancy is recommended. It’s always best to listen to your body and intuition, and when in doubt, consult with a health professional for guidance.\n\n## How Can You Tell If Black Onyx Isn’t Right for You?\n\nThe world of gemstones is highly personal, and what works for one person may not work for another. If you experience any negative side effects after wearing black onyx, it’s crucial to reassess whether the crystal is compatible with your energy.\n\nAlways remember, the right versatile gemstone for you should bring comfort, balance, and positivity.\n\n## Who Should Wear Black Onyx?\n\nBenefits of wearing black onyx\n\nIndividuals seeking a potent protective stone that offers emotional strength and stability during challenging situations will find Black Onyx ideal. This versatile gemstone is perfect for those wanting to:\n\n• Shield themselves from negative energy\n\n• Enhance their resilience\n\n• Ground themselves\n\n• Focus in their lives\n\nPersonal preferences and compatibility play a significant role in wearing Black Onyx. While the stone can be immensely beneficial for some, it’s vital to make sure its energy aligns with yours. Testing Black Onyx with a trial period can help determine if it is the right fit for you.\n\n## Benefits of Wearing Black Onyx\n\nWearing Black Onyx offers numerous benefits that extend across emotional, physical, and spiritual dimensions. Emotionally, the black onyx stone promotes emotional balance by helping to alleviate stress and anxiety. The stone’s grounding qualities absorb negative energy, promoting a sense of calmness and stability. It also helps individuals move on from past grievances, enhancing self-confidence and decision-making abilities.\n\nPhysically, Black Onyx is known to support health by:\n\n• Improving stamina\n\n• Enhancing the function of kidneys and liver\n\n• Aiding in relieving physical pains such as headaches and menstrual cramps\n\n• Contributing to overall well-being through its association with physical endurance and blood circulation.\n\nSpiritually, Black Onyx is heralded for its role in spiritual growth. It offers the following benefits:\n\n• Protection during meditation\n\n• Enhancement of intuition\n\n• Support for a deep connection with the Earth and one’s inner self\n\n• Balancing energy flow\n\n• Promoting emotional healing\n\nThis powerful grounding stone, with its healing properties, is a valuable tool in spiritual practices.\n\n## How to Wear Black Onyx?\n\nFor effective use of Black Onyx, it is suggested to integrate it into your everyday life, either through jewelry or by carrying the stone in a pocket or purse. Wearing Black Onyx jewelry, such as rings, bracelets, or necklaces, allows the stone to remain in close contact with your energy field, providing continuous protection and grounding. To maintain its effectiveness, it’s important to cleanse Black Onyx regularly.\n\nFor those seeking protection from negative energy, wearing Black Onyx on the right hand is believed to act as a shield by absorbing and dispelling harmful vibrations. Ensuring compatibility with your personal energy and zodiac sign can enhance the stone’s effectiveness, making it a powerful ally in your journey towards emotional balance and stability.\n\n## How to Safely Experiment With Black Onyx?\n\nIf you’re interested in exploring the world of black onyx, there are safe ways to experiment. Wearing black onyx is advised for individuals who are interested in experiencing improved sleep quality and warding off nightmares.\n\nThanks to its resilience, black onyx can be worn every day, allowing for prolonged experimentation without the risk of damage. However, as with any gemstone, it’s important to be mindful of any changes or discomfort and adjust as necessary.\n\n## What Are the Alternatives to Wearing Black Onyx?\n\nIllustration of alternative black gemstones\n\nIf you find that black onyx is not quite right for you, don’t worry – there are numerous alternatives. Black Agate, for instance, is a perfect substitute for black onyx, suitable for broad use by various individuals.\n\nAnother popular alternative is Black Cubic Zirconia. Known for its sleek appearance and its ability to promote analytical thinking and focus, Black Cubic Zirconia can be a great choice for those seeking an alternative to black onyx.\n\nBlack Garnet, hailed for its universal healing properties that can influence mood positively, is another wonderful alternative to consider.\n\n## How Does Black Onyx React With Other Stones?\n\nIllustration of black onyx with other gemstones\n\nPairing gemstones can be a wonderful way to enhance their unique properties, and the black onyx gemstone is no exception. This versatile stone can be synergistically paired with other gemstones to enhance its protective properties and other characteristics.\n\nAs a shield, the black onyx stone can help guard against negative energies and psychic attacks when worn with other stones. However, when pairing Black Onyx with other gemstones, it is generally recommended to cleanse black onyx and avoid those with bright or vibrant colors, as certain black onyx forms may not complement them well.\n\nIt’s also crucial to consider the energies involved in pairing stones. Opposite energies can cancel out, or have less desirable outcomes, and intentions must be clear to prevent the stones from working at cross-purpo\n\n## Summary\n\nBlack Onyx, with its bold and grounding energy, is a versatile gemstone that offers numerous benefits. However, its powerful properties mean that it is not suitable for everyone. Individuals with sensitive skin, high blood pressure, mental health issues, pregnant women, and children should exercise caution or avoid wearing Black Onyx altogether.\n\nThe stone’s compatibility with zodiac signs varies, making it essential to test its effects through a trial period. For those who find harmony with Black Onyx, it can provide emotional strength, protection, and spiritual growth. By understanding who should and shouldn’t wear Black Onyx, you can harness its full potential and integrate its energy into your life effectively.\n\n## Frequently Asked Questions\n\n## Who can not wear black onyx?\n\nAccording to astrology, Geminis should avoid wearing black onyx due to its negative effects on them. Individuals with mental health issues such as depression, bipolar disorder, or schizophrenia should also avoid wearing black onyx.\n\n## Which zodiac should wear black onyx?\n\nIf you are a Leo or Capricorn, wearing black onyx can help you master your destiny, provide confidence, center energy in times of stress, and enable wise decision-making.\n\n## Can Black Onyx cause skin irritation?\n\nYes, Black Onyx can cause skin irritation, particularly in individuals with sensitive skin. Be cautious if you have sensitive skin.\n\n## Should people with mental health issues wear Black Onyx?\n\nIt’s best for people with mental health issues like depression, bipolar disorder, or schizophrenia to avoid wearing Black Onyx as it may worsen symptoms.\n\n## Is Black Onyx suitable for pregnant women?\n\nIt is not recommended for pregnant women to wear Black Onyx due to potential risks like miscarriage and premature birth."
  gem.meaning_content = "Black Onyx stone is a beautiful and powerful crystal in the gemstones world. Anyone who has ever thought of bringing a healing crystal home must have come across the Black Onyx crystal. It is a mysterious stone filled with all the benefits of a black gemstone. The physical appearance of the stone is unique and has very distinct energy which can be harnessed for good.\n\nBlack Onyx meaning is derived from its ability to function as a powerhouse of protective and purifying energy. It is one of the important stones in the world of healing, meditation, and spirituality. The energies of this stone can be very helpful in times of grief, sorrow, and depression. It can also be used to cleanse and purify the mind, body, and soul.\n\nHere is a complete guide about Black Onyx meaning, Black Onyx healing properties, spiritual meaning, benefits, side effects and who should wear black onyx and much more. Continue reading to learn more!\n\nTable of Contents\n\nToggle\n\n• Black Onyx meaning\n• What is Black Onyx?\n• Black Onyx properties\n• Black Onyx healing properties\n• Emotional and Mental healing properties of Black Onyx\n• Spiritual healing properties of Black Onyx\n• Physical healing properties of Black Onyx\n• Metaphysical healing properties of Black Onyx\n\n• Black Onyx meaning and Chakra connection\n• Black Onyx side effects and who should not wear Black Onyx\n• Who should wear Black Onyx?\n• How to use Black Onyx?\n• How to cleanse and recharge Black Onyx?\n• How to tell if Black Onyx is real?\n\n## Black Onyx meaning\n\nBlack Onyx meaning is derived from its ability to protect against negative energy. Black onyx is a powerful stone that can help to guard against negative vibes and to cleanse and purify the mind, body, and soul. \n\nThe vibrations of this crystal can also help to connect you with your higher self and to achieve a state of inner peace. It motivates and gives a push to move forward in life by handling the hindrances and problems with ease.\n\n1. Helps to protect against negative energy\n\n2. Cleanses and purifies the mind, body, and soul\n\n3. Connects you with your higher self\n\n4. Achieves a state of inner peace\n\n5. Motivates and gives a push to move forward in life\n\n## What is Black Onyx?\n\nBlack Onyx is part of the Quartz family and is found in Brazil, India, and Uruguay. The name “Onyx” comes from the Greek word “onyx” which means “claw” or “fingernail”. \n\nThis semi-precious stone has been used in jewellery and other decorative objects for centuries. It is a popular material for cameos. Black Onyx is said to have many metaphysical properties. It is believed to help with decision-making, relieve fears, and promote happiness.\n\nBlack Onyx is made up of relatively parallel bands of colours. Black is the most common colour, but it can also be white, yellow, or brown. The bands are arranged in such a way that they resemble layers of a cake.\n\n## Black Onyx properties\n\nHere is a quick glance of the Black Onyx stone properties\n\n• Black Onyx is a 7 on the Mohs scale of hardness.\n\n• The stone has a vitreous lustre.\n\n• It is non-transparent.\n\n• The hardness on Mohs hardness scale is 7.\n\n• It has a specific gravity of 2.66.\n\n• It has a refractive index of 1.54-1.55.\n\n• It is double refractive.\n\n• It is found in Brazil, India, and Uruguay.\n\n• The name “Onyx” comes from the Greek word “onyx” which means “claw” or “fingernail”.\n\n## Black Onyx healing properties\n\nBlack Onyx is known for its protective nature against negative energy. This stone has strong healing benefits and given its colour, it absorbs all the negative vibrations around you to cleanse and purify your mind, body, and soul. \n\nBlack Onyx crystal has a mix of emotional, physical, and spiritual benefits which makes it one of the most powerful stones for overall healing. Its connection to the chakra system and the element of Earth make it a very grounding stone.\n\n## Emotional and Mental healing properties of Black Onyx\n\n1. Improves self-control\n\n2. Provides grounding effect\n\n3. Acts as a protection stone\n\n4. Helps with grief, sorrow, and depression\n\n5. Enhances courage and strength\n\n6. Banishes bad habits\n\nBlack Onyx is a strong stone that can help you deal with grief, sorrow, and depression. It can help you let go of the past and move on with your life. It can also provide you with the strength and courage you need to face your fears. Black Onyx is a stone of protection and can help you guard against negative energy. Black Onyx stone is known for its grounding effect and can help you stay calm and focused in times of stress.\n\nIt enhances self-control and banishes bad habits. It is a stone that can help you get in touch with your inner strength and power.\n\n## Spiritual healing properties of Black Onyx\n\n1. Connects with the higher self\n\n2. Helps achieve a state of inner peace\n\n3. Absorbs and transforms negative energy\n\n4. Helps you let go of the past\n\n5. Aids in achieving your highest potential\n\nBlack Onyx is a stone that can be used for protection against negative energy. It can help you connect with your higher self and achieve a state of inner peace. Black Onyx is known for its ability to absorb and transform negative energy. It can also help you let go of the past and move on with your life. Black Onyx is a powerful stone that can help you achieve your highest potential. \n\nBlack Onyx spiritual meaning is ‘the protector’. It protects you from the negative vibrations and clears the aura to help you achieve your highest potential.\n\n## Physical healing properties of Black Onyx\n\n1. Helps with physical stress and anxiety\n\n2. Improves stamina and endurance\n\n3. Relieves pain\n\n4. Helps with nerve health\n\n5. Keeps the nervous system healthy\n\nBlack Onyx has strong grounding and stabilising energies that can help you deal with physical stress and anxiety. It is believed that the Black Onyx stone helps one recover from physical trauma and injuries. Black Onyx can help improve your stamina and endurance and has the ability to relieve pain. It is excellent for nerve health and keeps the entire nervous system healthy\n\n## Metaphysical healing properties of Black Onyx\n\n1. Protects against negative energy\n\n2. Connects with the higher self\n\n3. Achieves calmness and a state of inner peace\n\n4. Grounds and stabilises the chakra system\n\nBlack onyx is a powerful stone that has a wide range of metaphysical healing benefits. It can be used to protect against negative energy, to connect with the higher self, to achieve a state of inner peace, and to absorb and transform negative energy. Black onyx is also known for its ability to ground and stabilise the chakra system.\n\n## Black Onyx meaning and Chakra connection\n\nBlack Onyx is connected to the Root Chakra. The Root Chakra is the first chakra and is located at the base of the spine. It is associated with the element of Earth and is responsible for our connection to the physical world. The Root Chakra is responsible for our sense of safety and security. It is a very grounding and stabilising chakra.\n\nWhen the Root Chakra is in balance, we feel safe, secure, and grounded. We are able to deal with stress and anxiety. We feel confident and have a sense of belonging. When it goes out of balance, we may feel anxious, fearful, and stressed. We may also feel disconnected from the physical world.\n\nBlack Onyx can help to balance the Root Chakra and restore a sense of security. It can also help to ground and stabilise the chakra.\n\n1. Helps to balance the Root Chakra\n\n2. Restores a sense of security\n\n3. Grounds and stabilises the chakra\n\n4. Helps with stress and anxiety\n\n5. Helps with a sense of belonging\n\n## Black Onyx side effects and who should not wear Black Onyx\n\nBlack Onyx is a very powerful stone and has many benefits. However, there are a few side effects that you should be aware of:\n\n• Black Onyx can be overwhelming for some people. If you are sensitive to energy, then it is best to use Black Onyx in small doses.\n\n• Black Onyx can also be too grounding for some people. For someone who is constantly on the go, Black Onyx may not be the best stone for them.\n\n• Black Onyx can also absorb negative energy. If you are around people who are negative or if you are in a negative environment, then Black Onyx will absorb that energy. It is best to cleanse the stone regularly if you are exposed to negative energy.\n\n• Black Onyx is also not recommended for pregnant women as it is a very powerful stone.\n\n## Who should wear Black Onyx?\n\nBlack Onyx is a stone that can be worn by anyone. However, there are some people who will benefit more from wearing Black Onyx:\n\n• Those who are stressed: Black Onyx is a very grounding and stabilising stone. If you are someone who is constantly on the go or if you are feeling stressed, then Black Onyx can help you to relax and feel more grounded.\n\n• Those who are grieving: Black Onyx is a stone of protection and can help to guard against negative energy. If you are grieving the loss of a loved one, then Black Onyx is the stone for you to help you to deal with the grief and move on with your life.\n\n• Those who want to get in touch with their inner strength: Black Onyx is a stone that can help you to get in touch with your inner strength and power. If you are looking to connect with your higher self, then Black Onyx can help you to achieve that.\n\n## How to use Black Onyx?\n\nThere are many ways to use Black Onyx and there is no right or wrong method. Black Onyx meaning stands for protection against negative vibes and keeping the stone as close as possible will only keep you more protected. \n\nHere are some well known ways to use Black Onyx:\n\n• Wearing Black Onyx: Black Onyx can be worn as a piece of jewelry or as a stone in a necklace or bracelet. This way the crystal stays closer to the body and is around you most of the time.\n\n• Carrying Black Onyx: Another way to keep the crystal close to you is by carrying it in your pocket or in a small pouch.\n\n• Placing Black Onyx in the home: Black Onyx can also be placed in the home in areas where you feel you need protection from negative energy.\n\n• Meditation with Black Onyx: Black Onyx can also be used in meditation. You can hold the crystal in your hand or place it on your body.\n\n• Black Onyx elixir: Black Onyx can also be made into an elixir. This can be done by placing the crystal in a bowl of water overnight. The elixir can then be used to drink or to wash the body.\n\n## How to cleanse and recharge Black Onyx?\n\nBlack Onyx does not need to be cleansed very often as it is a very powerful stone. However, it is always good to cleanse and recharge your crystals regularly. There are many ways to cleanse and recharge Black Onyx.\n\n• Sunlight: You can cleanse Black Onyx by placing it in sunlight for a few hours. This is one of the most effective and common ways. The energy from the sun will cleanse and recharge the crystal.\n\n• Moonlight: You can also cleanse Black Onyx by placing it in moonlight overnight. Moonlight is very gentle and has feminine energy which cleanses the stone softly. It is best to cleanse your stone on the full moon as the moonlight cleansing is the most effective on those days.\n\n• Running water: Another way to cleanse Black Onyx is by running it under cold water. Take the crystal in your hands and run it under cold water for a few minutes. You can also place the crystal in a bowl of cold water for a few hours.\n\n• Smudging: Smudging is a method of cleansing that is used to cleanse and purify the energy of a space. It is done by burning sage or Palo Santo and wafting the smoke over the crystal. This will cleanse the crystal of any negative energy.\n\n• Cleansing with other crystals: You can also cleanse Black Onyx with other crystals. Place the crystal you want to cleanse on top of a bed of sea salt or on a cluster of quartz crystals. Leave it there for a few hours or overnight. The energy of the other crystals will cleanse and recharge the Black Onyx.\n\n## How to tell if Black Onyx is real?\n\nThere are many fake crystals available in the market and it can be difficult to tell if a crystal is real or not. Here are some ways to tell if Black Onyx is real:\n\n• Look at the color: Black Onyx is a black stone with white bands running through it. If the stone is not black or if the bands are not white, there are chances it is not Black Onyx.\n\n• Look at the clarity: Black Onyx is a non-transparent stone. Notice the transparency of the stone. If the stone is transparent, then it is not Black Onyx.\n\n• Look at the Mohs hardness: Black Onyx has a Mohs hardness of 7. The stone has to be pretty hard. If the stone is not hard enough, then it is not Black Onyx. If you have doubts you may want to get it checked by a gemstonist.\n\n• Look at the refractive index: Black Onyx has a refractive index of 1.54-1.55. If the refractive index does not match it could be a fake Black Onyx.\n\n• Look at the double refraction: Black Onyx is double refractive. It reflects light from all sides. If the stone is not double refractive and does not throw light, do more checks to verify its authenticity. \n\n• Look for a certificate of authenticity: If you are buying Black Onyx from a store, then make sure that the store provides you with a certificate of authenticity. This will guarantee that the stone is real.\n\nInterested in learning about other crystals similar to Black Onyx crystal healing benefits? You may want to read about Red Agate stone."
