  gem.water_safety_content = "Yes, Black Tourmaline can go in water, but only for brief rinsing and not for prolonged periods.\n\nBlack Tourmaline, a powerful and versatile crystal, is renowned for its grounding and protective qualities. But when it comes to cleansing this crystal, many questions arise about the proper methods to maintain its energy and appearance. One common question is, can black tourmaline go in water? In this blog post, we’ll delve into the safety of using water with Black Tourmaline and discuss various cleansing practices to ensure its longevity and effectiveness in your energy work.\n\nTable of Contents\n\nToggle\n\n• Key Takeaways\n• Is Black Tourmaline Water Safe?\n• Can Black Tourmaline Go In Salt Water?\n• Can Black Tourmaline Go In Tap Water?\n• Can Black Tourmaline Go In the Sun?\n• Can Black Tourmaline Go In Salt?\n\n• The Compatibility of Black Tourmaline with Water\n• Understanding the Mohs Hardness Scale\n• Chemical Composition and Water Interaction\n• Water Exposure: A Risk Assessment\n\n• The Impact of Salt Water on Black Tourmaline\n• The Perils of Salt and Mineral Buildup\n• Avoiding Salt Water for Energetic Integrity\n\n• How to Cleanse Black Tourmaline Without Water?\n• Smudging with Sacred Smoke\n• The Power of Sunlight and Moonlight\n• Brown Rice for Absorbing Negativity\n\n• Ensuring the Longevity of Your Black Tourmaline\n• Gentle Handling and Soft Cloth Cleaning\n• Proper Storage Away from Other Minerals\n\n• Incorporating Black Tourmaline into Energy Work\n• Jewelry as a Protective Amulet\n• Meditation and Spiritual Awareness\n\n• Summary\n• Frequently Asked Questions\n• Can black tourmaline be washed in water?\n• What happens to tourmaline in water?\n• Can you put tourmaline in drinking water?\n• How do you activate black tourmaline stone?\n• Is it safe to expose Black Tourmaline to sunlight?\n\n## Key Takeaways\n\n• Black Tourmaline is safe to briefly rinse in water for cleansing, but prolonged exposure should be avoided.\n\n• Saltwater and salt solutions can damage the structure of Black Tourmaline, so they should not be used.\n\n• Alternatives such as smudging with sacred smoke or using sunlight/moonlight are effective methods for cleansing without water.\n\n## Is Black Tourmaline Water Safe?\n\nYes, Black Tourmaline is safe to be briefly rinsed in water, but prolonged exposure should be avoided.\n\nBlack Tourmaline has gained popularity in the world of crystal healing, known to block negative energy and cleanse the surrounding environment. While water cleansing is suitable for many crystals, including Black Tourmaline, understanding the stone’s interaction with water is key to prevent damage. In general, it is safe to briefly rinse Black Tourmaline in water for cleansing purposes, but prolonged exposure should be avoided.\n\nUnderstanding the Mohs Hardness Scale rating of Black Tourmaline, which ranges between 7 and 7.5, shows that this hard stone is less likely to crack when compared to softer stones like Rose Quartz. However, its chemical composition, which includes silica, boron, iron, and other mineral inclusions, makes it susceptible to damage if exposed to water for extended periods. Thus, care must be taken when using water to clean your Black Tourmaline stone.\n\n## Can Black Tourmaline Go In Salt Water?\n\nNo, Black Tourmaline should not be placed in salt water as it can damage the crystal’s structure and appearance.\n\nWhile Black Tourmaline can be safely rinsed with fresh water, it is not recommended to let your tourmaline go in water, especially saltwater, for cleansing purposes. Saltwater can cause damage to the crystal’s structure and appearance, making it brittle and prone to breaking. The abrasive nature of salt can also react with the stone’s components, particularly iron, leading to further damage.\n\nFor preserving the structure and energy of your Black Tourmaline, avoiding saltwater and choosing safer cleaning options is recommended.\n\n## Can Black Tourmaline Go In Tap Water?\n\nYes, using tap water for a very quick rinse is acceptable for cleansing Black Tourmaline; however, it is advised to avoid soaking the crystal for extended periods. The minerals present in tap water do not have a significant detrimental effect on Black Tourmaline, but prolonged exposure to water may pose a concern.\n\nHence, a quick rinse with tap water is perfectly acceptable; just ensure you’re gentle and limit the water contact.\n\n## Can Black Tourmaline Go In the Sun?\n\nYes, it is safe to expose Black Tourmaline to sunlight, but only for one to two hours to prevent color fading.\n\nSunlight can be used to cleanse and charge Black Tourmaline, but it is essential to avoid prolonged exposure to prevent color fading. Direct sunlight can cause the crystal’s color to fade over time, and it may also lead to structural damage.\n\nTo safely use sunlight for cleansing, limit your Black Tourmaline’s exposure to one or two hours and then place it in a secure, shaded spot.\n\n## Can Black Tourmaline Go In Salt?\n\nNo, direct contact with salt is not recommended for Black Tourmaline, as it can cause damage to the crystal’s structure. Salt can widen the cracks in the stone, leading to chipping, cracking, and even dissolution.\n\nTo prevent any potential damage, it is advisable to avoid exposing your Black Tourmaline to salt or salt solutions and opt for safer cleansing methods instead.\n\n## The Compatibility of Black Tourmaline with Water\n\nBlack tourmaline crystal with water droplets\n\nHaving considered the safety of water cleansing, it’s key to comprehend the factors affecting Black Tourmaline’s interaction with water. These factors include the crystal’s hardness and chemical composition, which can influence how it reacts when exposed to water.\n\nThe following sections will provide further insights into these aspects, aiding your decisions about cleansing your Black Tourmaline.\n\n## Understanding the Mohs Hardness Scale\n\nThe Mohs Hardness Scale is a measure of a mineral’s hardness, ranging from 1 (the softest mineral, talc) to 10 (the hardest, diamond). The scale is based on the ability of one mineral to scratch another. Black Tourmaline has a Mohs Hardness rating of 7 to 7.5, making it a relatively hard stone that is less likely to crack when submerged in water.\n\nHowever, keep in mind that despite its high hardness score, the stone can still break if submerged in water for too long, just like the human body can be affected by prolonged exposure to water.\n\n## Chemical Composition and Water Interaction\n\nBlack Tourmaline is composed of silica, boron, iron, and other mineral inclusions, which contribute to its unique properties and appearance. While there is no specific data available regarding the direct effect of its chemical composition on its interaction with water, it is generally safe to briefly rinse the crystal in water due to its high hardness value and ability to absorb negative energy. However, prolonged water contact should be avoided to prevent possible harm.\n\n## Water Exposure: A Risk Assessment\n\nWhile it is safe to use water for a quick rinse of Black Tourmaline, soaking it for extended periods may cause damage. Prolonged water exposure can lead to structural damage and discoloration, as well as negatively impact the stone’s energetic properties.\n\nFor the longevity and effectiveness of your Black Tourmaline, care should be taken when using water for cleaning and consider other methods if needed.\n\n## The Impact of Salt Water on Black Tourmaline\n\nAs mentioned earlier, salt water can have detrimental effects on Black Tourmaline, causing damage to the crystal’s structure and appearance.\n\nThe following sections will examine the risks of salt and mineral buildup on Black Tourmaline and highlight why saltwater should be avoided to maintain the crystal’s energy.\n\n## The Perils of Salt and Mineral Buildup\n\nSalt can be particularly harmful to Black Tourmaline, as it can widen the cracks in the stone, hastening the rusting process and causing damage. Additionally, salt can react adversely with the elements of the stone, especially those containing iron, leading to further deterioration.\n\nTo limit potential harm, prolonged exposure of Black Tourmaline to saltwater or salt solutions should be avoided.\n\n## Avoiding Salt Water for Energetic Integrity\n\nTo maintain the energetic integrity and appearance of your Black Tourmaline, it is important to avoid using saltwater for cleansing. The detrimental effects of saltwater on the stone’s structure can also negatively impact its energetic properties, rendering it less effective for its intended purpose.\n\nChoosing safer cleaning methods like a quick freshwater rinse, can help maintain your Black Tourmaline’s effectiveness in blocking negative energies and providing protection.\n\n## How to Cleanse Black Tourmaline Without Water?\n\nSmudging with sacred smoke for cleansing\n\nAs we’ve established, using water for cleansing Black Tourmaline should be done with caution. However, there are alternative methods for cleansing this powerful crystal that do not involve water.\n\nThe following sections will cover these alternative methods to combat energy vampires, such as smudging with sacred smoke, using sunlight and moonlight, and utilizing brown rice to absorb negativity.\n\n## Smudging with Sacred Smoke\n\nOne effective method for cleansing Black Tourmaline without water is smudging, which involves using sacred smoke from herbs such as sage, palo santo, or incense to remove negative energy. This ancient practice has been used by various cultures for centuries to purify spaces and objects, making it a suitable alternative for cleansing your Black Tourmaline crystal.\n\nFor smudging, just ignite your chosen herb or incense and let the smoke envelop the widely used crystal to clear unwanted energies, effectively cleansing crystals.\n\n## The Power of Sunlight and Moonlight\n\nAnother method is to place Black Tourmaline in direct sunlight or moonlight for a short duration, letting the natural light clean and recharge its energy. As mentioned earlier, it is important to avoid prolonged exposure to sunlight to prevent color fading and potential damage. However, moonlight has no adverse effects on Black Tourmaline and can be used for cleansing purposes without any concerns.\n\n## Brown Rice for Absorbing Negativity\n\nFinally, brown rice can be used to clean Black Tourmaline by drawing out negativity and detoxifying the crystal. To do this, simply bury the stone in a bed of dry brown rice for a period of 24 hours.\n\nThis method is gentle and effective, allowing your Black Tourmaline to release any negative energy it has absorbed and restore its protective qualities.\n\n## Ensuring the Longevity of Your Black Tourmaline\n\nGentle handling and cleaning with soft cloth\n\nProper handling, cleaning, and storage of your Black Tourmaline are essential in maintaining the crystal’s energy and appearance. The following sections will cover best practices for careful handling, soft cloth cleaning, and appropriate storage away from other minerals to prolong the life of your Black Tourmaline.\n\n## Gentle Handling and Soft Cloth Cleaning\n\nTo avoid damaging your Black Tourmaline, follow these steps to clean it:\n\n• Handle it with care.\n\n• Use a soft cloth to wipe the stone in circular motions.\n\n• Remove any grime or fingerprints.\n\n• Be cautious not to use any abrasive materials or chemicals that could harm the crystal.\n\nRegular cleaning of your Black Tourmaline helps to preserve its protective qualities, keeping it a potent instrument in your energy practice. A cleanse tourmaline routine ensures its effectiveness in maintaining a balanced and positive environment.\n\n## Proper Storage Away from Other Minerals\n\nStoring your Black Tourmaline separately from other minerals is important to avoid scratches and damage. To protect the crystal, store it in a fabric pouch, or wrap it in a natural fabric such as silk or suede to preserve its energy.\n\nWith these precautions, your Black Tourmaline can continue to serve as a potent and effective instrument for repelling negative energies and enhancing protection.\n\n## Incorporating Black Tourmaline into Energy Work\n\nBlack Tourmaline can be incorporated into various energy work practices, such as wearing it as jewelry for protection or using it in meditation for spiritual awareness. The subsequent sections will examine the benefits of utilizing Black Tourmaline in these manners, along with some guidance on integrating this versatile crystal into your energy work routine.\n\n## Jewelry as a Protective Amulet\n\nWearing Black Tourmaline as jewelry offers several benefits, such as shielding against negative energy, reducing stress and anxiety, and promoting feelings of safety and stability. Incorporating it into your daily routine by putting black tourmaline on allows you to utilize its protective qualities and maintain an energy balance.\n\nWhether worn as a bracelet, necklace, or ring, Black Tourmaline jewelry, featuring tourmaline stones, can serve as a powerful protective stone amulet for protection and emotional well-being.\n\n## Meditation and Spiritual Awareness\n\nIncorporating Black Tourmaline into your meditation practices can enhance your spiritual awareness and promote mental clarity. The crystal’s ability to repel negative energies and create a protective shield allows you to maintain a smoother and more balanced energy flow during meditation.\n\nHolding Black Tourmaline during meditation can assist in dispersing unwanted energies, including dark energy, and purifying your energy field, fostering a sense of well-being and spiritual development.\n\n## Summary\n\nIn conclusion, Black Tourmaline is a powerful crystal with numerous applications in energy work and protection. Understanding its compatibility with water and alternative cleansing methods is crucial to maintaining its effectiveness and preserving its appearance. By following proper handling, cleaning, and storage practices, you can ensure the longevity of your Black Tourmaline and continue to benefit from its protective and grounding properties.\n\n## Frequently Asked Questions\n\n## Can black tourmaline be washed in water?\n\nYes, black tourmaline can be washed in water. Warm, soapy water is the best method for cleaning it; ultrasonic and steam cleaners should not be used.\n\n## What happens to tourmaline in water?\n\nPink tourmaline features several microscopic cracks and fissures, which can cause it to break when submerged in water over time as water molecules enter the cracks.\n\n## Can you put tourmaline in drinking water?\n\nYes, tourmaline can be put in water, however there is no scientific evidence suggesting any benefits from doing so. It may add a mild taste to the water due to the metal ions it contains, but its effects are not scientifically proven.\n\n## How do you activate black tourmaline stone?\n\nActivating black tourmaline can be done by placing it on a selenite charging plate, leaving it out in the moonlight for several hours or burying it for 24 hours. Alternatively, soaking it in water can also be beneficial.\n\n## Is it safe to expose Black Tourmaline to sunlight?\n\nIt is safe to expose Black Tourmaline to sunlight in moderation, but limit exposure to one or two hours to prevent color fading."
  gem.sleeping_with_content = "Sleeping with Black Tourmaline under pillow promotes restful sleep, enhances dream recall and protects against negative energies when placed in the bedroom or worn as jewelry. Combining Black Tourmaline with other crystals such as Amethyst, Lepidolite and Rose Quartz may improve sleep quality. Placing Black Tourmaline under pillow should be done cautiously due to potential side effects including discomfort, disrupted sleep and feeling drained or sleepy.\n\nAre you struggling with restless nights and searching for a natural solution to improve your sleep quality? Look no further! Discover the powerful benefits of sleeping with “black tourmaline under pillow”. This protective stone is known to repel negative energies, promoting restful sleep and enhancing dream recall. Let’s embark on this journey to better sleep and learn how to effectively use black tourmaline in your bedroom.\n\nTable of Contents\n\nToggle\n\n• Can You Sleep With Black Tourmaline Under Pillow?\n• Where to Put Black Tourmaline in Bedroom?\n\n• Black Tourmaline Under Your Pillow: How It Works\n• Protection from Negative Energy\n• Promoting Restful Sleep\n• Enhancing Dream Recall\n\n• Choosing the Right Black Tourmaline Stone\n• Crystal Combinations for Better Sleep\n• Amethyst\n• Lepidolite\n• Rose Quartz\n\n• Setting Up a Crystal Grid for Sleep\n• Caring for Your Black Tourmaline Stone\n• How to Cleanse Black Tourmaline?\n• How to Charge Black Tourmaline?\n• How to Properly Store Black Tourmaline?\n\n• Potential Side Effects of Black Tourmaline Under Pillow\n• Alternatives to Placing Black Tourmaline Under Your Pillow\n• Summary\n• Frequently Asked Questions About Black Tourmaline Under Pillow\n• Where should I place my black tourmaline?\n• What is a good crystal to put under your pillow?\n• When should I wear black tourmaline?\n• Can you wear tourmaline all the time?\n• What does black tourmaline do when you wear it?\n\n## Can You Sleep With Black Tourmaline Under Pillow?\n\nYes, you can sleep with Black Tourmaline under pillow. Placing black tourmaline directly under your pillow is discouraged due to its sharp and delicate nature but locating an appropriate place for it in your bedroom allows you to enjoy its compelling benefits. Black tourmaline promotes a restful sleep, enhances dream recall, and shields against negative energies.\n\nTo wear black tourmaline as a pendant or bracelet can also help achieve these benefits.\n\n## Where to Put Black Tourmaline in Bedroom?\n\nPut Black Tourmaline on your bedside table, near the door or window in your bedroom for maximized protective and sleep-enhancing benefits. This allows the stone to work its magic while you sleep, warding off negative energies and promoting a peaceful slumber.\n\nAnother alternative is to combine black tourmaline with other sleep-promoting crystals, such as amethyst, lepidolite, and rose quartz, to create a crystal grid for sleep. Experiment with different placements and combinations to find the perfect setup for your unique needs and preferences.\n\n## Black Tourmaline Under Your Pillow: How It Works\n\nBlack tourmaline, a crystalline boron silicate mineral, consists of iron-based minerals like ferroan dravite and uvite. This potent stone is reputed to have the following benefits:\n\n• Counteract fear\n\n• Lessen stress and anxiety\n\n• Protect against electromagnetic radiation\n\n• Boost concentration\n\nWhen used correctly, black tourmaline can help improve sleep quality by cleansing negative energy and promoting relaxation.\n\n## Protection from Negative Energy\n\nReputed to repel negative energies and offer protection from misfortune, black tourmaline serves to obstruct toxic energy and rid you of any negative residue from the day.\n\nFurthermore, to activate black tourmaline, simply have a black tourmaline crystal in your environment, as it is a potent protection stone that guards against electromagnetic radiation from power lines and electronic devices due to its high concentration of iron.\n\n## Promoting Restful Sleep\n\nBlack tourmaline is suggested to be beneficial for sleep quality by:\n\n• Facilitating relaxation\n\n• Diminishing stress\n\n• Providing a grounding and protective energy\n\n• Reducing electromagnetic stress\n\n• Creating an atmosphere of tranquility and contentment.\n\nFurthermore, it is believed to absorb negative energy and transform it into positive energy, purifying the energy body and thus facilitating a more restful sleep.\n\n## Enhancing Dream Recall\n\nIt is plausible that black tourmaline can assist in improving dream recall and stimulating lucid dreaming. To enhance dream recall, place black tourmaline under your pillow while sleeping and combine it with other crystals, such as satin spar and selenite, for added benefits.\n\n## Choosing the Right Black Tourmaline Stone\n\nChoosing an appropriate black tourmaline stone is key to fully enjoy its benefits. A high-quality black tourmaline stone is renowned for its protective qualities, its ability to ground energy, its potential to increase motivation, and its capability to dispel negative energy. To verify the authenticity of your black tourmaline stone, observe its color and shape, assess the quality of the cut, and examine its clarity.\n\nThe recommended size of black tourmaline for sleeping purposes is between three and five centimeters long and one to three centimeters wide. When selecting a black tourmaline stone, be mindful of the following:\n\n• Any visible flaws or cracks\n\n• Ensure it is smooth to the touch\n\n• Deep black color\n\n• Free of any artificial treatments or enhancements.\n\n## Crystal Combinations for Better Sleep\n\nBeyond black tourmaline, other crystals can be integrated to enhance sleep quality. Popular stones for sleep and relaxation encompass amethyst, selenite, moonstone, and rose quartz.\n\nExperiment with different crystal combinations to find the perfect synergy for your needs, and experience the unique properties of liquid light.\n\n## Amethyst\n\nAmethyst is widely recognized as “the all-purpose stone” and is a protective stone that aids in alleviating stress and anxiety in one’s life. Placing amethyst under one’s pillow may be beneficial in addressing a variety of sleep issues while purifying and clearing the mind of any negative thoughts.\n\nIts connection to the third eye and crown chakra is particularly noted, and it has been utilized to aid in the healing of emotional wounds, encourage inner peace, and harness its healing properties.\n\n## Lepidolite\n\nLepidolite is a soothing crystal that is known for its calming properties and ability to mitigate stress and anxiety. Its gentle energy helps to reduce anxiety and foster a sense of peace and serenity.\n\nLepidolite can be used in combination with other crystals such as:\n\n• Rose quartz\n\n• Lithium quartz\n\n• Selenite\n\n• Celestite\n\n• Pink quartz\n\n• Citrine\n\n• Lapis lazuli\n\n• Clear quartz\n\n• Amethyst\n\n• Moldavite\n\n• Iolite\n\nFor enhanced sleep benefits and mental clarity, a good night’s sleep is essential.\n\n## Rose Quartz\n\nRose quartz is a gentle and joyful crystal that exudes warmth and emanates unconditional love. Placing rose quartz beneath one’s pillow or retaining it as an amulet on the bedside table can help ensure that no adverse vibes enter the bed. Its calming and soothing energy is often referred to as the “love stone” and is associated with feelings of love, compassion, and understanding.\n\nKeeping rose quartz close while sleeping can help create a peaceful and protective energy.\n\n## Setting Up a Crystal Grid for Sleep\n\nA crystal grid is a method of allowing crystal energy to be present in your environment, thereby preventing any negative energies from entering. To construct a crystal grid for sleep, you can follow these steps:\n\n• Begin by selecting a focal stone in the center.\n\n• Progress outward with additional crystals in your preferred layout.\n\n• You may also incorporate elements such as flowers, pods, or seashells to enhance the grid’s energy.\n\nExperiment with different crystal combinations and grid layouts to find the most suitable configuration for your unique needs. Commonly used crystals for sleep and relaxation include:\n\n• Amethyst\n\n• Selenite\n\n• Moonstone\n\n• Rose quartz\n\n## Caring for Your Black Tourmaline Stone\n\nMaintaining your black tourmaline stone properly is key to preserving its effectiveness. This includes cleansing, charging, and storing the stone.\n\nBy taking care of your black tourmaline, you can ensure it continues to provide protection and promote restful sleep.\n\n## How to Cleanse Black Tourmaline?\n\nTo cleanse black tourmaline stone, use methods like the use of water, sea salt, or moonlight. To cleanse black tourmaline with water, hold it under running water for a few minutes, visualizing negative energy being washed away. Alternatively, you can soak it in a bowl of clean water for a couple of hours.\n\nAnother method is to cleanse the stone under moonlight, providing a gentle and natural way to eliminate negative energy and purify the crystal through crystal healing.\n\n## How to Charge Black Tourmaline?\n\nTo charge black tourmaline, you can use both sunlight and moonlight. It’s necessary to recharge your black tourmaline stone to preserve its energy and effectiveness.\n\nTo charge black tourmaline stone under moonlight, place it outside or near an open window where it will be exposed to the light of the full moon. Another method for charging black tourmaline is to place it next to a clear quartz crystal, which can enhance its energy.\n\n## How to Properly Store Black Tourmaline?\n\nProper storage of your black tourmaline stone is key to safeguarding its energy and preserving its effectiveness. Keep the stone in a safe and secure place, such as a cloth box or a covered area, to prevent damage. It is important to cleanse your black tourmaline stone regularly to remove any negative energies it may have absorbed.\n\nAvoid storing black tourmaline with other gemstones to prevent cross-contamination of energies, and do not expose it to harsh chemicals or extreme temperatures.\n\n## Potential Side Effects of Black Tourmaline Under Pillow\n\nAlthough black tourmaline is broadly deemed safe and advantageous, potential side effects should be taken into account when positioning it under your pillow. Sleeping with black tourmaline under your pillow, especially in large amounts, may result in discomfort or disrupted sleep. Some individuals have reported experiencing headaches, nausea, and feeling drained or sleepy after sleeping with black tourmaline placed beneath their pillow.\n\nIt is important to remember that everyone’s experience with black tourmaline will be different, and what works well for one person may not be suitable for another. If you notice any negative effects, consider trying alternative placements or using other crystals to improve your sleep quality.\n\n## Alternatives to Placing Black Tourmaline Under Your Pillow\n\nIf positioning black tourmaline under your pillow doesn’t suit you, alternative methods exist for utilizing black tourmaline in your bedroom. You can:\n\n• Hang black tourmaline in your bedroom\n\n• Place it on your nightstand\n\n• Place it beneath your bed\n\n• Place it near your door\n\nExperiment with different placements to find what works best for you.\n\nAnother option is to use different crystals in place of black tourmaline for improved sleep quality. Some alternative stones include:\n\n• Amethyst\n\n• Fluorite\n\n• Green calcite\n\n• Moonstone\n\n• Selenite\n\n• Rose quartz\n\n• Citrine\n\n• Shungite\n\n• Red jasper\n\n• Orange calcite\n\n• Aragonite\n\n• Aventurine\n\n• Celestite\n\n• Agate\n\n• Smoky quartz\n\n• Bloodstone\n\n• Howlite\n\n• Labradorite\n\nExplore various combinations and placements to create the perfect sleep-enhancing environment for your needs.\n\n## Summary\n\nIn conclusion, black tourmaline is a powerful and protective stone that can help improve sleep quality, ward off negative energies, and enhance dream recall. While placing it directly under your pillow may not be the best option for everyone, there are alternative ways to use black tourmaline in your bedroom, as well as other crystals that can be combined for better sleep. By properly caring for your black tourmaline stone and experimenting with different placements and combinations, you can create a peaceful and restorative sleep environment tailored to your needs.\n\n## Frequently Asked Questions About Black Tourmaline Under Pillow\n\n## Where should I place my black tourmaline?\n\nFor optimal protection, place a black tourmaline under your mattress or on your nightstand while you sleep, and also conceal a brick-sized raw tourmaline at your home’s entrance to shield it from negative energy.\n\n## What is a good crystal to put under your pillow?\n\nAmethyst is a great crystal to place under your pillow as it purifies the mind and aids in sleep issues such as insomnia and nightmares.\n\n## When should I wear black tourmaline?\n\nWear black tourmaline when going to parties, bars, and large group gatherings, or during meditation and while using a pendulum for protection against negative energy.\n\n## Can you wear tourmaline all the time?\n\nAlthough you should avoid wearing tourmaline rings if you do work with your hands, wearing tourmaline earrings and pendants every day is safe.\n\n## What does black tourmaline do when you wear it?\n\nBlack Tourmaline is a protective stone that is believed to create a barrier of energy around the wearer, shielding them from negative influences such as electromagnetic radiation from electronic devices and negative energies from people or environments. It also helps release stress and tension while providing spiritual protection and promoting feelings of peace and calm."
  gem.meaning_content = "Black crystals are rare and have a unique mesmerizing black lustre. They are also known to have very high energy which can be used for protection, healing, and grounding oneself.\n\nBlack tourmaline is one of the most popular black crystals. It is a powerful stone that can be used to protect against negative energies and promote healing and grounding.\n\nHere is a complete guide to black tourmaline, including its meaning, history, benefits and how to use it.\n\nTable of Contents\n\nToggle\n\n• What is black tourmaline?\n• Black Tourmaline Meaning\n• History of Black Tourmaline\n• Black Tourmaline Physical Properties\n• Black Tourmaline Benefits\n• Black Tourmaline Healing Properties\n• Emotional healing properties\n• Physical Healing Properties\n• Metaphysical Healing Properties\n\n• Black Tourmaline and Chakra connection\n• How to Use Black Tourmaline?\n• Grounding Bath\n\n• Black Tourmaline Crystal Combination\n• Ways To Cleanse Black Tourmaline?\n• Black Tourmaline as a Zodiac Birthstone\n• Other FAQs on Black tourmaline\n• What is the meaning of the Black tourmaline Necklace?\n• What is the meaning of the Black tourmaline Bracelet?\n• What is Black Tourmaline used for?\n• How to tell if Black Tourmaline is real?\n• Can Black Tourmaline go in the sun?\n• What does a Black Tourmaline look like?\n• Black Tourmaline vs Black obsidian\n• Spiritual Meaning of Black Tourmaline\n• Can Black Tourmaline go in the water?\n• What is the difference between Black Tourmaline and Schorl Tourmaline?\n• Who should not use Black Tourmaline?\n• How much does Black Tourmaline cost?\n• What is Green Tourmaline?\n• What is Watermelon Tourmaline?\n• Is Black Tourmaline toxic?\n\n## What is black tourmaline?\n\nBlack tourmaline belongs to the tourmaline family and is black in color. It is also known as schorl tourmaline. Its composition is complex and includes iron, magnesium, sodium, lithium, and aluminium. It is found in igneous and metamorphic rocks.\n\nThis crystal is formed when hot magma or lava comes into contact with rocks that contain tourmaline. The tourmaline in the rocks is then heated and changed into black tourmaline.\n\nThe name “tourmaline” comes from the Sinhalese word “turamali”, which means “stone with mixed colors”.\n\n## Black Tourmaline Meaning\n\nBlack tourmaline Meaning stands for protection, grounding and cleansing. It is known as a powerful stone that can help to protect you from negative energy, psychic attack and EMF radiation.\n\nBlack tourmaline is also known for its ability to cleanse and purify your energy field and help ground you to the Earth. It purifies the emotional body and is excellent for releasing anger, resentment and fear. It is also a helpful stone for those who are highly sensitive or who tend to pick up on the negative energy of others.\n\nBlack Tourmaline meaning is defined by its ability to act as a protective shield and get rid of the negative thoughts and harmful energy in one’s body.\n\n## History of Black Tourmaline\n\nIn ancient times, black tourmaline was used to protect against evil spirits and negative energy. It was also said to have the power to ward off the evil eye.\n\nBlack tourmaline is a semi-precious stone that has been used for centuries for its unique properties. It is said to have first been used by the ancient Egyptians for its ability to protect against negative energy. It was also used by the ancient Greeks and Romans for its purported healing properties.\n\n## Black Tourmaline Physical Properties\n\nBlack Tourmaline is a type of tourmaline that is black in color. It is one of the most popular tourmalines and is used in a variety of jewelry and lapidary applications.\n\nIt is a hard stone with a range of 7 to 7.5 on Mohs hardness scale. It has a trigonal crystal system and a vitreous to dull luster.\n\nBlack Tourmaline is made up of divalent cations, such as magnesium, iron, and manganese. The cations are surrounded by an anion lattice of boron and oxygen.\n\n## Black Tourmaline Benefits\n\n-Black Tourmaline is a powerful stone that can protect you from negative energy of all kinds, including emotional stress, environmental pollution, and negative energies from other people.\n\n-Black Tourmaline can also help to boost your mood, increase motivation, and give you a more positive outlook on life.\n\n-It is also said to be helpful in overcoming addiction and can be used to purify and cleanse the auric field.\n\n– This crystal acts as a psychic shield, deflecting and transmuting negative energies, entities, or destructive forces.\n\n-Black Tourmaline is also said to be helpful in reducing stress, tension, and anxiety.\n\n-It can also be used to ground and protect you during meditation and spiritual work.\n\n## Black Tourmaline Healing Properties\n\nBlack Tourmaline is an excellent crystal that has emotional, physical health, and spiritual healing properties. It has many healing powers that make it a popular stone among healers. It’s a stone that can be used for protection from negative energy, as it helps to cleanse and purify the aura. It’s also helpful in grounding and centering the wearer.\n\n## Emotional healing properties\n\n– Promotes emotional stability\n\n– Cleanses and purifies the aura\n\n– Helps to ground and center the wearer\n\n– Boosts self-esteem and self-love\n\n– Provides clarity and direction\n\n– Gets rid of unwanted energies\n\n– Greater self-confidence\n\nThis stone acts as a purifier of emotions, ensuring that all negative energies and emotions are cleansed and released. It’s a stone that can help to provide emotional stability and equilibrium. During turbulent times, it can be a great stone to have as it can help to ground and center the wearer.\n\nIt is also a crystal of self-confidence and can help to boost self-esteem and your own energy. If you’re feeling lost or confused, Black Tourmaline can help to provide clarity and direction. Its protective energy promotes self-love and boosts positive self-image.\n\n## Physical Healing Properties\n\n– Helps in detoxifying the body\n\n– Boosts the immune system\n\n– Reduces pain\n\n– Promotes tissue regeneration\n\n– Relieves tension headaches and migraines\n\n– Draws out toxins and impurities\n\nBlack Tourmaline stones are great for the physical body. They have many physical benefits and are great for physical health. It is a magical crystal for detoxification as it helps to remove toxins from the body. It’s also said to boost the immune system and promote healing in the body.\n\nThis stone can be used to relieve pain, as it has analgesic properties. It helps in reducing muscle aches and boosting overall physical vitality.\n\nThose suffering from strained or torn muscles can also benefit from black tourmaline’s ability to promote tissue regeneration.\n\nBlack Tourmaline when heated and applied to the skin is said to draw out toxins and impurities. It can also be used to relieve tension headaches and migraines.\n\nIt produces negative ions when heated which helps to neutralize electromagnetic radiation from electronic devices.\n\nBlack Tourmaline is amazing for a good night’s sleep. These healing crystals act as a constant cloak that makes you feel connected to yourself and provides you with peace of mind. This feeling helps in getting a peaceful sleep.\n\n## Metaphysical Healing Properties\n\n– Shields from bad energy\n\n– Helps to ground and center\n\n– Can increase vitality, stamina, and energy levels\n\n– Great for those who feel scattered or ungrounded\n\n– Helps to promote self-confidence and reduce fear\n\n– Cleanses and purifies the chakras\n\n– Helps bring you back into balance\n\n– Can help to cleanse and protect your aura\n\n– Generates Positive vibrations\n\nBlack tourmaline is a powerful stone that can protect you from bad energy of all kinds, including psychic attacks, negative thoughts and emotions, and even electromagnetic fields. It helps to ground and centre and can also increase your vitality, stamina, and energy levels.\n\nIt’s a great stone for anyone who feels scattered or ungrounded and insecure, as it will help you to feel more centred and confident. Black tourmaline helps in connecting with the spiritual world.\n\nIts association with the root chakra makes it a great stone for grounding and security. It can also be used to cleanse and purify the chakras. Root chakra imbalances can manifest as feeling ungrounded, anxious, or scattered.\n\nIf you’re feeling any of these things, black tourmaline can help to bring you back into balance.\n\nBlack tourmaline is a powerful stone for protection from negative forces of all kinds. It can help to cleanse and purify your aura, and it can also be used to protect your space from harmful energy.\n\nIt’s especially helpful in clearing away negative thoughts and harmful energies. If you’re feeling drained or overwhelmed by negative energy, black tourmaline can help to cleanse and protect you.\n\nThese Black crystals are helpful for those who are sensitive to EMF (electromagnetic fields). It can help to protect you from the negative effects of EMF, and it can also help to reduce stress and anxiety. If you’re feeling overwhelmed by EMF, black tourmaline can help to create a protective barrier around you.\n\n## Black Tourmaline and Chakra connection\n\nBlack Tourmaline is most commonly associated with the Root Chakra, which is located at the base of the spine. The Root Chakra is responsible for our feeling of safety and security and is associated with the element of earth.\n\nIt is the base of our chakra system and is the foundation for all the other chakras. Keeping it balanced ensures that we feel grounded, stable and secure in our lives.\n\nBlack Tourmaline is also associated with the Third Eye Chakra, which is located between the eyebrows. The Third Eye Chakra is responsible for our intuition and our ability to see the bigger picture.\n\nIt is associated with the element of fire. Keeping it balanced helps us to trust our intuition, make clear decisions and see the world with clarity.\n\nBlack Tourmaline crystal also connects with the earth star chakra which helps the wearer connect with the energy of the earth. It aids in building a bond between the human being and mother earth.\n\n## How to Use Black Tourmaline?\n\nWhen using a Black Tourmaline, it is imperative to build a bond with the stone first. This can be done by holding the stone in your cupped hands and meditating with it. You can also lay down and hold the stone against your solar plexus chakra or your heart chakra.\n\nIf you are looking to use the stone for protection, you can carry it with you in your pocket or wear it as a piece of jewelry. You can also place it in your environment, such as in your car or at your desk at work.\n\nHere are some of the best ways to use Black Tourmaline for maximum impact:\n\nWearing Black Tourmaline As a Jewellery\n\nBlack Tourmaline can be made into beautiful jewellery pieces such as bracelets, necklaces and rings. The Black shiny surface of the stone makes it a perfect candidate for jewellery making.\n\nNot only does it look great, but it also has the properties to protect you from negative energies. Keeping the stone close to your body for long periods of time is a great way to receive its benefits. Wear black tourmaline stones to make the most of its protective nature.\n\nFor Protection\n\nBlack Tourmaline is one of the best stones that you can use for protection. It can absorb negative energies and deflect them back to their source. It is also a great stone to use if you are feeling anxious or stressed.\n\nPlacing a piece of Black Tourmaline in your environment will help to create a protective bubble around you.\n\nFor Healing\n\nBlack Tourmaline is a powerful healing stone. It can be used to cleanse and purify the body, mind and spirit. It can also be used to release negative emotions and traumas.\n\nIf you are feeling low or disconnected, holding a piece of Black Tourmaline can help you to feel more grounded and connected.\n\nFor Meditation\n\nBlack Tourmaline crystals are a great stone to use for meditation. It can help to still the mind and provide clarity. It is also a powerful stone for protection during meditation.\n\nIf you are new to meditation, holding a piece of Black Tourmaline in your hand can help you to feel more grounded and connected.\n\nWhile meditating, try to bring the focus to the crystal and feel the energy emanating from it.\n\n5. At home and Office\n\nBlack Tourmaline is a great stone to keep in your home or office. It can help to deflect negative energies and create a protective bubble around your space.\n\nPlace a piece of Black Tourmaline near the entrance of your home or office to create a protective barrier. You can also place it in your car to help deflect negative energy while you are driving.\n\n## Grounding Bath\n\nIt is recommended that you use Black Tourmaline in a bathtub full of warm water. This helps to cleanse your aura and ground your energy.\n\n1. Add 4-5 drops of black tourmaline oil to your bathtub.\n\n2. Fill the tub with warm water and relax for 20-30 minutes.\n\n3. Focus on your breath and let your mind clear.\n\n4. When you’re finished, drain the tub and ground yourself by walking barefoot on the earth for a few minutes.\n\n## Black Tourmaline Crystal Combination\n\nBlack tourmaline crystals are often used in combination with other stones, which helps amplify its effects. Many crystals combine well with this Black stone. Some popular combinations include:\n\nBlack tourmaline with Amethyst\n\nThis combo is great for protection against negative energy and psychic attack, as well as for purification and spiritual growth. Amethyst is a stone of peace and tranquillity which when combined with black tourmaline can create a powerful shield of protection.\n\nThis is for people who tend to attract drama or who are highly sensitive and need extra support.\n\nBlack tourmaline with Citrine\n\nThis is a great combination for manifestation, as citrine is a stone of abundance and prosperity. Citrine is also known for its Solar Plexus Chakra clearing properties, which when combined with black tourmaline can help to clear away any blockages that are preventing you from achieving your goals.\n\nBlack tourmaline with Jet\n\nThis is a potent combination of protection and psychic defense, as jet is a very grounding stone. Jet can also help to absorb negative energy, which when combined with black tourmaline can create a powerful shield against negativity.\n\n## Ways To Cleanse Black Tourmaline?\n\nThere are many ways that you can cleanse your Black Tourmaline. Here are some of the most popular ways:\n\nRunning Water\n\nThe simplest way to cleanse your Black Tourmaline is to run it under cool, running water for a few minutes. You can do this in your sink or in a natural body of water such as a river, stream, or lake.\n\nSalt Water\n\nAnother way to cleanse your Black Tourmaline is to soak it in salt water overnight. To do this, simply add a few tablespoons of salt to a bowl of water and stir until the salt is dissolved. Then place your Black Tourmaline in the water and let it soak overnight.\n\nNext morning, rinse your Black Tourmaline under running water and allow it to air dry.\n\nSmudging\n\nSmudging is a popular method of cleansing crystals and gemstones. To smudge your Black Tourmaline, simply hold it in your hand and pass it through the smoke of a smudge stick or incense. The smoke is known for its ability to cleanse and purify. It is important to note that some people are sensitive to smoke, so if you are one of those people, smudging may not be the best option for you.\n\nReiki\n\nReiki is a form of energy healing that can be used to cleanse and purify crystals and gemstones. To cleanse your Black Tourmaline with Reiki, simply hold it in your hand and allow the Reiki energy to flow through you and into the crystal.\n\nMoonlight\n\nAnother popular way to cleanse your Black Tourmaline is to leave it out in the moonlight overnight. The moon is known for its ability to cleanse and purify. Simply place your Black Tourmaline on a windowsill or outside on a clear night and allow it to soak up the moonlight.\n\nOnce you have cleansed your Black Tourmaline, it is important to recharge it. This can be done by placing it in direct sunlight for a few hours or by leaving it out in the moonlight overnight.\n\nYou may also want to use affirmations to recharge your crystal. Some of the most popular affirmations for Black Tourmaline are:\n\n• I am surrounded by love and light.\n\n• I am safe and protected.\n\n• I am connected to the Earth and all of her wisdom.\n\n• I am grounded and centered.\n\n• I am open to receiving all the good that the Universe has to offer.\n\n## Black Tourmaline as a Zodiac Birthstone\n\nBlack Tourmaline is the zodiac birthstone for the sign of Capricorn.\n\nCapricorn is the tenth astrological sign in the zodiac, originating from the constellation of Capricornus. It spans the 270–300th degree of the zodiac, corresponding to celestial longitude. Under the tropical zodiac, the sun transits this area on average between December 21 and January 20, and under the sidereal zodiac, the sun transits this area between approximately January 16 and February 15.\n\nCapricorn is considered an earth sign and is one of four cardinal signs. Capricorn is also considered a feminine sign.\n\nBlack Tourmaline is considered a lucky charm for those born under the sign of Capricorn.\n\nCapricorns are known for their hard work, ambition, and determination. They are also known for their practicality and level-headedness. Black Tourmaline is best for Capricorns who want to stay grounded and focused on their goals.\n\nBlack Tourmaline is also the zodiac birthstone for the sign of Aquarius.\n\nAquarius is the eleventh astrological sign in the zodiac and is associated with the constellation of Aquarius. It spans the 300–330th degree of the zodiac, corresponding to celestial longitude. Under the tropical zodiac, the sun transits this area on average between January 21 and February 20, and under the sidereal zodiac, the sun transits this area between approximately February 15 and March 14.\n\nAquarius is considered an air sign and is one of four fixed signs. Aquarius is considered a masculine sign.\n\nAquarians are independent and have a humanitarian spirit. They are known for their eccentricity and intelligence. Black Tourmaline is best for Aquarians who want to stay connected to their community and make a difference in the world.\n\n## Other FAQs on Black tourmaline\n\n## What is the meaning of the Black tourmaline Necklace?\n\nThe meaning of the Black tourmaline necklace is that it provides protection against negative energy. It is also said to promote grounding, balance, and positive thinking. This necklace is meant to stay close to the body, so it can do its job properly. Being closer to your body all the time makes it more effective and powerful.\n\n## What is the meaning of the Black tourmaline Bracelet?\n\nThe black tourmaline bracelet is a type of jewelry that is said to have protective and healing properties. It is said to be helpful in deflecting negative energy and protecting the wearer from harmful influences. Wearing Black Tourmaline bracelet is also said to promote a sense of well-being and balance. It is a beautiful piece of jewelry that can be worn by both men and women.\n\nWear a Black Tourmaline bracelet if you are seeking:\n\n– Protection from negative energy\n\n– A sense of well-being\n\n– Balance and harmony\n\n## What is Black Tourmaline used for?\n\nBlack Tourmaline is a very popular crystal that is used for a variety of purposes. It is said to be a powerful protective stone that can shield you from negative energy of all kinds, including psychic attacks, EMF radiation, and negative environmental energies.\n\nBlack Tourmaline is also helpful in grounding and centering yourself, as well as promoting positive attitudes and a sense of empowerment.\n\n## How to tell if Black Tourmaline is real?\n\nThere are a few ways to tell if Black Tourmaline is real. One way is to look for a label or stamp on the stone. If the stone is stamped with “Black Tourmaline” or “BT”, then it is most likely real. Another way to tell if the stone is real is to look for signs of wear. It is likely fake if the stone is polished or has a shiny surface. Real Black Tourmaline will have a dull or matte finish.\n\nYou may also want to do a knife test. Take a sharp knife and try to scratch the surface of the stone. The stone is most likely fake if the knife leaves a scratch. Real Black Tourmaline is very hard and will not be scratched by a knife.\n\n## Can Black Tourmaline go in the sun?\n\nThe hardness of Black Tourmaline is 7-7.5 on the Mohs Scale of Hardness, making it a relatively hard stone. This means that it can be used in a variety of jewelry applications, including rings and bracelets.\n\nHowever, Black Tourmaline is a semi-precious stone, so it should be stored away from other jewelry to avoid scratching. Black Tourmaline is a dark stone, so it should not be left in direct sunlight for extended periods, as this can cause the stone to fade.\n\n## What does a Black Tourmaline look like?\n\nA Black Tourmaline typically appears as a black, translucent crystal. It can also be found in a variety of other colors, including brown, green, yellow, and pink. It has vertical striations running along its length and a vitreous luster. The surface is often rough, but can also be smooth.\n\n## Black Tourmaline vs Black obsidian\n\nBlack tourmaline is a type of tourmaline, which is a semi-precious stone. It is known for its black color and is used in a variety of jewelry and other decorative items. Black obsidian, on the other hand, is a type of volcanic glass. It is also black in color and is used in a variety of applications, including jewelry and sculptures.\n\n## Spiritual Meaning of Black Tourmaline\n\nBlack Tourmaline is a powerful stone that helps to protect against negative energy of all kinds, including electromagnetic fields, psychic attacks, and negative thoughts. It is also said to be helpful in restoring balance and harmony.\n\nIt is a crystal that connects one to their higher self and is also said to be helpful in communicating with the spirit world. Reaching out to the spiritual realm can help to bring in higher guidance and understanding.\n\n## Can Black Tourmaline go in the water?\n\nThe hardness of Black Tourmaline stone is 7-7.5 which makes it durable enough to withstand water. However, it is best to avoid getting it wet as it can absorb water and become brittle.\n\n## What is the difference between Black Tourmaline and Schorl Tourmaline?\n\nThe main difference between Black Tourmaline and Schorl Tourmaline is their color. Black Tourmaline is black or dark-colored, while Schorl Tourmaline is blue-black.\n\n## Who should not use Black Tourmaline?\n\nBlack Tourmaline is a stone of protection and grounding. Those who are seeking a stone of protection may want to consider using Black Tourmaline. However, Black Tourmaline is not a stone that should be used by everyone. Those who are sensitive to the energies of stones should not use Black Tourmaline. Those who are pregnant or nursing should not use Black Tourmaline.\n\n## How much does Black Tourmaline cost?\n\nBlack Tourmaline stone typically costs between $5 and $10 per carat. It is considered to be a relatively affordable gemstone. The price will also depend on the quality and size of the stone.\n\n## What is Green Tourmaline?\n\nGreen tourmaline is a type of tourmaline that is green in color. It is considered to be a semi-precious stone and is used in a variety of jewelry pieces. Green tourmaline is also believed to have a number of metaphysical properties, such as promoting healing, abundance, and prosperity.\n\n## What is Watermelon Tourmaline?\n\nWatermelon Tourmaline is part of Tourmaline family that is characterized by its green rind and pink center. The name is derived from its resemblance to a watermelon. This crystal is found in many different localities around the world, including Brazil, Afghanistan, and Madagascar.\n\n## Is Black Tourmaline toxic?\n\nNo, black tourmaline is not toxic. This is a non-toxic, non-hazardous stone and is safe to use in all settings.\n\nRead about other healing gemstones that have similar properties: \n\nBlack Obsidian\n\nHematite Quartz"
