  gem.meaning_content = "Blue Onyx is a powerful protection stone that has been used for centuries. It is said to absorb and transform negative energy, and to help alleviate fears and worries. Blue Onyx promotes strength and self-discipline and boosts confidence and decision-making ability. \n\nBlue Onyx meaning is derived from its deep blue color, which is associated with the Throat Chakra. \n\nThis guide will teach you all about the Blue Onyx meaning, uses and its benefits. Read on to learn everything you need to know about this beautiful stone!\n\nTable of Contents\n\nToggle\n\n• What is Blue Onyx?\n• Blue Onyx meaning\n• Benefits of Blue Onyx \n• Blue Onyx meaning and Chakra connection\n• Blue Onyx healing properties\n• Blue Onyx emotional healing properties\n• Blue Onyx physical healing properties\n• Blue Onyx metaphysical healing properties\n• How to best use Blue Onyx benefit \n• During meditation\n• For concentration and focus\n• For decision-making\n• As jewellery\n\n• Best stone combinations with Blue Onyx\n• Best ways to cleanse Blue Onyx\n• Ways to recharge Blue Onyx\n• What is the Blue onyx zodiac?\n\n## What is Blue Onyx?\n\nBlue Onyx is a type of onyx that has a blue color. It can either be banded or unbanded. The properties of blue onyx depend on its type. There are two main types of blue onyx: natural and enhanced. Natural blue onyx is a semi-precious stone that is found in nature. \n\nEnhanced blue onyx is created when natural onyx is enhanced with dyes or other treatments. While both types of blue onyx have similar physical properties, enhanced blue onyx may have different metaphysical properties.\n\nBlue Onyx is a member of the chalcedony family. It is found in many different locations around the world including Brazil, Uruguay, and the United States. The name “onyx” comes from the Greek word for “fingernail” because it was once used to make nail files.\n\nBlue onyx has a waxy luster and a Moh’s hardness of 7. It has a trigonal crystal system and a vitreous to a pearly lustrous finish. Its color can range from light blue to dark blue, and it is often banded with white or grey stripes.\n\nBlue onyx is believed to have calming and soothing properties. It is thought to help with decision-making, promote inner strength, and provide support during times of stress.\n\n## Blue Onyx meaning\n\nBlue Onyx meaning is defined as the power of protection. It is known to provide physical and emotional strength in times of need. It is the stone that promotes willpower, perseverance and self-discipline.\n\nBlue Onyx also has a nickname, the Warrior Stone. This is because it gives people the strength they need to overcome any obstacle. \n\nThe meaning of this stone also includes its ability to help one stay the course, even when things are tough. It will give you the courage you need to face your fears and overcome them. \n\n## Benefits of Blue Onyx \n\nBlue onyx is said to offer a number of benefits, both physical and metaphysical. Some of the most commonly cited benefits include:\n\n– Helps to balance the chakras\n\n– Promotes positive energy\n\n– Can help to relieve stress and anxiety\n\n– May improve circulation\n\n– May boost immunity\n\n– May aid in detoxification\n\nImage by amazon.com\n\n## Blue Onyx meaning and Chakra connection\n\n– Helps with communication and self-expression\n\n– Assists in finding your true voice\n\n– Aids in the communication of needs and truths\n\n– Facilitates creativity\n\n– Connects you to your higher wisdom\n\nBlue Onyx is connected to the Throat Chakra. Throat Chakra is located in the center of the neck at the level of Adam’s apple. It is connected to the element of Water and its color is blue. The Throat Chakra is responsible for communication, self-expression, and truth.\n\nThe Throat Chakra is out of balance when we have trouble communicating our needs or truths. We may be afraid to speak our minds or may hold back our creativity. When the Throat Chakra is balanced, we are able to express ourselves freely and creatively.\n\nBlue Onyx’s connection with the throat chakra makes it a stone with many healing benefits and also a solution for many problems. It helps us to express ourselves clearly, find our true voice, and to communicate our needs and truths. Blue Onyx also helps us to be creative and to access our higher wisdom.\n\n## Blue Onyx healing properties\n\nThe healing properties of blue onyx have been known for centuries. The stone is said to be effective in treating a wide range of ailments, from anxiety and depression to physical ailments such as headaches and stomach problems. \n\nLets go through all the major areas that Blue Onyx covers in our lives.\n\n## Blue Onyx emotional healing properties\n\n– Blue Onyx is said to be helpful in overcoming fears and phobias.\n\n– It is also said to be helpful in dealing with grief, loss and sadness.\n\n– Blue Onyx is said to promote inner strength and courage.\n\nBlue Onyx is the stone for soothing the mind and emotions. A cluttered mind is often the root cause of emotional imbalance and stress. The serenity of Blue Onyx can still the mind, bringing inner peace and emotional stability. \n\nIt is excellent for those who are prone to anxiety or panic attacks, as well as those who tend to overthink things. By calming the mind, Blue Onyx also helps to ease insomnia and promote restful sleep.\n\nBlue Onyx acts as that protective shield of the aura which bounces back the negative energies. It absorbs your negativities and transmutes them into positive ones. The stone is also useful when you want to get rid of your fear, phobias, and paranoia. It calms your mind and gives you the strength to face your fears.\n\nGiven the stone’s connection with mother earth, it sends negative vibrations into the earth to be grounded, and this is why it is also known as the “Worry Stone.”\n\n## Blue Onyx physical healing properties\n\n– Blue Onyx is believed to be helpful in the treatment of disorders of the bones and joints.\n\n– It is also said to be helpful in the treatment of disorders of the nervous system.\n\n– It is believed to be helpful in the healing of wounds and cuts.\n\n– Treats skin disorders. \n\n– Helpful in the treatment of toothaches and gum infections.\n\nWhile Blue Onyx is popularly known for its emotional and mental healing powers, this crystal possesses physical healing benefits as well which is now getting recognised by many healers.\n\nThis stone is believed to be helpful in treating disorders of bones, teeth, hearing and the eyes. It is also said to ease pains in the lower back and feet.\n\nIt helps in issues related to blood disorders and is also beneficial for regulating blood pressure and improving circulation. \n\nThis crystal is also known to help in the detoxification of the body and in the treatment of disorders of the digestive system. As per many healers, Blue Onyx syncs with the body’s natural rhythm and helps in the absorption of vitamins and minerals from food.\n\n## Blue Onyx metaphysical healing properties\n\n– Blue Onyx is known as a stone of protection and strength.\n\n– It is said to promote courage, stamina and self-discipline.\n\n– Blue Onyx is also known to be helpful in the development of psychic abilities.\n\n– It is said to be helpful in times of grief and sorrow, and to promote inner strength.\n\n– Aiding in communication\n\n– Helping you to achieve your goals\n\n– Manifesting your desires\n\n– Releasing negative emotions and thought patterns\n\n– Connecting you with your higher self and spiritual guides\n\n– Balancing the chakras\n\n– Healing the body, mind, and spirit\n\nBlue Onyx is a powerful stone that can help you achieve your goals and manifest your desires. It can also help you to release negative emotions and thought patterns. Blue Onyx connects you with your higher self and your spiritual guides. This process can help you to understand your true purpose in life. \n\nApart from emotional and physical healing, Blue Onyx connects with the body chakra as well. It aligns and balances the chakras, allowing for a free flow of energy throughout the body. \n\nBlue Onyx specifically connects with the throat chakra that is located in the center of the neck. This chakra is responsible for communication, expression and creativity. When this chakra is balanced, we are able to express ourselves clearly and creatively. We are also able to communicate our needs and wants effectively.\n\nIf you are looking for a stone that can help you to manifest your desires, achieve your goals and heal your body, mind and spirit, Blue Onyx is the stone for you!\n\nBeing able to communicate effectively and expressing yourself truthfully plays an important part in addressing the mental and emotional needs of an individual. It allows for the free flow of communication which in turn helps to foster healthy relationships.\n\n## How to best use Blue Onyx benefit \n\nBlue Onyx is a powerful crystal that deserves to be part of your daily life. There are many ways to use Blue Onyx but here are the best ones which give the maximum benefits:\n\n## During meditation\n\nBlue Onyx is the perfect crystal to use during meditation as it will help you to still your mind and connect with your inner wisdom. It will also enhance your concentration and focus. \n\nGiven it is an excellent stone for soothing your mind and emotions, using Blue Onyx while meditation can benefit you at different levels.\n\nAll you have to do is, hold the crystal in your hand or keep it close to you while meditating. Feel the vibrations\n\nof the crystal entering your body and filling you with a sense of calm and peace. Bring your attention to the stone and let it guide you into a deeper meditative state.\n\n## For concentration and focus\n\nIf you are looking to improve your concentration and focus, Blue Onyx is the crystal for you. It will help to still your mind and give you the clarity and mental strength that you need to stay focused on your goals.\n\nTo use Blue Onyx for concentration and focus, keep it close to you while working or studying. You can also wear it as a necklace or bracelet. Another option is to place it on your desk or workstation.\n\n## For decision-making\n\nIf you are struggling to make a decision, Blue Onyx can help. It will give you the clarity and confidence that you need to make the right choice.\n\nTo use Blue Onyx for decision-making, hold it in your hand while thinking about your options. Alternatively, you can place it on a table in front of you while making your decision. Let the crystal guide you towards the best option for you.\n\n## As jewellery\n\nBlue Onyx looks stunning when made into jewellery. Not only does it look beautiful, but it also has the added benefit of keeping the stone close to your body so that you can reap its benefits throughout the day.\n\nTo use Blue Onyx as jewellery, choose a piece that you love and wear it as often as you can. You can also give it as a gift to someone special in your life.\n\nA Blue Onyx bracelet is my personal choice as it’s the perfect way to keep the crystal close to your body while still being able to show it off.\n\nThe other form of Blue Onyx jewellery that i highly recommend is the Ring!\n\nWearing a Blue Onyx ring is said to promote spiritual insights, intuition and psychic abilities. It is also said to help with decision-making, promoting wise choices and banishing bad habits. \n\nBlue Onyx is also known as a stone of protection, helping to protect the wearer from negative energies and influences. Wearing it as a ring makes it more personal and intimate, as well as a beautiful piece of jewellery.\n\n## Best stone combinations with Blue Onyx\n\nWhile there are many ways to combine different stones together, here are some of the best combinations with blue onyx:\n\nBlue Onyx with Amethyst\n\nThis is a great combination for those who want to enhance their spiritual connection and intuition. Amethyst is a powerful stone that can help to open up the third eye chakra, while blue onyx can help to bring peace and calmness.\n\nBlue onyx with Turquoise\n\nThe perfect combination for those who want to promote communication and self-expression. Turquoise encourages communication, while blue onyx can help to soothe the mind and emotions. Together they make a great team for opening up and expressing themselves.\n\nBlue onyx with lapis lazuli\n\nA great combination for those who want to boost their psychic ability and intuition. Lapis lazuli is a stone that is known for its ability to open up the third eye chakra, while blue onyx can help to calm and focus the mind. This combination is perfect for those who are looking to enhance their psychic abilities.\n\nApart from the above crystal combinations, Yellow-coloured crystals have a special affinity with blue onyx and can be used to intensify, expand and activate its energies. \n\nCrystals that can be used in this way include citrine, lemon quartz, golden beryl and yellow tourmaline.\n\nBelow are some other stones that go very well with blue onyx:\n\n– Blue kyanite\n\n– Blue lace agate\n\n– Celestite\n\n– Larimar\n\n## Best ways to cleanse Blue Onyx\n\nAs we have seen above, Blue Onyx has many healing powers. But what happens when this crystal wades away all those negative energies from the wearer? \n\nHealing crystals like Blue Onyx absorb all the negativities. This is why they need to be cleansed and recharged from time to time to reignite their powers. Here are some ways to cleanse your crystal.\n\nUsing White light visualisation\n\nThis is one of the most popular ways to cleanse your crystals. To do this, simply hold your crystal in your hand and visualise it being bathed in white light. You can do this for as long or as short as you feel is necessary.\n\nHow this works is that the white light is said to be purifying and will cleanse your crystal of any negative energy it may have picked up.\n\nUsing Running water\n\nThis is another popular way to cleanse your crystals and can be done with either fresh or saltwater. Simply hold your crystal under running water for a few minutes, making sure that it comes into contact with all sides of the crystal.\n\nWater is one of the purest elements which washes off any negative energy that may be attached to your crystal.\n\nCleaning with salt\n\nThis method is similar to the running water method, but instead of using fresh water, you use salt water. Simply add some salt to a bowl of water and stir until it is dissolved. Then, place your crystal in the bowl and leave it for a few hours (or overnight if you can).\n\nThe salt will absorb any negative energy from your crystal, leaving it feeling refreshed and cleansed.\n\nCleansing with sage\n\nSage is a powerful herb that has been used for centuries for its cleansing properties. To cleanse your crystal with sage, simply hold your crystal in your hand and waft the smoke from a burning sage stick over it.\n\nThe smoke from the sage will purify your crystal and remove any negative energy it may have picked up.\n\n## Ways to recharge Blue Onyx\n\n1. Through affirmations: \n\nThis is a powerful way to recharge your crystal. some affirmations for Blue Onyx are:\n\n-I am safe\n\n-I am secure\n\n-I am surrounded by love and protection\n\n2. By sunlight: \n\nSunlight is also a great way to cleanse and recharge your crystals. Simply place your Blue Onyx in direct sunlight for a few hours.\n\n3. By moonlight: \n\nPlacing your crystal under the light of the moon is also said to be a great way to cleanse and recharge it.\n\n## What is the Blue onyx zodiac?\n\nThe blue onyx zodiac is Pisces. Pisces are known for their compassion, empathy, and intuition. They are also very creative and have a strong connection to the spiritual realm. \n\nBlue Onyx is a perfect stone for Pisces, as it helps to amplify their natural gifts and provides them with protection from negative energy.\n\nOther important questions (Answered!):\n\nWhat is the other name of Blue Onyx?\n\nThe other name of Blue Onyx is Lumerian Aquatine Calcite.\n\nWhat is lemurian blue onyx meaning?\n\nLemurian blue onyx is said to be a stone of wisdom and peace. It is believed to promote communication and understanding, and to help one find their true purpose in life.\n\nLemurian blue onyx is helpful in relieving stress and anxiety, and to promote relaxation and restful sleep.\n\nIs blue onyx dyed?\nNo, blue onyx is not dyed. It is a natural stone that forms in layers of white and blue.\n\nEnjoyed reading about Blue Onyx? Am sure you will love reading about Black Onyx as well. Do give this a read!"
