if gem = Gemstone.find_by(slug: "blue-tigers-eye")
  gem.meaning_content = "Table of Contents\n\nToggle\n\n• What is Blue tiger’s eye\n• Physical properties\n\n• Blue tiger’s eye meaning\n• Blue tigers eye healing properties\n• Physical healing properties of Blue tigers eye\n• ​​Metaphysical properties of blue tigers eye\n• Emotional healing properties of blue tigers eye\n\n• Uses of Blue tigers eye\n• Blue tigers eye as Jewellery\n• Blue tigers eye in healing \n• Blue tigers eye at home\n• Blue tigers eye at work\n\n• Varieties of Blue tigers eye \n• Chakras and Blue tigers eye meaning\n• Best crystals to combine with Blue tigers eye\n• Blue lace agate and blue tigers eye\n• Sodalite and blue tigers eye\n• Amazonite and blue tigers eye\n• Aquamarine and blue tigers eye\n\n• How to cleanse Blue tigers eye\n• Blue tiger’s eye as birthstone \n• Relationship, love and blue tigers eye \n• Money and Blue tigers eye\n• Can you sleep with Blue tigers eye\n• Who should wear Blue tigers eye\n• Is blue tiger’s eyes rare? \n• How to tell if Blue tigers eye is real\n• Is Blue tigers eye natural\n\n## What is Blue tiger’s eye\n\nBlue tiger’s eye is a type of quartz that is blue in colour and has shades of an ocean or sky. It is a stone known for bringing balance and peace. It has been around for a long time now and was famous since ancient times.\n\nIt has a natural appearance unlike other colours of the tiger’s eye. The blue colour of this gemstone is preserved because of the presence of iron in the quartz. \n\nIt is known by different names like hawk’s eye, falcon’s eye, Ox eye, Tiger iron and bull’s eye. \n\nFrom ancient times, it has been used as a talisman and amulet to ward off evil spirits and negative energy. It is also said to bring good luck. Blue tiger’s eye meaning is drawn from its potential to act as a protective stone.\n\nIt is believed to be linked to the energy of the planet Neptune and the element of water which makes it a powerful stone for psychic work and for connecting with the spirit realm. Blue tiger’s eye meaning is derived from the fact that this good luck stone is also known to promote courage, strength, and stamina. \n\nIt can be found in different parts of the world like Australia, Brazil, Canada, China, Czech Republic, India, Italy, Madagascar, Russia, South Africa, Spain, and the United States.\n\n## Physical properties\n\n• Colour: The colour of blue tigers eye can range from a deep blue to a light blue. It can also have shades of green, yellow, or brown.\n\n• Clarity: Blue tigers eye is typically semi-transparent.\n\n• Hardness: The hardness of blue tigers eye is 7 on the Mohs scale.\n\n• Specific Gravity: The specific gravity of blue tigers eye is 2.64.\n\n• Refractive Index: The refractive index of blue tigers eye is 1.544-1.553.\n\n## Blue tiger’s eye meaning\n\nBlue tigers eye meaning is a gemstone that is said to be helpful in promoting peace, harmony, and balance. It is linked with the Throat Chakra. It is said to be a stone of communication, helping one to express their ideas, thoughts, and feelings. \n\nThe Blue tiger’s eye is also said to be helpful in calming the mind and reducing stress. This gemstone not just has one meaning but different people attribute different meanings to this beautiful stone. It acts as a protective stone, warding off negative energy and promoting positive vibes. \n\nIn the olden days, it was used as a talisman to ward off evil spirits. It is known as the symbol of strength and courage. It helps one to overcome their fears, challenges in life and anxieties. Blue tiger’s eye crystal is known for its healing properties. It is said to be helpful in treating migraines, eye problems, and vertigo. It is also said to be helpful in relieving stress, tension, and anxiety.\n\n## Blue tigers eye healing properties\n\nThe Blue Tigers eye is a wonderful gemstone that helps to calm and centre the wearer. It is said to be helpful for those who tend to be scattered or easily distracted. It is also said to be helpful for those who have difficulty expressing themselves. \n\nIt is a strong stone for communication and can help to open up the channels of communication between people. It is known for its emotional, physical and metaphysical healing properties. Let’s have a look at each one of them\n\n## Physical healing properties of Blue tigers eye\n\n• Helping to relieve stress and tension: This stone helps in relaxing the mind and body by releasing stress and tension. It is also helpful in reducing anxiety and depression which in turn keeps many ailments away while keeping the body healthy.\n\n• Helping with respiratory problems: Blue tiger’s eye is helpful in treating respiratory problems such as asthma and bronchitis. It enhances the function of the lungs and respiratory organs while making sure they work properly. \n\n• Helping with digestive problems: This stone helps in treating digestive problems such as indigestion, diarrhoea, and constipation.\n\n• Helping with skin problems: This stone is believed to help in treating skin problems such as eczema and psoriasis.\n\n• Helping with menstrual problems : This stone helps in regulating the menstrual cycle and relieving cramps and other menstrual problems.\n\n## ​​Metaphysical properties of blue tigers eye\n\n• Enhancing psychic abilities: This stone is said to enhance psychic abilities and connect the wearer to their higher self.\n\n• Provides mental clarity: Blue tiger’s eye gives mental clarity and focus. It is also said to be helpful in increasing memory and concentration. Many use it as a necklace to benefit from the inner calm and stability that it provides.\n\n• Enhancing communication: This stone is believed to be helpful in enhancing communication skills. It is also said to be helpful in opening up the channels of communication between people. A clear thought process and communication skills can strengthen the inner self.\n\n• Increases creativity: This stone is said to be helpful in enhancing creativity and self-expression. One begins to open up themselves as they feel the push to explore new things. This helps in gradually enhancing creativity as one venture into new arenas. \n\n• Enhancing self-confidence: This stone is said to be helpful in increasing self-confidence and self-esteem. The inner voice within becomes strong and all the self-doubts begin to drift away. One feels confident on a daily basis and trusts the inner voice. You will trust your intuition and gut feelings more without doubting yourself. \n\n• Increases willpower: This stone is said to be helpful in increasing willpower and self-discipline. This in turn helps in achieving and making your dreams come true. \n\n• Enhancing courage and determination: Blue tiger’s eye is said to be helpful in increasing courage and strength. It also enhances determination so perseverance also is increased and achieving your goal becomes easier.\n\n## Emotional healing properties of blue tigers eye\n\n• Relieves stress and tension: Blue tiger’s eye stone helps in relaxing the mind and body by releasing stress and tension. It is also helpful in reducing anxiety and depression.\n\n• Calms and balances the emotions: This stone helps in calming and centring the emotions. It is also said to be helpful in dealing with emotional trauma. If one has suffered from past trauma and feels there is a blockage or a hindrance due to which they are not able to move forward, this stone helps in surpassing that. It gives the courage to move forward in life by dealing with those emotions. \n\n• Promote self-awareness: This stone is said to be helpful in promoting self-awareness and emotional understanding. It helps in listening closely to the inner voice and understanding where your happiness and peace lies. \n\n• Helps with self-acceptance: This stone is said to be helpful in promoting self-acceptance and self-love. You begin to learn more about yourself and the way you are. It gives you the confidence to love yourself and accept your flaws as is. \n\n• Promote self-forgiveness: This stone is said to be helpful in promoting self-forgiveness and healing. \n\n## Uses of Blue tigers eye\n\n## Blue tigers eye as Jewellery\n\nThis stone can be made into jewellery such as bracelets, necklaces, and rings. It is famously worn as a necklace as it remains close to the throat chakra. Thus, helping in unblocking and activating it. \n\nimage by indiamart.com\n\n## Blue tigers eye in healing \n\nThis stone can be used in healing by placing it on the body or holding it in the hand. It can also be used in meditation. \n\n## Blue tigers eye at home\n\nBlue tigers’ eyes can be placed in the home to promote calm and peace. It can also be used to enhance communication and creativity. It can be placed in the wealth corner of the home to attract more wealth and abundance into your life. \n\n## Blue tigers eye at work\n\nThis stone is said to be helpful in promoting communication and self-expression. It is also said to be helpful in promoting emotional balance and stability. This makes it a great stone to use at work. It will help to promote communication and understanding between coworkers. It will also help to reduce stress and anxiety.\n\n## Varieties of Blue tigers eye \n\n​​There are two main varieties of blue tigers eye \n\n1. Hawk’s Eye\n\nHawk’s eye is a variety of blue tigers eye that is blue-grey in colour. It is said to be helpful in promoting clarity and insight. \n\n2. Serpentine\n\nSerpentine is a variety of blue tigers eye that is green-blue in colour. It is said to be helpful in promoting emotional balance and stability.\n\n## Chakras and Blue tigers eye meaning\n\nBlue tiger’s eye is a very unique and versatile stone that can connect to many chakras. This makes it a super powerful stone.\n\nThe Blue tiger’s eye is associated with the throat chakra. The throat chakra is the fifth chakra and is located at the base of the throat. It is associated with the element of ether and is said to be the centre of communication and expression. The throat chakra is said to be responsible for communication, creativity, self-expression, and truth. \n\nThe Blue tiger’s eye is also connected with the third eye chakra which is the sixth chakra. The third eye chakra is located between the eyebrows and is associated with the element of air. It is said to be the centre of intuition and insight. When the blue tiger’s eye connects with the third eye chakra is said to enhance psychic abilities, intuition, and wisdom. \n\nIt can also connect with the higher chakras such as the crown chakra, the soul star chakra, and the cosmic chakra. \n\nThis makes it a powerful stone for spiritual growth and development. Using blue tigers’ eyes can make it easier to connect with the higher chakras and to access higher levels of consciousness. It can also be used to open up the third eye chakra and to develop psychic abilities.\n\n## Best crystals to combine with Blue tigers eye\n\nBlue tigers’ eyes can combine well with other blue stones. Especially when working with the throat chakra, the combination makes the impact stronger.\n\nSome of the best crystals to combine with blue tigers eye are:\n\n## Blue lace agate and blue tigers eye\n\nBlue lace agate is a stone that is said to be helpful in promoting communication and self-expression. These properties are similar to that of the blue tiger’s eye and hence the combination becomes perfect. It is also said to be helpful in calming the mind and emotions.\n\n## Sodalite and blue tigers eye\n\nSodalite is a stone that is said to be helpful in promoting communication and truth. It is also said to be helpful in promoting intuition and psychic abilities. Sodalite is a great stone to use in combination with blue tiger’s eye. It will help to enhance the communication and psychic properties of blue tiger’s eye.\n\n## Amazonite and blue tigers eye\n\nAmazonite is a stone that is said to be helpful in promoting communication and self-expression. It is also said to be helpful in promoting creativity and self-love.\n\nThese two stones work well together to help promote communication, self-expression, and emotional balance. They can also be used to help promote creativity and self-love.\n\n## Aquamarine and blue tigers eye\n\nAquamarine is said to be helpful in promoting communication and self-expression. It is also said to be helpful in promoting emotional balance and stability. This makes it a great stone to use in combination with blue tigers’ eyes. Aquamarine will help to promote communication, understanding, and compassion. It will also help to promote emotional balance and stability.\n\n## How to cleanse Blue tigers eye\n\nBlue tigers’ eyes can be cleansed using a variety of methods. Some of the most popular methods are:\n\nUsing Sunlight: Sunlight is a great way to cleanse and recharge blue tigers’ eyes. Simply place the stone in sunlight for a few hours. Make sure it is not kept in direct sunlight for long durations. \n\nUsing Moonlight: Moonlight is another great way to cleanse and recharge blue tigers’ eyes. It is considered to be a gentle and harmless form of cleansing a gemstone. Simply place the stone in direct moonlight for a few hours or overnight. Use affirmations as well while doing this process. Remove it the next morning and it is ready to use.\n\nUsing Running water: Running water is a great way to cleanse and recharge blue tigers’ eyes. Simply place the stone under running water for a few minutes and use a soft cotton cloth to wipe it off gently. It is a hard crystal and water does not affect its quality so water is considered safe to cleanse. \n\nSmudging: Smudging is a great way to cleanse and recharge blue tigers’ eyes. Simply hold the stone in the smoke of a smudge stick for a few minutes.\n\nSalt bath: You may also soak the blue tiger’s eye in a salt bath overnight. This will help in cleansing it. Use a soft cloth to wipe it off clean.\n\n## Blue tiger’s eye as birthstone \n\nThe Blue tiger’s eye is the natural birthstone for the month of June. It is also the zodiac stone for the sign of cancer. It can be given as a gift for a cancer birthday or as a gift for a June birthday which will help to promote calm and peace.\n\n## Relationship, love and blue tigers eye \n\nThe most important pillars of a relationship are – communication, compassion and calm. Blue tigers’ eyes are a great stone when it comes to these three pillars. It is said to be helpful in promoting communication and self-expression. It is also said to be helpful in promoting emotional balance and stability. \n\nGiving you calm and helping in sorting things out patiently while letting the other side communicate is what the blue tiger’s eye promotes. This makes it a great stone for those who are in a relationship or those who are looking for love. It will help to promote communication, understanding, and compassion. As a calming stone, it helps in reducing the tension in the air and brings positivity. \n\nThere are misunderstandings, confusion and many debates in a relationship. Resolving those issues calmly becomes important. The key to these issues is communication. A peaceful and calm communication helps in sorting out these issues. Blue tigers agate plays an important role in enabling this. \n\n## Money and Blue tigers eye\n\nMoney and ​​Blue tigers’ eyes are connected. The best way to use this stone for wealth is to keep it in your purse or wallet. You can also carry it with you when you go to interviews or meetings. This will help to increase your chances of success. It is said to help you make better decisions when it comes to money. It also attracts a flow of income to your home or work which is stable in nature.\n\nIt is believed to be excellent for entrepreneurs and business people.\n\nBlue tigers’ eyes can also be placed in the wealth corner of your home to attract more wealth and abundance into your life. \n\nYou can also place blue tigers’ eyes in your office or place of work to help you with your career and to attract more success.\n\n## Can you sleep with Blue tigers eye\n\nYes, you can sleep with blue tigers eye. This stone is said to be helpful in promoting calm and peace. It is also said to be helpful in promoting communication and self-expression. It is also said to be helpful in promoting emotional balance and stability. This makes it a great stone to use for sleep and relaxation. It will help to promote restful sleep and to reduce stress and anxiety.\n\n## Who should wear Blue tigers eye\n\nThis stone is said to be helpful for those who tend to be scattered or easily distracted. It is also said to be helpful for those who have difficulty expressing themselves. It is a strong stone for communication and can help to open up the channels of communication between people. It is known for its emotional and metaphysical healing properties. \n\nThis stone is also said to be helpful in promoting self-awareness and emotional understanding. It can also be used to help promote self-acceptance and self-love.\n\n## Is blue tiger’s eyes rare? \n\nNo, blue tigers’ eyes are not rare. It is a fairly common stone that can be found in many places around the world.\n\n## How to tell if Blue tigers eye is real\n\nThere are a few ways to tell if blue tigers’ eyes are real.\n\n• First, look at the colour of the stone. Real blue tiger’s eye should be a deep blue colour. If the stone is a lighter blue or has any other colours in it, it is not a real blue tiger’s eye.\n\n• Second, look at the surface of the stone. Real blue tigers eye should be smooth and have a glossy finish. If the surface of the stone is rough or dull, it is not a real blue tiger’s eye.\n\n• Third, hold the stone in your hand and focus your attention on it. Real blue tigers’ eyes should make you feel calm and peaceful. If the stone makes you feel anxious or stressed, it is not a real blue tiger’s eye.\n\n## Is Blue tigers eye natural\n\nYes, the blue tiger’s eye is a natural stone. It is not man-made or synthetic. It is found in nature and is not created in a laboratory."
