if gem = Gemstone.find_by(slug: "selenite")
  gem.water_safety_content = "No, Selenite can NOT go in water due to its hardness and water solubility.\n\nSelenite is a delicate and captivating crystal. It has gained popularity for its powerful energy cleansing properties. But with its increasing popularity comes the responsibility of knowing how to care for these fragile crystals.\n\nIn this article, uncover the truth about selenite’s relationship with water, specifically the answer to the question: can selenite go in water? Also, get practical tips for keeping Selenite crystals in pristine condition.\n\nTable of Contents\n\nToggle\n\n• Key Takeaways\n• Is Selenite Water Safe?\n• What happens if Selenite gets Wet?\n• Is Selenite Water Soluble?\n\n• Understanding Selenite’s Composition and Water Solubility\n• The Role of Water in Selenite’s Structure\n• Comparing Selenite with Other Water-Soluble Minerals\n\n• The Experiment: Testing Selenite’s Reaction to Water\n• Immediate Effects: What You Notice Right Away\n• Long-Term Exposure: Changes After an Extended Period\n\n• Practical Advice: Can Selenite Go in Water Safely?\n• Quick Cleansing with a Wet Cloth\n• Risks of Submerging Selenite in Water\n\n• Alternative Methods to Cleanse Selenite\n• Moonlight Charging: Harnessing the Full Moon’s Energy\n• Smudging with Dried Herbs\n\n• Selenite and Its Interactions with Different Types of Water\n• Selenite and Salt Water: A Cautionary Note\n• The Myth of Selenite Infused Moon Water\n\n• Preserving the Beauty of Selenite Crystals\n• Keeping Selenite Dry and Safe\n• Sunlight Exposure: Can Selenite go in the Sun?\n• How to Polish Selenite?\n\n• Know the Basics of Selenite Crystal\n• Is Selenite Toxic?\n• Is Selenite Safe to Touch?\n• Can you Wash Selenite?\n• How to Tell if Selenite is Real?\n\n• Summary\n• Frequently Asked Questions about Selenite Crystal\n• Can I take a bath with Selenite?\n• Can selenite go in the Sun?\n• Can selenite go in salt?\n• Which crystals cannot be cleansed in salt water?\n• Is selenite toxic?\n\n## Key Takeaways\n\n• Selenite is a fragile and water soluble material, thus it should be handled with caution to avoid permanent damage.\n• Understanding its composition and solubility can help preserve the beauty of selenite crystals.\n• Cleanse selenite using alternative methods such as moonlight charging or smudging with dried herbs instead of submerging in water.\n\n## Is Selenite Water Safe?\n\nNo, selenite is not water safe (unlike many other crystals) due to its low hardness and solubility in water. Ranking a mere 2 on the Mohs Hardness Scale, selenite is one of the softest crystals, making it particularly vulnerable to water. When exposed to water, selenite can dissolve and lose its luster.\n\nGiven its sensitivity, handle selenite with care and refrain from submerging it in water, even in a glass jar, as this may reduce the crystal’s size and sheen.\n\n## What happens if Selenite gets Wet?\n\nWhen selenite gets wet, its structure can be affected. It may become softer and more fragile, with its luster potentially diminishing. As selenite is soluble in water, it can even dissolve if exposed for an extended period. While some changes to selenite’s appearance and texture can be reversed, prolonged soaking of the crystal should be avoided, as it can result in irreversible damage.\n\n## Is Selenite Water Soluble?\n\nYes, selenite is water soluble, meaning it is capable of dissolving in water and should be kept away from it. Its solubility is due to its chemical composition of sodium selenite (Na2SeO3). Selenite dissolves at a relatively quick rate, so it is advisable not to submerge or cleanse it in water to prevent its dissolution. Factors such as temperature, pressure, and the amount of solute already dissolved in the water can also affect the rate of dissolution.\n\nHence, caution should be exercised with selenite to avoid its exposure to water.\n\n## Understanding Selenite’s Composition and Water Solubility\n\nSelenite’s chemical composition, or its chemical formula, is calcium sulfate dihydrate (CaSO4·2H2O), which plays a significant role in its water solubility. This gentle chemical structure allows water to dissolve selenite, reinforcing the need to keep the crystal dry and avoid water when cleaning it to prevent dissolution.\n\nSelenite’s solubility and the fact that selenite dissolve over time when exposed to water for an extended period, make it crucial to handle it carefully and minimize contact with water to retain its luster.\n\n## The Role of Water in Selenite’s Structure\n\nWater plays a role in selenite’s structure, as it exhibits slight solubility in water and interacts with its molecular structure through chemical reactions. In weakly acidic solutions, selenite can interact with sodium sulfide, which can affect its solubility.\n\nWater does contribute to selenite’s chemical composition, but remember, its exposure to water can result in dissolution and potential damage. Therefore, selenite should be handled carefully and water should not be used for its cleaning.\n\n## Comparing Selenite with Other Water-Soluble Minerals\n\nComparing selenite with other water-soluble minerals helps us understand its unique characteristics and how it responds to water. Water-soluble minerals share the commonality of being able to dissolve in water, undergoing a process of dissolution where the mineral particles break down and disperse in the liquid. Other crystals that are not suitable for water cleansing include:\n\n• Fluorite\n• Calcite\n• Kyanite\n• Malachite\n\nContact with water can cause these water-soluble minerals to dissolve and diminish, which underscores the need for careful handling of selenite to preserve its aesthetic appeal and properties.\n\n## The Experiment: Testing Selenite’s Reaction to Water\n\nTo further explore selenite’s reaction to water, an experiment was conducted to observe its response to water exposure in both the short and long term. Using various tools and methods, such as electrothermal atomic absorption spectrometer and breakthrough curve modeling, researchers were able to study the immediate and long-term effects of selenite’s exposure to water.\n\n## Immediate Effects: What You Notice Right Away\n\nIn the experiment, when selenite was exposed to water, it remained insoluble and did not dissolve or exhibit any visible alterations. This suggests that selenite may be more resilient to water exposure than initially thought. However, keep in mind that selenite still remains a soft mineral, necessitating careful handling to prevent damage.\n\n## Long-Term Exposure: Changes After an Extended Period\n\nOver time, the experiment revealed that exposure to water had detrimental effects on selenite, leading to diminished endurance and maximum swim, decreased gonad-somatic index (GSI) and cumulative production of eggs, and potential damage to the liver and kidneys.\n\nThese findings emphasize the need to avoid prolonged water exposure when managing selenite, as its delicate structure can degrade over time due to water.\n\n## Practical Advice: Can Selenite Go in Water Safely?\n\nBased on our understanding of selenite’s water solubility and the experiment’s findings, there are some practical tips for handling selenite when it comes to water exposure. While it’s crucial to avoid submerging selenite in water, there are alternative methods for cleansing and maintaining its beauty without causing damage.\n\n## Quick Cleansing with a Wet Cloth\n\nFor quick cleansing of selenite without causing damage, a wet cloth can be employed. Use a soft cloth, such as a damp rag or a soft toothbrush, to gently wipe the surface of the crystal. Be mindful not to use excessive water or apply too much pressure while scrubbing, as this could cause damage to the delicate crystal.\n\nEmploying a damp cloth allows you to effectively clean your selenite crystals without subjecting them to the risks linked to water submersion.\n\n## Risks of Submerging Selenite in Water\n\nSubmerging selenite in water carries several risks, including:\n\n• The potential for water to seep into the cracks of the stone and widen them, leading to structural damage and increased brittleness\n• The appearance of the crystals can be dulled\n• The optical properties of the stone can be compromised, potentially reducing its value\n\nTo safeguard the aesthetic allure and integrity of your selenite crystals, you should avoid submerging them in water and handle them gently.\n\n## Alternative Methods to Cleanse Selenite\n\nAs we’ve established that water is not a suitable method for cleansing selenite, it’s important to explore alternative methods that can effectively cleanse and maintain the crystal’s beauty without causing damage.\n\nTwo popular methods for cleansing selenite without using water are moonlight charging and smudging with dried herbs.\n\n## Moonlight Charging: Harnessing the Full Moon’s Energy\n\nHarnessing the full moon’s energy is a powerful way to charge and cleanse selenite crystals. To charge selenite with moonlight, follow these steps:\n\n• Find a sacred space, preferably in direct moonlight such as a windowsill.\n• Place the selenite crystals in the moonlight.\n• Leave them there for a few hours to absorb the gentle, calming energy of the moon.\n\nThis method enables you to cleanse your selenite without subjecting it to potential water damage.\n\n## Smudging with Dried Herbs\n\nAnother effective method to cleanse selenite without using water is smudging with dried herbs. To smudge selenite, you can use a smudge stick of your preference, such as sage, palo santo, or rosemary. Light the tip of the smudge stick and move the selenite through the smoke to purify it.\n\nThis method not only cleanses the crystal but also fills the surrounding environment with the positive energy of the dried herbs.\n\n## Selenite and Its Interactions with Different Types of Water\n\nSelenite exhibits distinct reactions to various types of water, including salt water and moon water. Understanding these interactions is essential for proper care and handling of selenite crystals, ensuring their beauty and energy remain intact.\n\n## Selenite and Salt Water: A Cautionary Note\n\nWhile selenite is insoluble in water, including salt water, it’s important to exercise caution when using salt water to cleanse or handle selenite. Salt water can weaken the material, cause cracking, or even cleave the crystal.\n\nTo retain the allure of your selenite crystals, it’s recommended to steer clear of salt water and choose alternative cleansing techniques like moonlight charging or smudging with dried herbs.\n\n## The Myth of Selenite Infused Moon Water\n\nThe belief that selenite can be infused with water to capture the energy of the moon is a myth due to the fact that selenite dissolves in water, thus rendering it unsuitable to be infused with water. Though the notion of selenite-infused moon water might sound enticing, remember that selenite is water-soluble and should not be combined with water for any reason, as it could result in the dissolution and possible harm to the crystal.\n\n## Preserving the Beauty of Selenite Crystals\n\nCaring for selenite crystals requires a gentle touch and an understanding of their unique properties. By following the tips and advice provided in this blog post, you can ensure that your selenite crystals remain beautiful and energetic, enriching your life and space with their calming presence.\n\n## Keeping Selenite Dry and Safe\n\nTo ensure your selenite remains dry and safe from potential water damage, it should be stored in a moisture-free location and kept away from humid environments. When cleaning selenite, use a damp cloth rather than a dripping one, and gently wipe the surface of the crystal.\n\nRemember to handle selenite with care and avoid using excessive water to prevent potential damage to the crystal.\n\n## Sunlight Exposure: Can Selenite go in the Sun?\n\nNo, Selenite can NOT go in the Sun. While sunlight can charge the energy of a selenite crystal, it’s important to avoid exposing it to direct sunlight for extended periods, as this can cause harm to the crystal, make it appear lackluster, and potentially attract negative energy.\n\nLong-term sun exposure can make selenite lose its sheen and appear dull, hence it’s recommended to keep it out of direct sunlight whenever feasible.\n\n## How to Polish Selenite?\n\nPolishing selenite is a delicate process that requires a gentle touch. Here’s how to do it:\n\n• Begin by sanding the crystal with 600 or 1000 grit sandpaper.\n• Use a slightly damp cloth with toothpaste to carefully polish the crystal.\n• Be gentle and light to avoid causing any damage to the delicate crystal.\n\nBy following these steps, you can maintain the luster and beauty of your selenite crystal, keeping it an attractive and energetic addition to your space.\n\n## Know the Basics of Selenite Crystal\n\nHaving a basic understanding of selenite crystal, including its toxicity, safety, and how to identify genuine selenite, is crucial for anyone drawn to the captivating energy of this unique crystal. By familiarizing yourself with the properties and care requirements of selenite, you can ensure you’re well-equipped to enjoy the benefits and beauty of this remarkable crystal.\n\n## Is Selenite Toxic?\n\nSelenite is not toxic when in a moist state. However, it’s important to exercise caution when handling selenite and to avoid ingestion or excessive exposure. While selenite is not toxic in its natural state, high doses of selenite may have adverse effects on muscle contractility and may lead to heart toxicity and breathing difficulties.\n\nConsequently, selenite should be handled cautiously to prevent ingestion or inhalation.\n\n## Is Selenite Safe to Touch?\n\nYes, Selenite is safe to touch. Selenite has no adverse effects on skin; hence, it is safe to touch and handle without gloves. No personal protective equipment is required for handling this crystal. As it is a soft mineral, it can be easily scratched and is warm to the touch due to its thermal insulating properties. While it is safe to handle, it’s important to be gentle with selenite to avoid causing any damage to the delicate crystal.\n\n## Can you Wash Selenite?\n\nYes, you can wash Selenite but caution is required due to its fragility and water solubility. To clean selenite, it’s recommended to run it under water and scrub it gently with a soft toothbrush. However, it should not be left submerged in water for an extended period, as this could cause the stone to disintegrate.\n\nAdditionally, it is suggested to dry the crystal promptly after cleaning.\n\n## How to Tell if Selenite is Real?\n\nTo tell if a selenite crystal is genuine, look for the following characteristics:\n\n• Transparency\n• Luster\n• Delicate crystal form\n• Excellent cleavage along distinct planes\n\nGenuine selenite is clear and colorless, whereas Satin Spar Selenite can be translucent and present in white or orange. Selenite’s low hardness means it can be easily scratched with a fingernail, leaving a white powdery residue.\n\n## Summary\n\nIn conclusion, selenite crystals are known for their captivating beauty and powerful energy cleansing properties. While their delicate nature requires special care when it comes to water exposure, it’s possible to maintain their beauty and energy by following the tips and advice provided in this blog post. By understanding the unique properties of selenite and practicing proper care, you can enjoy the benefits and beauty of this remarkable crystal for years to come.\n\n## Frequently Asked Questions about Selenite Crystal\n\n## Can I take a bath with Selenite?\n\nNo, you can not take a bath with Selenite. Selenite should not be placed in water or become too wet as it can dissolve. To enjoy the energies of love during your bath, add two rose quartz stones to your bathwater for optimal benefit.\n\n## Can selenite go in the Sun?\n\nNo, Selenite can not go in the Sun. Selenite can be left in the sun for a short time, but to maintain its properties and glossy sheen, it should be charged quickly by using meditation, mantras, incense, smudge sticks, or crystal grids.\n\n## Can selenite go in salt?\n\nNo, Selenite should not be put in salt as it has a low Mohs score of 2 and dissolves in both saltwater and normal water. To maintain its self-cleansing properties, cleanse it with a damp cloth.\n\n## Which crystals cannot be cleansed in salt water?\n\nSelenite, Calcite, and Fluorite should not be cleansed in salt water, as they are particularly vulnerable to the solution.\n\n## Is selenite toxic?\n\nSelenite is not toxic when in a moist state, but caution should be exercised to avoid ingestion or excessive exposure."
  gem.save!
  puts "  Updated gemstone: selenite"
end

if gem = Gemstone.find_by(slug: "smoky-quartz")
  gem.water_safety_content = "Smoky Quartz is safe when submerged in water, but should not be exposed to prolonged sunlight. Salt and direct contact with salt should be avoided as they can corrode and damage the crystal. Tap or spring/distilled water is recommended for cleaning Smoky Quartz. Other methods such as moonlight are also available if needed.\n\nCrystals have been making waves in the wellness scene lately, with their fascinating abilities to enhance emotional well-being, facilitate relaxation, and promote self-care. Among the myriad of crystals available, Smoky Quartz stands out due to its unique properties and versatility. However, to ensure that your Smoky Quartz crystal continues to serve you effectively, understanding the correct methods of care, such as knowing “can smoky quartz go in water,” is key.\n\nTable of Contents\n\nToggle\n\n• Is Smoky Quartz Water Safe?\n• Is Smoky Quartz Safe in Salt Water?\n• Can Smoky Quartz Go In Tap Water?\n• Can Smokey Quartz Go In the Sun?\n• Can Smoky Quartz Go In Salt?\n\n• Smoky Quartz and Water Interaction\n• The Mohs Hardness Scale and Smoky Quartz\n• The Impact of Water on Smoky Quartz’s Healing Properties\n\n• Caring for Your Smoky Quartz: Best Practices\n• How to Cleanse Smoky Quartz Without Water?\n• Sunlight and Smoky Quartz: A Delicate Balance\n\n• Creating Crystal Infused Water Safely\n• Understanding Which Crystals Dissolve in Water\n• The Role of Salt Water in Cleansing Crystals\n\n• The Do’s and Don’ts of Submerging Crystals in Water\n• Integrating Crystals into Water-Based Energy Healing\n• Gem Elixirs and Their Healing Potentials\n• Using Crystals in Baths for Emotional Balance\n\n• Summary\n• Frequently Asked Questions About Smoky Quartz In Water\n• Is quartz safe in water?\n• Can you wash smoky quartz?\n• How does Smoky Quartz interact with sunlight?\n• What are some safe ways to cleanse Smoky Quartz?\n\n## Is Smoky Quartz Water Safe?\n\nYes, Smoky Quartz can be submerged in water for cleansing, but avoid prolonged exposure to sunlight and salt water to maintain its condition.\n\nSmoky quartz crystal submerged in water\n\nA common query among crystal enthusiasts is the water-safety of their crystals. Generally, Smoky Quartz, part of the clear quartz crystal family, is water safe. As one of the quartz crystals that are safe for water, Smoky Quartz can be cleansed by briefly submerging it in water. Nonetheless, the kind of water used substantially influences the durability and effectiveness of the crystal.\n\nExposure to sunlight, however, is another story. While you might be tempted to leave your Smoky Quartz bathing in the sun’s rays, remember that extended exposure can lead to discoloration. Therefore, reconsider sun-soaking your Smoky Quartz, as it does not favor excessive sunlight.\n\n## Is Smoky Quartz Safe in Salt Water?\n\nNo, Smoky Quartz should not be placed in salt water as it can be damaged by the salt’s corrosive properties.\n\nThough Smoky Quartz is water safe, one must be cautious while using salt water for its cleansing. You might think that the combination of water and rock salt would be beneficial for your crystal, given the purifying properties often attributed to both elements. However, that’s not the case for Smoky Quartz.\n\nThe mineral composition of Smoky Quartz, primarily silicon dioxide, does not play well with salt water. The corrosive nature of salt can lead to rusting, cracks, or even gradual dissolution of the crystal. Essentially, your precious Smoky Quartz can start to degrade and lose its appealing appearance if exposed to salt water. So, while Smoky Quartz can go in water, salt water is a definite no-go.\n\n## Can Smoky Quartz Go In Tap Water?\n\nYes, Smoky Quartz can be cleansed in tap water, but distilled or spring water is preferred for purity.\n\nYou may indeed immerse your Smoky Quartz briefly in tap water. Tap water is generally safe for Smoky Quartz and can be used to cleanse it. However, for optimal results, distilled or spring water is recommended.\n\nEven though tap water will not harm the crystal or affect its healing properties, distilled or spring water is believed to be more effective. This is because these types of water are free from impurities that tap water may contain, providing a cleaner and more effective cleanse for your Smoky Quartz. Hence, even though Smoky Quartz is safe in tap water, opting for distilled or spring water could be beneficial.\n\n## Can Smokey Quartz Go In the Sun?\n\nYes, Smoky Quartz can go in the sun for short periods but should not be left for long to prevent fading.\n\nTime to rethink if you intend to expose your Smoky Quartz to prolonged sunlight. Despite its durability, Smoky Quartz is not a fan of the sun. Prolonged exposure to direct sunlight can cause the crystal to fade or even change color.\n\nThe culprit behind this discoloration is the UV light present in the sun’s rays. While a few hours of sunlight might not cause noticeable damage, leaving your Smoky Quartz in direct sunlight for extended periods can lead to a significant loss in color depth. In essence, despite Smoky Quartz’s durability, it is advisable to limit its sun exposure.\n\n## Can Smoky Quartz Go In Salt?\n\nNo, Smoky Quartz should not be placed in salt as it can be damaged by the salt’s corrosive properties.\n\nAs previously mentioned, Smoky Quartz does not interact well with salt water or salt. Placing your Smoky Quartz directly in salt can lead to corrosive damage and rusting.\n\nThe corrosive nature of salt, whether it’s sea salt, rock salt, or table salt, can lead to damage to the Smoky Quartz. This can result in fissures and the stripping off of the polish, diminishing the appearance of the stone. So, while Smoky Quartz is a hardy member of the quartz family, it’s best to keep it away from salt.\n\n## Smoky Quartz and Water Interaction\n\nSmoky quartz and water interaction\n\nComprehending Smoky Quartz’s interaction with water is key to preserving its healing attributes and visual appeal. This interaction is generally safe, thanks to the crystal’s hardness and durability. On the Mohs hardness scale, Smoky Quartz scores a 7, making it resistant to scratching or damage when placed in water.\n\nBut it’s more than just about physical durability. Water, in fact, has the potential to boost the healing properties of Smoky Quartz. When Smoky Quartz is submerged in water, it can act as a shielding and stabilizing crystal, transforming negative energies. However, like everything else, moderation is necessary. Avoid keeping Smoky Quartz immersed in water for too long.\n\n## The Mohs Hardness Scale and Smoky Quartz\n\nA look at the Mohs hardness scale can help comprehend why Smoky Quartz is usually safe for water contact. This scale is a rating system that determines the hardness of a crystal, with 10 being the hardest. Smoky Quartz scores a 7 on this scale, indicating that it’s quite durable and resistant to scratching or damage.\n\nNonetheless, a crystal’s compatibility with water is not solely determined by its hardness. Other factors, such as the salt content in the water, also play a part. For instance, soft crystals with a hardness rating of 7 or lower, like Smoky Quartz, are prone to corrosion when exposed to water with high salt content. Therefore, it’s advisable to avoid exposing such crystals to salty water.\n\n## The Impact of Water on Smoky Quartz’s Healing Properties\n\nApart from its physical resilience to water, what about the healing properties of Smoky Quartz? Interestingly, water can indeed enhance the healing properties of Smoky Quartz. When properly cleansed and charged, a water-submerged Smoky Quartz can act as a powerful healing tool.\n\nCleansing Smoky Quartz with water can help in releasing any stored negative or unwanted energies, enabling the stone to absorb positive frequencies and enhance its healing properties. It’s important to remember, though, that the crystal should not be left in the water for too long to prevent any potential damage.\n\n## Caring for Your Smoky Quartz: Best Practices\n\nAppropriate care for your Smoky Quartz guarantees not only its durability but also its efficacy in healing and energy work. As we’ve discussed, though Smoky Quartz is water-safe, there are safer and more effective ways to cleanse and charge this crystal.\n\nThe key to properly caring for your Smoky Quartz is knowing the best methods that will not harm the crystal or diminish its healing properties. These methods must be gentle yet effective, ensuring that your Smoky Quartz is not only physically clean but also energetically clear and charged.\n\n## How to Cleanse Smoky Quartz Without Water?\n\nSmoky quartz being cleansed under moonlight\n\nConsidering the possible problems with water and sunlight exposure, alternative methods to cleanse your Smoky Quartz might cross your mind. Fret not, for there are other methods available that are just as effective, if not more.\n\nCleansing methods involve moonlight, burying in soil, or using a selenite charging plate.\n\n• Moonlight is an excellent tool for reviving the healing energies of crystals.\n\n• Burying Smoky Quartz in soil can effectively cleanse and recharge it.\n\n• A selenite charging plate is also a good option, with selenite having a feminine energy that can charge other stones.\n\n## Sunlight and Smoky Quartz: A Delicate Balance\n\nDespite Smoky Quartz’s dislike for the sun, it doesn’t entirely exclude sunlight. In fact, Smoky Quartz can be charged in sunlight, but with a few precautions. The key is to strike a balance between benefiting from the sun’s energy and preventing harm to the crystal.\n\nBelow listed are care tips for Smoky Quartz.\n\n• Expose to sunlight for only a short period, preferably 2 to 3 hours\n\n• Prolonged exposure can result in a loss of color depth and fading\n\n• Limit exposure to direct sunlight\n\n• Protect from extreme heat\n\nBy following these care tips, you can maximize the longevity and effectiveness of your Smoky Quartz.\n\n## Creating Crystal Infused Water Safely\n\nCrystal-infused water preparation\n\nIf the concept of making your own crystal-infused water appeals to you, it is important to know which crystals are safe and how to correctly cleanse and charge them. Not all crystals are safe to submerge in water, and some may even dissolve when they come in contact with water.\n\nCreating crystal-infused water is not as simple as dropping your favorite crystal into a glass of water. The type of crystal, the water used, and the cleansing and charging methods all play a significant role in the safety and effectiveness of the resulting crystal-infused water. Using a crystal water bottle can help streamline this process.\n\n## Understanding Which Crystals Dissolve in Water\n\nA primary step in making crystal-infused water is identifying the safe crystals, as some can be considered water unsafe crystals. Particularly those with a softer material or lower score on the Mohs hardness scale may dissolve in water, making them unsuitable for creating crystal-infused water.\n\nPrior to creating your own crystal-infused water, ensure to research or seek advice from crystal experts. This will ensure that you’re using crystals that won’t dissolve in water, ensuring the safety and effectiveness of your crystal-infused water.\n\n## The Role of Salt Water in Cleansing Crystals\n\nWhile salt water may not be suitable for all crystals, it can be used for cleansing certain crystals. The key is to know which crystals can safely be submerged in salt water without causing damage.\n\nSalt water is often used as a cleansing agent due to its ability to clear negative energy. However, crystals should only be submerged in salt water for short periods to prevent any potential damage. In addition, it’s important to thoroughly rinse the crystals with clean water after a salt water cleanse to remove any residual salt.\n\n## The Do’s and Don’ts of Submerging Crystals in Water\n\nHaving examined the various facets of Smoky Quartz and water, it’s time to consider some general guidelines for immersing crystals in water. Keep in mind that while these guidelines are generally applicable, it’s always best to research the specific properties of each crystal before submerging it in water.\n\nDo: Ensure that the crystal you’re about to go in the water with is water-safe. This means it won’t dissolve in water or release any harmful substances when submerged.\n\nDon’t: Don’t leave your crystals in water for an extended period, especially if it’s salt water. Prolonged exposure to water, particularly salt water, can cause crystals to degrade or become damaged, and in some cases, even turn into toxic crystals.\n\n## Integrating Crystals into Water-Based Energy Healing\n\nGem elixirs and water-based energy healing\n\nCrystals can be incorporated into your everyday routines and energy healing practices, apart from cleansing and charging. One such practice is water-based energy healing, where crystals are used to charge water with their healing properties. This can be done through creating gem elixirs or by adding crystals to baths.\n\nIncorporating crystals into water-based energy healing can support emotional balance and amplify their healing abilities. However, it’s important to ensure that the crystals used are water-safe and have been properly cleansed and charged.\n\n## Gem Elixirs and Their Healing Potentials\n\nGem elixirs represent a potent method to utilize the healing attributes of crystals and precious stones. They’re created by infusing water with the energy of a crystal, creating a potent healing elixir. This water can then be consumed, used in baths, or even sprayed in the environment for space cleansing.\n\nWhile the idea of drinking crystal-infused water might seem strange at first, gem elixirs have been used for centuries in various cultures for healing purposes. From promoting emotional balance to boosting physical health, gem elixirs can serve as a valuable tool in your self-care and wellness routine.\n\n## Using Crystals in Baths for Emotional Balance\n\nOne more method of employing crystals in water-based energy healing is incorporating them into baths. This practice not only promotes relaxation but also helps to create emotional balance. Again, it’s crucial to ensure that the crystals used are water-safe.\n\nAdding Smoky Quartz to your bath can create a calming atmosphere, helping to soothe any emotional turmoil and promote a sense of balance. This can be especially beneficial after a long day, helping to wash away any negative energies and leaving you feeling refreshed and rejuvenated.\n\n## Summary\n\nIn conclusion, while Smoky Quartz can be safely submerged in water for cleansing, it’s important to be mindful of the exposure duration and the type of water used. Prolonged exposure to sunlight or salt water can potentially harm the crystal. Alternative cleansing methods, like using moonlight or burying in soil, can be just as effective without the potential risks. When creating crystal-infused water, it’s essential to ensure that the crystals used are water-safe and have been properly cleansed and charged. With proper care and usage, Smoky Quartz can continue to serve as a powerful tool in your wellness and self-care routine.\n\n## Frequently Asked Questions About Smoky Quartz In Water\n\n## Is quartz safe in water?\n\nQuartz crystals are safe to put in water, so they make an ideal choice for creating crystal elixirs.\n\n## Can you wash smoky quartz?\n\nIt’s safe to clean your Smoky Quartz using water and a small amount of soap, however be sure to rinse it off thoroughly and pat it dry afterwards. Do not leave Smoky Quartz in direct sunlight or soaked in water for long periods of time, and consider charging it up with Clear Quartz or smudging with sage instead.\n\n## How does Smoky Quartz interact with sunlight?\n\nSmoky Quartz is not recommended for prolonged exposure to sunlight, as it can cause the stone to fade or discolor.\n\n## What are some safe ways to cleanse Smoky Quartz?\n\nSmoky Quartz can safely be cleansed using moonlight, burying it in soil, or with a selenite charging plate."
  gem.meaning_content = "In the Quartz family of crystals, Smoky Quartz is one of the most well-known and popular varieties. Smoky Quartz meaning is linked with the power of grounding and protection. It helps to dissolve negative energy and bring emotional calmness.\n\nIt’s a semi-precious stone with healing properties that have been known and utilized since ancient times.\n\nIts connection to three of the chakra stones makes it a powerful all-around tool for spiritual growth and great addition to your crystal collection.\n\nThis guide covers everything you need to know about Smoky Quartz, including Smoky Quartz meaning, history, benefits, and how to use it.\n\nTable of Contents\n\nToggle\n\n• What is Smoky Quartz\n• Smoky Quartz meaning\n• History of Smoky Quartz\n• Smoky Quartz crystal Properties\n• Types of Smoky Quartz crystals\n• Smoky Quartz benefits\n• Smoky Quartz Healing properties\n• Emotional healing properties of Smoky Quartz stones\n• Physical healing properties of Smoky Quartz\n• Metaphysical healing properties of Smoky Quartz\n\n• Smoky Quartz and Chakra connection\n• The Best Crystals And Stones To Combine With Smoky Quartz\n• Ways to use Smoky Quartz\n• Ways to cleanse Smoky Quartz\n• Astrology And Smoky Quartz meaning\n• Zodiac signs and Smoky Quartz crystal\n• Other frequently asked questions about Smoky Quartz crystals\n• Smoky Quartz For Protection\n• Smoky Quartz For Concentration And Focus\n• Smoky Quartz For Grounding\n• Rose Quartz vs Smoky Quartz: What’s the Difference?\n• Lapis Lazuli vs Smoky Quartz: What’s the Difference?\n• How to choose the right Smoky Quartz\n\n## What is Smoky Quartz\n\nSmoky quartz is part of the quartz crystal family and is a brown to black variety that gets its name from its smoky color. It is a very common variety of quartz and is found in many different locations around the world. This charming stone has a long history of use for both practical and metaphysical purposes. It is a very popular gemstone and is used in a variety of jewelry pieces. It is also a popular choice for ornamental and lapidary purposes.\n\n## Smoky Quartz meaning\n\nSmoky Quartz meaning is all about practicality, endurance and strength. It is a grounding and stabilizing stone that gives you the motivation to get things done. This crystal is perfect for people who need a little extra push to get going. It can also help you to let go of negative emotions and thought patterns.\n\nIt is the national gem of Scotland for its connection to the country’s rugged landscape. It was also used as a talisman by the ancient Druids for its protective and healing properties.\n\n## History of Smoky Quartz\n\nSmoky Quartz has a long history of use as a talisman and amulet. The ancient Druids used it as a protective stone, and it was also used in Scottish folklore as a way to ward off evil spirits. In more recent times, it has been used as a healing stone for a variety of different ailments.\n\nThis crystal was first discovered in the early 19th century in the Swiss Alps. It quickly became popular for its unique color and its many benefits.\n\nAncient greek goddess of agriculture, Demeter, was known to wear a smoky quartz necklace during her search for her daughter Persephone. This crystal is known to relieve stress and anxiety. Smoky quartz is also a powerful stone for cleansing and purifying the body and mind.\n\nSmoke Quartz became one of the most popular crystals in the world and is still highly sought after today.\n\n## Smoky Quartz crystal Properties\n\nSmoky Quartz is a variety of Quartz that ranges in color from pale brown to nearly black.\n\nSmoky Quartz is found in many different locations around the world, including Brazil, Switzerland, and the United States.\n\nSmoky Quartz has a Mohs hardness of 7 and a trigonal crystal system.\n\nSmoky Quartz is often used in jewelry and as a decorative stone.\n\nIt is made of silicon dioxide and is considered a semiprecious stone.\n\n## Types of Smoky Quartz crystals\n\n• Cairngorm: A type of smoky quartz found in the Cairngorm Mountains of Scotland. Cairngorm quartz is said to have a calming effect on the wearer and is used to relieve stress and anxiety.\n\n• Morion: A darker, more opaque variety of smoky quartz. It is said to be helpful in dealing with grief and sadness.\n\n• Rutilated: A type of smoky quartz that contains needle-like inclusions of rutile. It is said to be helpful in promoting mental clarity and focus.\n\n• Smokey Citrine: A type of smoky quartz that has a yellowish-brown color. It is said to be helpful in manifesting abundance and prosperity.\n\n• Star: A type of smoky quartz that contains inclusions of rutile or hematite that form a star-like pattern. It is said to be helpful in aligning the chakras and promoting balance in the body.\n\n• Brandberg: A type of smoky quartz found in Namibia. It is said to be helpful in accessing the Akashic Records and is used in shamanic healing.\n\n• Dormant Volcano: A type of smoky quartz found in the area around Mt. Shasta in California. It is said to be helpful in activating the Earth Star chakra and is used in grounding and centering.\n\n• Smoky Amethyst Quartz: A type of smoky quartz that contains inclusions of amethyst. This type of Quartz is helpful in calming the mind and promoting relaxation.\n\n• Smoky Citrine Quartz: A type of smoky quartz that contains inclusions of citrine. It is said to be helpful in manifesting abundance and prosperity.\n\n• Smoky Topaz Quartz: A type of smoky quartz that contains inclusions of topaz. These are mostly used in promoting mental clarity and focus.\n\n## Smoky Quartz benefits\n\n• Aids in the manifestation of one’s dreams and desires\n\n• Helps to ground and center one’s energy\n\n• Aids in relieving stress and anxiety\n\n• Helps to transmute negative energy\n\n• Protects against negative influences and entities\n\n• Enhances one’s psychic abilities\n\n• Aids in meditation and visualisation\n\n• Helps establish a connection with mother earth\n\n• \n\n## Smoky Quartz Healing properties\n\nSmoky Quartz crystal meaning is particularly powerful when it comes to grounding and protection, making it one of the most popular stones in crystal healing. If you’re looking for a stone that can help you get in touch with your natural strength and power, or if you’re in need of some extra support during a time of change or challenge, smoky quartz is an excellent choice.\n\n## Emotional healing properties of Smoky Quartz stones\n\n• Aids in relieving stress and anxiety\n\n• Helps to ground and center one’s energy\n\n• Aids in releasing negative emotions and thought patterns\n\n• Encourages positive thinking and emotional balance\n\n• Helps build self-confidence\n\n• Excellent grounding stone\n\nSmoky Quartz is a perfect stone for those who are seeking emotional healing. During situations that are stressful and make one feel anxious, holding or wearing Smoky Quartz can help to ground and center one’s energy.\n\nBeing able to hold on to the calm and deal with the situation with a complete balance of emotions is a great strength that this stone can offer.\n\nIf you find yourself dwelling on negative emotions or thought patterns, Smoky Quartz can be a great stone to help you release negative energies and make space for more positive thinking.\n\nWhen doubting yourself and your abilities, Smoky Quartz can boost confidence and encourage you to think positively and stay balanced. It helps develop the lost self-confidence within you.\n\nIt will ease the survivor’s guilt, self-blame, and self-hatred. It will give you the courage to face your fears and trust your intuition by eradicating negative vibrations.\n\n## Physical healing properties of Smoky Quartz\n\n• Helps with headaches, muscle aches and stomach upsets\n\n• Detoxifies the body\n\n• Pain relief\n\n• Strengthens the immune system\n\n• Relieves back pain, neck pain, and headaches\n\n• Treats conditions like carpal tunnel syndrome and Raynaud’s disease\n\n• Eases the pain of arthritis and joint problems\n\n• Reduces the effect of electromagnetic smog and radioactive materials\n\nApart from being an excellent emotional healing crystal, Smoky Quartz is also beneficial for physical healing. Those suffering from anxiety, get affected physically also.\n\nThis crystal can ease symptoms like tension headaches, muscle aches, and stomach upsets. It also detoxifies the body, helps in pain relief and strengthens the immune system.\n\nSmoky Quartz crystal is also known to relieve back pain, neck pain, and headaches. It is also helpful in treating conditions like carpal tunnel syndrome and Raynaud’s disease.\n\nThis crystal can also be used to ease the pain of arthritis and joint problems.\n\nSmoky Quartz properties make it one of the best absorbers in the gemstone community. This makes it the preferred crystal for those affected by EMF and are sensitive to environmental pollution. Smoky Quartz is also excellent for those who are going through radiation therapy.\n\n## Metaphysical healing properties of Smoky Quartz\n\n• Helps shield against the negative energy field\n\n• Helps to ground and anchor you\n\n• Aids in meditation and stilling the mind\n\n• Enhances dreams and astral travel\n\n• Connects you with the earth’s energy\n\n• Keeps the aura clear and positive\n\n• Aids with psychic shielding\n\nSmoky Quartz is a very powerful and protective stone with many metaphysical properties. It is often used for psychic shielding. Smoky Quartz grounds and anchors you to the earth, allowing you to let go of negative energies and thought patterns.\n\nIt is said to be particularly helpful in removing negative energy from the environment.\n\nThe Smoky Quartz crystals are an excellent stone for meditation and can help to still the mind and bring about a deep sense of peace. It can also be used to enhance dreams and astral travel.\n\nSmoky Quartz is associated with the root chakra which is the base chakra that governs our sense of security and grounding. The root chakra is associated with the element of earth, and so Smoky Quartz can be used to connect with the earth’s energy.\n\nIt can also help to ground and anchor you when you are feeling scattered or ungrounded.\n\n## Smoky Quartz and Chakra connection\n\n– Connected to the Root chakra, Crown chakra and Solar plexus\n\n– Associated with the element of Earth\n\n– Helps with feeling grounded\n\n– Aids in balancing the energies of the body\n\n– Releases lower vibrational energies from the body\n\nSmoky quartz is connected to the root chakra. The Root chakra is located at the base of the spine and is associated with the element of earth. The base chakra is responsible for our feeling of safety and security in the world. It is also connected to our survival instincts and our sense of self-preservation.\n\nWhen unblocked and balanced, the root chakra allows us to feel grounded and connected to the earth. We feel safe, secure and confident. We are able to stand up for ourselves and our beliefs.\n\nWhen the root chakra is blocked or imbalanced, we may feel anxious, fearful or even paranoid. We may feel disconnected from the world around us and disconnected from our own bodies. We may have trouble trusting others or feeling safe in our environment.\n\nSmoky Quartz makes sure that the energy flow in the body is unhindered. It helps to clear and ground the chakras and to release negative energy from the body. It is also helpful in balancing the energies of the body and in aligning the chakras.\n\nSolar plexus chakra and Smoky Quartz meaning\n\nThe solar plexus chakra is located in the upper abdomen, just below the sternum. It is associated with the element of fire, and its energy is said to be very powerful and intense. Smoky quartz is said to be a very effective stone for balancing and clearing this chakra. It is also said to be helpful in relieving stress and anxiety and promoting a sense of calm and peace.\n\n## The Best Crystals And Stones To Combine With Smoky Quartz\n\nBlack Tourmaline\n\nA powerful protective stone, black tourmaline is excellent for absorbing and grounding negative energy. It can also help to boost the healing properties of smoky quartz. When these two are combined, they create a potent stone pairing that can cleanse and protect your auric field.\n\nObsidian\n\nAnother excellent stone for protection, obsidian can help to create a shield around your energy body. It can also assist in the release of negative emotions and patterns. Combined with smoky quartz, obsidian makes for a powerful stone ally in your journey of self-transformation.\n\nAmethyst\n\nA stone of spiritual protection and purification, amethyst can help to cleanse your energy field and open you up to higher states of consciousness. It can also assist in the release of negative attachments and patterns. Combined with smoky quartz, amethyst makes for a powerful stone duo that can help you to let go of the past and move forward into the light.\n\n## Ways to use Smoky Quartz\n\nAs Jewelry\n\nSmoky Quartz can be made into beautiful jewelry that can be worn every day. The stone can also be used as a talisman or amulet to protect the wearer from negative energy. Smoky Quartz jewelry can be worn as a bracelet or necklace. Wearing them every day helps to cleanse and protect your energy field.\n\nSmoky Quartz necklace\n\nWearing a smoky quartz necklace not only gives a stylish look but also protects the wearer from negative energy. It is believed to be a powerful stone that can help to deflect negative energy and promote positive vibes. It is also thought to be helpful in relieving stress and anxiety.\n\nIn the Home\n\nSmoky Quartz can be used to cleanse and purify your home. Place Smoky Quartz stones in every room to absorb negative energy and create a protective barrier.\n\nAt Work\n\nSmoky Quartz can be placed on your desk or in your office to help you stay grounded and centered. This grounding stone will help to deflect negative energy from co-workers and clients and attract positive energy.\n\nIn Meditation\n\nSmoky Quartz can be used in meditation to help you connect with your higher self. The stone will also help to clear your mind and release negative thoughts. Keep the crystal on the palm while meditating and focus on your breath.\n\nFor Healing\n\nSmoky Quartz can be used to heal the mind, body, and soul. The stone helps to release negative emotions, unwanted energy and traumatic memories. It can also be used to relieve pain and tension.\n\nFeng Shui\n\nSmoky quartz is excellent for use in Feng shui. It is a very grounding and protective stone and can help to create a feeling of safety and security in your home. It is also said to promote good luck and fortune.\n\nSmoky quartz can be placed in any area of your home or office to help create a more positive and supportive environment. It is particularly effective in the career and wealth areas of your feng shui chart.\n\n## Ways to cleanse Smoky Quartz\n\nUsing Water\n\nUse running water to cleanse your smoky quartz. You can do this by holding the crystal under a running faucet or by placing it in a bowl of water. Let the crystal sit in the water for a few minutes, then remove it and allow it to air dry.\n\nUsing Salt\n\nSalt is a natural cleanser and can be used to cleanse your smoky quartz. Simply mix some salt with water and stir until the salt has dissolved. Then, place your crystal in the solution and let it sit for a few minutes. Rinse the crystal off with fresh water and allow it to air dry.\n\nUsing Incense\n\nYou can cleanse your smoky quartz with incense smoke by holding the crystal over a burning stick of incense. Allow the smoke to waft over the crystal for a few minutes, then place the crystal in a safe place to air dry.\n\nUsing Sunlight\n\nSunlight is a great way to cleanse your smoky quartz. Simply place the crystal in direct sunlight for a few hours. The sun’s rays will help to remove any negative energy from the crystal and restore the stone’s energy.\n\nMake sure the crystal is not in direct sunlight for too long, as this can cause the crystal to fade.\n\nUsing Moonlight\n\nMoonlight is another great way to cleanse your smoky quartz. Simply place the crystal in direct moonlight for a few hours. The moon’s energy will help to remove any negative energy from the crystal.\n\nKeeping crystal in moonlight overnight will not be harmful.\n\nSmoky Quartz grid\n\nSmokey Quartz crystal can be used to create a grid around your home or property. This will help to protect your space from negative energy and will also promote positive energy flow.\n\nTo create a grid, you will need 9 Smokey Quartz crystals. Place one crystal at each of the 4 corners of your property and then place one in the center. Place the remaining 4 crystals at the 4 cardinal points (north, south, east, and west).\n\nSmoky Quartz elixir\n\nSmoky Quartz can be used to create an elixir that can be used to promote positive energy and to cleanse and purify the body. To make the elixir, place a natural Smoky Quartz crystal in a bowl of water and allow it to charge in the sun for a few hours.\n\nAfter the elixir has been charged, drink it throughout the day or use it to cleanse your body by bathing in it.\n\n## Astrology And Smoky Quartz meaning\n\nSmoky quartz is a very popular gemstone, and it is believed to have a number of astrological benefits. The stars and planets are said to be especially beneficial if you wear smoky quartz, as it is thought to bring good luck and protection.\n\nThe stone is also said to be helpful in promoting success in business and career. It is believed to enhance one’s ability to focus and think clearly. Smoky quartz is also thought to be helpful in relieving stress and tension.\n\n## Zodiac signs and Smoky Quartz crystal\n\nSmoky Quartz is a particularly good stone for those who are sensitive to energy and can be used to help protect against negative energy. It is also said to be helpful for those who are going through difficult times or are feeling overwhelmed.\n\nSmoky Quartz is associated with the zodiac sign Scorpio and is said to be helpful for those who are going through a difficult time or are feeling overwhelmed. Scorpio is a sign that is known for its intensity and power, and Smoky Quartz is said to be a stone that can help harness and focus that energy.\n\n## Other frequently asked questions about Smoky Quartz crystals\n\n## Smoky Quartz For Protection\n\nSmoky Quartz is a gemstone that can be used for protection against negative energy. It helps cleanse and protect the aura and also helps shield the wearer from negative thoughts and feelings. Smoky Quartz crystals keep unwanted energies out and help to relieve stress.\n\n## Smoky Quartz For Concentration And Focus\n\nSmoky quartz crystals are powerful stones for those seeking to improve their concentration and focus. The smoky color of the stone is said to help ground and center the wearer, promoting a calm and clear mind. This makes smoky quartz an excellent choice for those seeking to improve their mental clarity and performance for a brighter future.\n\nSmoky quartz is also said to be helpful for those who suffer from anxiety or stress. The stone is said to promote relaxation and peace of mind, helping to ease stress and worry.\n\n## Smoky Quartz For Grounding\n\nSmoky Quartz crystal’s connection with mother earth makes it the perfect stone for grounding and connection. These grounding stones provide a sense of security and safety, while also promoting creativity and problem-solving.\n\nThe grounding properties of Smoky Quartz can also be helpful when you are feeling scattered or disconnected. It can help to center and focus your energy, while also promoting a sense of calm and peace.\n\n## Rose Quartz vs Smoky Quartz: What’s the Difference?\n\nSmoky quartz is a member of the quartz family and is closely related to rose quartz. Both minerals are composed of silicon dioxide (SiO2) and have a hexagonal crystal structure. The main difference between smoky quartz and rose quartz is its color. Smoky quartz is black, brown, or grey in color, while rose quartz is pink.\n\n## Lapis Lazuli vs Smoky Quartz: What’s the Difference?\n\nThese are two different types of stones that are often used in jewelry and other decorative objects.\n\nOne of the most significant differences between them is their hardness. Lapis lazuli has a Mohs hardness of 5-6, while smoky quartz has a Mohs hardness of 7. This means that smoky quartz is significantly harder and is less likely to scratch or chip\n\n## How to choose the right Smoky Quartz\n\nSmoky Quartz is a great choice for those who are looking for a dark, moody gemstone. It ranges in color from a light brown to a deep, rich black, and can even be found in a smoky grey. This gemstone is perfect for those who want to add a touch of darkness to their jewelry collection.\n\nWhen choosing Smoky Quartz, it is important to keep in mind the gemstone’s hardness. Smoky Quartz is a 7 on the Mohs Scale of Hardness, which means it can scratch easily. It is important to choose a Smoky Quartz that has been cut and polished properly, so that it will not show any damages easily.\n\nSmoky Quartz is a great choice for those who are looking for a unique gemstone. These dark stones are perfect for those who want to add a touch of darkness to their jewelry collection."
