Article.find_or_create_by!(slug: "handyman-business-ideas") do |a|
  a.title = "50 Most Profitable Handyman Business Ideas for Starting Your Own Business"
  a.excerpt = "Starting a handyman service company can be a profitable business venture, especially for those with specialized skills and experience in a range of areas. The market for odd jobs, small repairs, and other services is constantly growing, and there is a wide range of services that a handyman can offer to prospective customers in need … Read more"
  a.content = "Starting a handyman service company can be a profitable business venture, especially for those with specialized skills and experience in a range of areas. The market for odd jobs, small repairs, and other services is constantly growing, and there is a wide range of services that a handyman can offer to prospective customers in need of home repairs and improvements.\n\nFrom carpentry skills to other specialized areas, there are certain jobs that are in high demand and can be especially lucrative for a handyman. However, running a successful handyman business requires more than just technical know-how; it also involves business operations, managing business expenses, and identifying and targeting the right market to grow the business.\n\nIn this blog, we’ll explore the 50 most profitable handyman business ideas to help you find the right niche and make a successful start in the industry.\n\nTable of Contents\n\nToggle\n\n• Definition of a Handyman Business\n• Most profitable handyman business ideas and business model\n• 1. General home repairs and maintenance\n• 2. Carpentry and woodworking services\n• 3. Plumbing repairs and installations\n• 4. Electrical services and installations\n• 5. Painting and decorating services\n• 6. Flooring installation and repairs\n• 7. Drywall and plastering services\n• 8. Roofing and gutter repairs\n• 9. Window and door repairs and installations\n• 10. Fence and deck repairs and installations\n• 11. Power washing and exterior cleaning services\n• 12. Landscaping and lawn care services\n• 13. Snow removal and winter services\n• 14. Furniture assembly and installation\n• 15. Appliance repairs and installations\n• 16. Interior design and decor consultations\n• 17. Custom shelving and storage solutions\n• 18. Lighting and fixture installations\n• 19. HVAC repairs and installations\n• 20. Home security system installations\n• 21. Home automation and smart home installations\n• 22. Home theatre and audio-visual installations\n• 23. Pet door installations\n• 24. Pressure washing and exterior cleaning services\n• 25. Pest control services\n• 26. Garage door repairs and installations\n• 27. Art hanging and installation\n• 28. Storage unit cleanouts and organization\n• 29. Event setup and tear-down services\n• 30. Handyman services for businesses and offices\n• 31. Mobile locksmith services for homes and businesses\n• 32. Swimming pool maintenance and repair\n• 33. Kitchen and bathroom remodeling\n• 34. Green energy and sustainability consulting\n• 35. Building maintenance for property management companies\n• 36. Home and office cleaning services\n• 37. Moving and relocation assistance\n• 38. Water damage restoration and mold remediation\n• 39. Audio and video system installations\n• 40. Disaster cleanup and restoration services\n• 41. Air conditioning installation, repair, maintenance and service\n• Boat cleaning service\n\n• How much does it cost to start a handyman business?\n• Advantages of Starting a Handyman Business\n• Professional Service Offered\n\n## Definition of a Handyman Business\n\nA handyman business is a type of service-oriented company that provides various home maintenance and repair services. The primary focus of a handyman business is to offer affordable and efficient services to help homeowners, renters, and small business owners maintain and improve their properties.\n\nTypically, a handyman business will offer a broad range of services, including general repair work, maintenance services, and installation services. These services can range from simple tasks such as changing light bulbs or fixing a leaky faucet to more complex jobs such as installing a new appliance or repairing a damaged roof.\n\nA handyman business can be run as a sole proprietorship, partnership, or limited liability company (LLC). A handyman business owner may choose to work independently or hire employees to assist with the workload. In addition, some handyman businesses specialize in specific services such as plumbing, electrical work, or carpentry.\n\nOne of the benefits of starting a handyman business is the ability to offer a flexible schedule to customers, often including emergency repairs outside of typical business hours. This can be particularly attractive to homeowners who work during the day and need someone to be available for repairs outside of regular business hours.\n\n## Most profitable handyman business ideas and business model\n\n## 1. General home repairs and maintenance\n\nThis is a broad category that includes a variety of home repair services. Some examples of general home repairs and maintenance services that a handyman business can offer include fixing leaky faucets, repairing drywall damage, replacing light fixtures, repairing or replacing door knobs, patching holes in walls, fixing or replacing toilets, unclogging drains, and more. \n\nGeneral home repairs and maintenance services are in high demand, as homeowners and renters alike often have small projects or repairs that need to be taken care of but do not require the services of a specialized contractor.\n\n## 2. Carpentry and woodworking services\n\nCarpentry and woodworking services are popular offerings for a successful handyman business. Skilled carpenters and woodworkers can provide a range of services, from building custom furniture and cabinetry to repairing damaged woodwork in homes or offices.\n\nThis type of work requires specialized tools and knowledge of different types of wood and joinery techniques, making it a valuable service for customers who want high-quality, durable woodwork in their homes or businesses. \n\nA handyman business that offers carpentry and woodworking services can set itself apart from competitors and attract customers who value craftsmanship and attention to detail.\n\n## 3. Plumbing repairs and installations\n\nPlumbing repairs and installations are critical offerings for most handyman businesses. From fixing leaky faucets and clogged drains to installing new toilets and water heaters, a skilled handyman can provide a range of plumbing services for both residential and commercial customers.\n\nAs plumbing issues can be urgent and cause significant damage if not addressed promptly, providing fast and reliable plumbing services can help drive business growth for a handyman job.\n\nBy building a reputation for expertise in plumbing repairs and installations, a handyman business can attract new customers and retain existing ones through word-of-mouth recommendations. \n\nA new business can be built as a carpet installation business as well. With the right tools and training, a handyman can expand their skillset and become a go-to expert for all plumbing-related needs.\n\n## 4. Electrical services and installations\n\nElectrical services and installations involve working with wiring, circuits, outlets, and light fixtures. A handyman business that offers electrical services can install new light fixtures, replace or repair broken outlets, troubleshoot electrical issues, and install electrical appliances like ceiling fans. \n\nIt is important to ensure that anyone performing electrical work is properly licensed and certified to do so, so a handyman business should ensure that their technicians are properly qualified to perform these services.\n\n## 5. Painting and decorating services\n\nPainting and decorating services are a popular and profitable offering for a new handyman business. From interior painting to wallpaper installation, a skilled handyman can provide a range of services to meet client expectations and enhance the appearance of homes and businesses.\n\nOffering a variety of finishes and color options, a handyman can help clients achieve their desired look and create a customized space. With the right skills and tools, painting and decorating services can be some of the most profitable jobs for a handyman. \n\nBy providing high-quality work and exceptional customer service, a handyman can build a reputation for excellence and attract new clients through word-of-mouth referrals.\n\nWith the added benefit of repeat business and the potential for upselling additional services, painting and decorating can be a lucrative addition to any handyman’s portfolio of offerings.\n\n## 6. Flooring installation and repairs\n\nA handyman business that offers flooring installation and repairs can provide services such as installing new hardwood floors, replacing damaged tiles, or repairing floorboards. Offering flooring installation and repairs is a great way to add value to a homeowner’s property as well as improve the overall appearance of a home.\n\n## 7. Drywall and plastering services\n\nDrywall and plastering services involve repairing holes and cracks in walls and ceilings, installing new drywall or plastering an entire room. A handyman business can offer drywall and plastering services for both residential and commercial properties and can help property owners keep their space in great condition.\n\n## 8. Roofing and gutter repairs\n\nA handyman business that offers roofing and gutter repairs can help homeowners fix leaks, repair shingles, and fix any other roofing issues. Gutter repairs and cleaning are also important services to offer, as clogged gutters can cause damage to a home’s foundation over time.\n\n## 9. Window and door repairs and installations\n\nWindow and door repairs and installations involve replacing broken windows, repairing window and door frames, and installing new windows and doors. A handyman business that offers these services can help homeowners improve the safety and efficiency of their homes while enhancing the overall appearance.\n\n## 10. Fence and deck repairs and installations\n\nFences and decks can add significant value to a property, and repairing or installing these structures is often beyond the scope of a homeowner’s DIY abilities. A handyman business can offer services such as repairing fence posts, installing new fence panels, or repairing and staining a deck. \n\nThis is a great service to offer, especially in areas with lots of outdoor living spaces, as homeowners often need"
  a.category = cat
  a.published = true
  a.published_at = DateTime.parse("2023-02-20T13:23:56")
end

