Article.find_or_create_by!(slug: "11-best-crystals-for-grief") do |a|
  a.title = "11 Best Crystals For Grief, Trauma And Loss"
  a.excerpt = "Grief is a feeling of deep sadness in response to loss. It is a natural response to death, divorce, job loss, and other forms of loss. People deal with grief in different ways. Some people may withdraw from friends and family, while others may seek comfort from them. Dealing with grief is difficult and not … Read more"
  a.content = "Grief is a feeling of deep sadness in response to loss. It is a natural response to death, divorce, job loss, and other forms of loss. People deal with grief in different ways. Some people may withdraw from friends and family, while others may seek comfort from them.\n\nDealing with grief is difficult and not always linear. There is no “right” or “wrong” way to grieve, and each person will experience grief differently. Some common coping mechanisms include talking about the loss, spending time with loved ones, crying, journaling, and participating in activities that bring joy.\n\nUsing grief crystals to help with trauma can be a soothing method to help ease the pain. while they don’t take away the hurt, they can help to refocus and ground the individual.\n\nTable of Contents\n\nToggle\n\n• Stages of grief and loss\n• Denial\n• Anger\n• Bargaining\n• Depression\n• Acceptance\n• Hope\n\n• Best 11 Healing crystals for grief\n• Amethyst – Emotional Healing\n• Rose Quartz – Compassion and Forgiveness\n• Hematite – Helps to ground and protect from negative energy\n• Black Tourmaline – Protection and Grounding\n• Smoky Quartz – Positive Energy\n• Rhodonite – Encourages emotional healing and understanding\n• Moonstone – Emotional balance\n• Obsidian – Emotional Purification and Transformation\n• Pink Opal – Helps to open the heart and nurture inner peace\n• Pyrite – Promotes joy and optimism in difficult times\n• Lepidolite – Supports transformation and renewal\n\n• How to use crystals for grief\n• Other Grief Crystals and Stones\n\n## Stages of grief and loss\n\nGrief takes its own pace to work through. There are no ‘right’ or ‘wrong’ ways to feel, and no timeline for grief. However, most people tend to experience similar thoughts and emotions in a similar order.\n\nThe stages of grief and loss are typically broken down into five stages: denial, anger, bargaining, depression, and acceptance. However, it is important to note that these stages are not always experienced in a linear fashion and that people may move back and forth between them. Additionally, not everyone experiences all five stages.\n\n## Denial\n\nIn the first stage, denial, individuals may refuse to believe that the loss has occurred. This can be a defence mechanism to help them cope with the pain. It is often temporary and may give the individual time to adjust to the new reality.\n\n## Anger\n\nAnger is the second stage and is often directed at those who have been perceived to be responsible for the loss, whether that is a specific person or circumstance. The individual may also feel anger towards themselves or a higher power. This stage can be difficult to cope with, but it is important to remember that anger is a normal reaction to loss.\n\n## Bargaining\n\nThe third stage, bargaining, often occurs when an individual is coming to terms with the reality of the loss. They may make deals with themselves or a higher power in an attempt to change the situation. For example, someone may bargain for more time with a loved one who is terminally ill.\n\n## Depression\n\nDepression is the fourth stage and is characterized by feelings of sadness, hopelessness, and despair. This is a natural response to loss, but it is important to seek help if the depression is severe or lasts for an extended period of time.\n\n## Acceptance\n\nThe fifth stage and final one is acceptance. In this stage, individuals come to terms with the loss and start to move on with their lives. This does not mean that they are happy about the loss, but rather that they have accepted it and are beginning to heal.\n\nAdding another stage to the 5 stages of grief: Hope\n\n## Hope\n\nI am adding this stage to the 5 stages of grief, as I believe it is an important part of the grieving process. Hope is what helps us to get through difficult times. It is what gives us the strength to keep going when we feel like we can’t. Hope is what allows us to see the light at the end of the tunnel.\n\n## Best 11 Healing crystals for grief\n\nHealing crystals can be used to help with grief as they can act as a tool to focus on and help redirect feelings that may be overwhelming. Crystals with properties such as loving, caring, and calming energy can be used to help bring peace, comfort, and understanding during a difficult time. \n\nAdditionally, crystals such as amethyst, black tourmaline, and obsidian can help to provide protection and grounding.\n\nHere is a list of the best crystals for grief that can help with sorrow for various stages of healing:\n\n## Amethyst – Emotional Healing\n\nAmethyst is part of the healing crystals for grief that can be very helpful in times of grief and sorrow. It helps overcome feelings of loss and loneliness, and can also be helpful in dealing with the death of a loved one. \n\nIts healing properties build inner strength and courage, and can also help to ease the pain of bereavement.\n\nThe stone is known as a natural tranquilizer and can help to ease the mind and body of stress and tension. When one is in deep sorrow, it can be difficult to eat or sleep. Amethyst can help to ease these symptoms and help to promote restful sleep.\n\n## Rose Quartz – Compassion and Forgiveness\n\nRose Quartz is a stone of the heart, a crystal of unconditional love. They are one of the best crystals for grief. It carries a soft feminine energy of compassion and peace, tenderness and healing, nourishment and comfort.\n\nRose Quartz speaks directly to the heart chakra, dissolving emotional wounds, fears and resentments, and circulates divine loving energy throughout the entire aura. Reawakening the heart to its own innate love, provides a deep sense of personal fulfilment and contentment, allowing one the capacity to truly give and receive love from others.\n\nRose Quartz is one of the most positive comfort crystals which heals in a healthy way using its gentle energies. Rose Quartz provides emotional comfort which helps in getting rid of negative energies and encourages one to flow freely with one’s thoughts.\n\n## Hematite – Helps to ground and protect from negative energy\n\nHematite is a powerful stone for grounding and protection. It helps to absorb negative energy and calm the mind. It can be helpful in times of grief, loss and sorrow as it helps to ground and anchor the soul. \n\nIts connection to the root chakra also makes it a helpful stone for those who are feeling lost or disconnected from their lives. When Hematite is by your side, you can’t help but feel more centered and stable.\n\n## Black Tourmaline – Protection and Grounding\n\nBlack tourmaline is a powerful stone for protection and grounding. It is also helpful in clearing away negative energy. This makes it an ideal stone for those who are grieving, as it can help to dissipate feelings of sadness, anger, and despair.\n\nThis stone is connected to the root chakra, making it helpful in stabilizing emotions and promoting a sense of security. The emotional healing powers of black tourmaline ensure that the negative effects of grief are quickly dissipated, making way for the positive emotions of hope and healing to take their place.\n\n## Smoky Quartz – Positive Energy\n\nSmoky Quartz is a powerful crystal for emotional healing and support. These are also one of the best crystals for grief. It can help to ground and center you during times of grief and loss, and can also help to release any negativity or sadness that you may be holding onto.\n\nThere is a calm energy to Smoky Quartz that can help to ease any feelings of anxiety or stress and can promote a sense of inner peace.\n\nThe association of Smoky Quartz with the Earth element can also help to promote a sense of stability and security during times of upheaval. Smoky Quartz is connected to the root chakra which balances and grounds the whole energy system. \n\nIt brings deep, calming energy and an emotional balance to the entire chakra system.\n\n## Rhodonite – Encourages emotional healing and understanding\n\nRhodonite is a stone that can be used to help ease the pain of grief and loss. It can help to bring comfort and peace to those who are grieving and can also help to release any anger or resentment that may be held in the heart. \n\nRhodonite is also a great stone for helping to heal the wounds of the past and can assist in moving on from old hurts.\n\nThe way it helps in dealing with past hurt is it amplifies your self-worth. It encourages you to love and forgive yourself so that you can start to heal the wounds of the past.\n\nWhen you start to love and forgive yourself, it becomes easier to love and forgive others. Rhodonite also helps to bring calm and peace to the mind and can be used to ease stress and anxiety.\n\nIts connection with the heart makes it a powerful crystal for healers as it can help to open up the heart chakra and to bring in love and compassion. Rhodonite helps bring balance and stability during times of stress. It is a stone of forgiveness, reconciliation and unconditional love.\n\nRhodonite can be used in crystal healing to help heal emotional wounds and traumas, to promote self-love and self-forgiveness, and to bring peace and calm to the mind. It can also be used to help balance emotions and ease stress and anxiety.\n\n## Moonstone – Emotional balance\n\nThis pearly white stone is said to be connected to the moon and to the ebb and flow of the tides. Moonstone is believed to bring light into the dark times, making it an excellent choice for those going through grief or loss.\n\nIt is a wonderful stone for letting go of the past and moving forward. Having a positive outlook and attitude is important when grieving, and moonstone is said to encourage this. Moonstone is the stone of new beginnings and is also a reminder that happiness and hope still exist.\n\nWhile this stone is best for the stage of grief where you are beginning to accept what has happened, it can also be helpful at any stage of the grieving process.\n\nIt is associated with the Crown Chakra which is the chakra of cosmic consciousness and our connection to the Divine. When going through grief, we may feel discon"
  a.category = cat
  a.published = true
  a.published_at = DateTime.parse("2023-01-07T10:55:04")
end

