Article.find_or_create_by!(slug: "how-to-know-if-a-chakra-bracelet-is-real") do |a|
  a.title = "How to know if a chakra bracelet is real?"
  a.excerpt = "Chakra bracelets are a beautiful piece of jewellery which has many spiritual benefits and plays an important role in the spiritual journey. But the key is that the chakra bracelet has to be made of real and high-quality gemstones and how to know if a chakra bracelet is real becomes important. Currently, in the market, … Read more"
  a.content = "Chakra bracelets are a beautiful piece of jewellery which has many spiritual benefits and plays an important role in the spiritual journey. But the key is that the chakra bracelet has to be made of real and high-quality gemstones and how to know if a chakra bracelet is real becomes important.\n\nCurrently, in the market, many sellers sell lower-quality versions to cut their costs. This leads to reduced spiritual benefits and the bracelet loses its original properties. Therefore, it is important to have a few checks before you purchase the chakra bracelet. Below is the complete guide which explains how to know if a chakra bracelet is real. Also answering other questions related to chakra bracelets.\n\nTable of Contents\n\nToggle\n\n• What are chakra bracelets?\n• How to know if a chakra bracelet is real?\n• Few other ways to know if a chakra bracelet is real\n• 1. Real chakra bracelets have 8 different types of beads.\n• 2. Uneven holes in the bracelet beads\n• 3. Does the chakra bracelet have colour stains\n• 4. Order of the stones\n• 5. Use nail polish remover\n\n• Understanding the chakras of chakra bracelet\n• 1st chakra: Root chakra – Black Tourmaline stone \n• 2nd Chakra: Sacral chakra – Orange Carnelian stone\n• 3rd Chakra: Solar plexus chakra – Yellow Citrine stone\n• 4th Chakra: Heart chakra – Green Aventurine stone\n• 5th Chakra: Throat chakra – Blue Lapis Lazuli stone\n• 6th Chakra: Third eye chakra – Indigo Lapis Lazuli\n• 7th Chakra: Crown chakra – Clear Quartz Crystal stone\n\n• How do chakra bracelets work?\n• What are the benefits of wearing a chakra bracelet? \n• Emotional healing benefits of chakra bracelet\n• Physical healing benefits of chakra bracelet \n• Spiritual healing benefits of chakra bracelet \n\n• How to care for a chakra bracelet?\n• How to choose the right chakra bracelet?\n• Can you wear more than one chakra bracelet?\n• How to use chakra bracelets?\n• Meditate with chakra bracelets\n\n• What are other ways of activating chakras?\n• 1. Activating chakra bracelet with the help of mantra\n• 2. Activating chakra bracelet with the help of sound\n• 3. Activating chakra bracelet with the help of light\n• 4. Activating chakra bracelet with the help of movement\n• 5. Activating chakra bracelet with the help of thoughts\n\n• Which wrist to wear a chakra bracelet\n\n## What are chakra bracelets?\n\nChakra bracelets are pieces of jewellery that are said to promote balance and well-being by aligning and clearing the chakras, or energy centers of the body. The seven chakra energy centers are located along the spine, from the base to the crown of the head. Each chakra is associated with a different colour and chakra bracelets are often made with colourful beads that correspond to the different chakras. \n\nThere is no scientific evidence to support the claim that chakra bracelets can balance or clear the chakras. However, some people believe that wearing a chakra bracelet may help them to feel more centered and grounded. Some people also find that the colors of the beads can be soothing and calming. \n\nIf you’re interested in trying a chakra bracelet, look for one that is made with high-quality materials and that has beads that are the colours of the chakras. You may also want to choose a bracelet that has a meaning or story that resonates with you. \n\nCharka bracelets have become very famous and are now found in abundance. This has led to sellers selling low-quality bracelets, hence it is important to check the authenticity of the chakra before buying them. Read on to know how to know if a chakra bracelet is real.\n\n## How to know if a chakra bracelet is real?\n\n​​There are many ways to tell if a chakra bracelet is real or not. One way is to look for a stamp of approval from a reputable organisation, such as the Better Business Bureau. Another way is to check the materials used to make the bracelet. Most real chakra bracelets will be made from natural stones, like quartz or amethyst. Below are other important checks to know if a chakra bracelet is real\n\n1. Inspect the bracelet for any signs of damage or wear and tear. A real chakra bracelet should be in good condition with no visible signs of damage. \n\n2. Check that the bracelet is made of natural materials. A real chakra bracelet will usually be made of crystals, stones or beads. \n\n3. Ask the seller if the bracelet has been cleansed and charged. A real chakra bracelet will have been cleansed and charged with positive energy before being sold. \n\n4. Test the bracelet by wearing it for a period of time. A real chakra bracelet should help to balance and align your chakras.\n\n## Few other ways to know if a chakra bracelet is real\n\n## 1. Real chakra bracelets have 8 different types of beads.\n\nMost part of the chakra bracelet is made with black beads and the rest of them with red, orange, white or purple, yellow, green and indigo make up for the remaining 25%. If the bracelet is missing any of these colours and has a different colour, it is most likely to be a fake one. \n\nMany artisans make this bracelet with other precious stones or gemstones but again, these may not be the real chakra bracelets. The most important thing is that the real chakra bracelet has to be made with high-quality precious stones. \n\n## 2. Uneven holes in the bracelet beads\n\nHold the chakra bracelet in your hands and look at the holes that are drilled in the beads. Do the holes and the edges look smooth? Or are they slightly uneven?\n\nIf the holes are uneven then it is likely to be a real chakra bracelet. If it is smooth, it means the beads are made of plastic or some other material that is easy to drill. \n\nThe real chakra bracelet is made of precious stones that are not very easy to drill. This causes the hole edges to become uneven and rough. \n\n## 3. Does the chakra bracelet have colour stains\n\nHold the chakra bracelet in your hand and pull the beads apart to see the string. If you find colour on the string, the bracelet is likely to be fake. This means the bracelet has been painted. Most of the chakra bracelets have white-coloured strings but many use other colours as well. Whatever may be the case, do check for the colours on the strings.\n\n## 4. Order of the stones\n\nThe order of the beads in the chakra bracelet has to be in the order of the rainbow colours. Red, orange, yellow, green, blue and indigo followed by purple. \n\n## 5. Use nail polish remover\n\nUse a cotton swab and rub it on the beads. If the swab picks the colour, the chakra bracelet is likely to be a fake one. Which means it has been coloured and is not authentic. \n\n## Understanding the chakras of chakra bracelet\n\nThe seven chakras are the root chakra, the sacral chakra, the solar plexus chakra, the heart chakra, the throat chakra, the third eye chakra, and the crown chakra. Each chakra is associated with a different colour, and chakra bracelets are often made with colourful beads that correspond to the different chakras.\n\n## 1st chakra: Root chakra – Black Tourmaline stone \n\nThe root chakra is located at the base of the spine. It is associated with the colour red and is said to represent grounding, security, and survival. The colour black also represents the transformation in the root chakra. \n\nIt is a colour of new beginnings, letting go of the past, and moving forward into the future. Black tourmaline stone is associated with the root chakra. It is a protective stone that grounds and balances the energy in the body. It helps to release fear and anxiety and promotes a sense of safety and security.\n\nZircon, Smoky Quartz, Garnet, Red Zincite are some other crystals related to the root chakra.\n\n## 2nd Chakra: Sacral chakra – Orange Carnelian stone\n\nThe Sacral Chakra, or Svadhisthana, is located just below the navel. It is associated with pleasure, sexuality, and creativity. When this chakra is balanced, we feel pleasure in our lives and are able to create and enjoy new experiences. When it is imbalanced, we may feel blocked creatively or sexually and may experience pain or numbness in the lower abdomen or pelvis.\n\n## 3rd Chakra: Solar plexus chakra – Yellow Citrine stone\n\nThe solar plexus chakra is located just above the navel, in the area of the solar plexus. This chakra is associated with the element of fire, and the associated qualities include a will, power, and determination. The solar plexus chakra is responsible for our personal power, and our ability to take action and make decisions. When this chakra is in balance, we feel confident and self-assured, and we are able to assert our own power and authority. \n\nWhen the solar plexus chakra is out of balance, we may feel powerless, or we may have difficulty making decisions. We may also feel disconnected from our personal power, and our ability to take action. The colour of this chakra is yellow. \n\nYellow colour is associated with the sun, and with the element of fire. When worn as jewellery it helps with motivation and willpower. Those who are seeking to increase their personal power, or to find their purpose in life, may benefit from wearing solar plexus chakra jewellery. \n\n## 4th Chakra: Heart chakra – Green Aventurine stone\n\nThe heart chakra, or Anahata, is the fourth chakra. It is situated in the center of the chest and is associated with the element of air. The heart chakra is the chakra of love, compassion, and forgiveness. Its energy is expansive and open, and it is through this chakra that we connect with others and the world around us. \n\nWhen the heart chakra is balanced, we feel compassion and love for ourselves and others, and we are able to forgive. When it is out of balance, we may feel closed off, judgmental, and resentful. The colour associated with the heart chakra is green. \n\nThe green stone within your chakra bracelet is present to promote and encourage a healthy balance of the heart chakra. If you are having trouble with your heart chakra, try meditating with green stones, such as jade, emerald, or green tourmaline.\n\n## 5th Chakra: Throat chakra – Blue Lapis Lazuli stone\n\nThe Throat Chakra is l"
  a.category = cat
  a.published = true
  a.published_at = DateTime.parse("2022-08-14T08:58:58")
end

